title: layered banana pineapple dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs in large bowl.
Add sugar and margarine and press mixture evenly on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Arrange bananas on bottom of pan.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually add milk.
Add pudding mix.
Beat until blended.
Spread evenly over banana slices.
Spoon pineapple over pudding mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Refrigerate 3 hours.

title: clam dip or spread
directions: Saute garlic, onion, parsley and oregano in butter about 2 minutes.
Mix with clams and juice.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Can also be used as "baked clams" in party shells.

title: barbecued chicken breasts
directions: Cut all fat off chicken breast pieces, then wash the chicken. Pour barbecue sauce in a bowl to dip breasts in.
Cover the chicken good in barbecue sauce.

title: cheerwine punch
directions: Shake the cans of grapefruit-pineapple drink.
Place these in freezer.
Remove from freezer about 4 hours before serving.
Place in a punch bowl and break apart.
Pour the Cheerwine over the slushy mixture.
Serves 45 (4 ounce) cups.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Layer all in a 7 x 12-inch pan in order written.
Bake at 300° (325°) for 1 hour.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Gradually stir milk and egg into pudding mix in saucepan.
Add rice and raisins.
Stir over medium heat until mixture just comes to a boil.
Pour into bowl.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: bacon quiche
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Cook onion in bacon drippings until tender.
Drain well.
Beat together eggs, cream and salt.
Stir in bacon and onion.
Toss cheese with flour.
Place in frozen pie shell.
Pour egg mixture over.
Bake at 325° on cookie sheet for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted midway comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Let oatmeal stand in water for 3 minutes.
Mix all ingredients with spoon and pour in pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix everything together at least 2 hours prior to serving. Store in refrigerator.

title: stuffed crab
directions: Melt butter and olive oil.
Add seasonings; cook until wilted. Soak toasted bread in water and squeeze until dry.
Chop bread and add to seasoning.
Cook for 1/2 hour on low heat, stirring occasionally.
Add crab meat, cayenne pepper and salt to taste. If dry, add 1/2 stick of butter.
Stuff cleaned crab shells or put in casserole with bread crumbs sprinkled on top.
Top with pieces of butter.
Before serving, put in oven for 20 minutes on low heat.

title: sausage cheese bread
directions: Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until center puffs.
I double the recipe for a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Blend cottage cheese in blender until smooth.
Pour into bowl and stir in Hi-Energy Vanilla Supplements.
Stir in strawberries next.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together until smooth.
Add egg yolks one at a time, beating well.
Add sifted flour to mixture alternately with buttermilk, soda and salt.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites last.
Bake in three 8-inch greased layer cake pans at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk in one bowl.
Mix sour cream and Cool Whip together with pudding.
Put vanilla wafers in bottom of loaf pan, then mixture of pudding, sour cream and Cool Whip, then bananas.
Probably will make 2 to 3 layers, depending on size of pan.

title: o'dolly cookies
directions: Melt butter, then add graham cracker crumbs and pat firmly. Add chocolate chips.
Add butterscotch chips and nuts.
Pour evenly Eagle Brand milk.
Sprinkle on coconut.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple pudding-n-pie
directions: Grease a pie plate with butter and fill it with thinly sliced apples.
Mix 1/2 cup of sugar and the cinnamon and sprinkle over the apples.
Dot with 1 tablespoon of butter.

title: mazola oil pie crust
directions: Mix together and press in pie pans.
Makes 2 (9-inch) crusts.

title: cocktail sausages
directions: Slice sausage in pieces (1/4-inch thick).
Place in crock-pot. Add chili sauce and jelly.
Cook on low for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: fruit cake
directions: Bake for 30 minutes at 250° and 30 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut custard pie(also known as impossible pie)
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Blend on low.
Pour into 9-inch greased (Pam works great) pie pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain well.
Cook noodles and beans while beef browns.
Combine cooked beef, beans and noodles.
Add tomato soup and water.
Add salt, pepper, etc., if desired.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Pour into casserole dish; top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Delicious!!

title: mustard glaze
directions: Combine ingredients.
Brush mixture on ham frequently during the last hour of baking.
Makes 1 cup (enough for 10 to 13 pound ham).
May be used on roast, chicken or turkey or as a dipping sauce for shrimp or chicken nuggets.

title: pork chop rice dinner
directions: Heat oil in heavy 12-inch skillet on medium high heat.
Add pork chops for 4 minutes on each side until browned.
Remove chops, set aside.
Reduce heat to low and add onion and rice. Cook for 1 minute, stirring.
Add green pepper, water, tomatoes, black pepper and 1 teaspoon salt.
Bring to boil.
Place pork chops on top of rice mixture.
Cover skillet.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes or until the rice is tender and pork chops are fully cooked.
Add 1/4 cup water after 15 minutes if mixture seems dry.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until done; drain.
Melt butter and blend in flour, salt, pepper and garlic, if desired.
Add chicken broth. Cook and stir until thickened.
Stir in half and half.
Place broccoli crosswise in a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour half of the sauce over the broccoli.
Top with chicken.
Pour remaining sauce over chicken; add mushrooms on top.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: southwestern biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add and cut in the shortening using a pastry blender or two knives until mixture has the consistency of coarse crumbs.
Add remaining ingredients, adding more milk, if necessary, so dough is pliable but is still wet.
Turn dough onto a heavily floured surface and knead it lightly (8 to 10 times).
Do not overwork dough.
Roll dough to even thickness of 3/4 to 1-inch and cut out biscuits with a 2-inch round cutter (size of juice can), dipping cutter between cutting each biscuit so they won't stick.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake in center of oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve immediately or bake up to 2 hours in advance and reheat 5 minutes at 300°.
Makes 12 to 14 biscuits.

title: chow chow
directions: Cut up vegetables and mix together.
Add 2 handfuls of canning salt.
Let stand overnight.
Next day, drain.
Boil vinegar and water; mix with vegetables.
Add sugar and boil until nearly tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pack in sterilized jars and seal.
Can be put in a canner and boiled a while if preferred, but not necessary.

title: hash quiche
directions: Combine roast and 1 beaten egg.
Press lightly in greased pie plate to form a crust.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Add celery and onion and place in the crust.
Mix together 3 beaten eggs and Bisquick.
Blend in milk and stir until smooth and pour over the vegetables; bake at 375° until vegetables are tender.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: caramel graham crackers
directions: Boil the brown sugar and oleo.
Stir to blend.
Line jelly roll pan with graham crackers and pour mixture over crackers. Sprinkle with chopped pecans. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Remove from pan immediately and cool on wax paper.

title: squash delight
directions: Alternately layer squash, onions and sliced tomatoes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Place in microwave oven and cook on High power, 30 to 45 minutes, depending on size of casserole and oven wattage.

title: cold yam salad
directions: Mix together sour cream, lemon juice, sugar and spices.
In a large bowl, combine yams, celery and onion.
Add most of the sour cream dressing and mix well.
Chill for 2 hours or overnight. Serve it in a bowl lined with salad greens, topped with reserved dressing.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mash artichokes after drained.
Mix everything else with the artichokes.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Watch until it bubbles; keep and serve warm.
Spread on crackers.
Delicious and real popular.

title: glazed apricot sweet potatoes
directions: In large
saucepan
bring
to a boil apricot and next 5 ingredients.
Boil	gently 2 minutes.
Reduce heat to low; add potatoes and
stir	gently	to
coat.
Cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes
until
potatoes are heated through.
Place in serving dish and garnish with lemon peel.
Makes 12 servings.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° in glass dish until golden brown.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: oven baked chicken
directions: Place chicken on foil in baking dish.
Sprinkle soup mix and Creole seasoning evenly over all.
Wrap loosely with foil and bake 45 to 60 minutes in a 375° oven.
Open foil last 10 minutes of cooking time to allow to brown.
Serves 6.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers thin.
Add thinly sliced onions.
Mix in salt. Cover with two trays of ice cubes and let stand 3 hours.
Drain in colander.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to boil in large pot.
Put in cucumbers and onions.
Bring to boil again.
Remove and put in hot jars.

title: turkey quesadillas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wrap tortillas in foil and heat in oven for 8 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a 12-inch skillet, heat oil over moderate heat.
Add onion and red pepper; saute, stirring occasionally, until onion is soft.
Add the turkey and salt to the skillet; saute, stirring, until the turkey is no longer pink.
Add the garlic, cumin, chili powder, oregano and optional jalapeno pepper.
Saute, stirring, for 1 minute or until mixture is dry. Stir in the tomato sauce and cilantro.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix margarine, cream cheese and 10x sugar in mixer.
Mix vanilla pudding and milk until thick in blender.
Layer and chill.

title: white texas sheet cake
directions: In a large sauce pan, bring butter and water to a boil. Remove from heat; stir in flour, sugar, eggs, sour cream, almond extract, salt, and baking soda until smooth.
Pour into a greased 15 x 10 x 1 inch jelly roll baking pan.
Bake at 375 degrees for 20 to 22 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool for 20 minutes. Meanwhile, prepare frosting.
Pour and spread over warm cake.

title: dutch triple fudge cake
directions: Cook pudding as directed on package.
Blend in cake mix (dry). Pour into prepared oblong pan, 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup chocolate chips and 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Add all ingredients and mix. Refrigerate.

title: rice consomme
directions: Melt butter.
Combine ingredients.
Bake in covered casserole dish 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: hamburger mac-casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Place in buttered casserole dish. Melt butter in double boiler.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Blend. Add milk slowly until sauce thickens.
Add shredded cheese. Fry hamburger meat.
Drain fat and combine with macaroni.
Mix thoroughly.
Add sauce and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Whip whipping cream with 2 tablespoons sugar until stiff. Just before serving, combine rice, pineapple, whipped cream and sugar.

title: no-fat crabmeat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with veggies or crackers.

title: western casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together, drain off all fat.
Stir in corn, beans, soup, cheese, milk and chili powder.
Bring to a boil.
Turn into casserole, alternating with tortillas.
Heat in oven or microwave until hot.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Combine ingredients; mix. Press firmly into 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes or until edges are browned; cool. For unbaked crust, chill 45 minutes; fill.

title: texas caviar
directions: Dice above ingredients together.
Marinate overnight in salad dressing. Season with salt and pepper, if desired.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Break eggs and beat.
Drain salmon; remove skin and bones. Add to eggs and bread crumbs.
Salt, butter and milk are added last.
Grease pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet and place them in a casserole dish.
Put the onion and green pepper on top of them.
Place the potatoes around the pork chops.
Add the tomato soup and 1/2 can of water.
Cover and cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown chops in fat; salt and pepper to taste.
Place in bottom of greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine other ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover and bake until tender in 325° oven.

title: old fashioned mints
directions: Have margarine at room temperature.
Put 1/2 cup sifted powdered sugar
and
the
butter in mixer and cream.
Add milk and mix
again.
Add 1 cup powdered sugar and cream again. Add food coloring
and
oil	of
peppermint. Add most of powdered sugar and
cream together until doughy.
Knead on bread board or wax paper. Add a small amount of powdered sugar until dough holds together.
Pinch off about 1/2 cup. Roll into long rope. Cut off pieces with scissors onto wax paper.
Air dry several hours before storage.

title: bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Bacon should be crumbled.)

title: chocolate lush
directions: Meanwhile mix together and set aside the cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Mix instant chocolate or butterscotch pudding (use only 1 3/4 c. milk).
Spread layer of cream cheese mixture over cooled crust.
Spread out pudding mixture.
Now spread remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: grilled chicken
directions: Melt margarine.
Add honey and 1/2 package dressing in a bowl or pan.
Dip chicken in mixture or marinade for a short time. Throw on grill for approximately 20 minutes, turning frequently.

title: cheese squares
directions: Mix brown sugar, margarine, flour and walnuts until crumbly. Reserve 1 cup.
Press remainder in 9 x 13 pan and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Blend sugar, lemon juice, milk, vanilla, cream cheese and eggs.
Pour over baked crust.
Sprinkle reserved mixture over filling.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Refrigerate.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to boil; cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast dissolved in water.
Stir in 2 1/2 cups sifted flour (may use hand beater).
Let stand in warm place for 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients sifted together; mix well.
May put into refrigerator until next day.
Shape into rolls.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 425°.
Bake sweet buns for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: pan fried fish deep-fry
directions: Coat fish in combined dry ingredients.
Dip in combined egg and water.
Coat again in dry ingredients.
Pan fry in margarine and oil until fish flakes easily with fork.
Drain on paper towels.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: reese's cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, cream shortening, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour and baking soda; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in peanut butter chips and chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool slightly; remove to wire racks and cool completely. Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix Cool Whip, sugar, and cheese and set aside.
Lightly grease pizza pan.
Slice cookie dough 1/4 inch thick; lay in pan and smooth together to make crust.
Cook per directions.
Cool. Spread cheese mixture over crust.
Arrange fruit and top with glaze. Suggested fruits:
peaches, strawberries, pineapple, grapes, pears, mandarin oranges, strawberries, bananas, kiwi fruit.

title: southern biscuits
directions: *If using self-rising flour, omit baking powder and salt.

title: walnut cake(recipe for 2 cakes)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place the Crisco in an electric mixer bowl, gradually add the sugar and beat on medium speed at least 10 minutes.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Toss the chopped walnuts with the remaining tablespoon flour and set aside.
Add the eggs to the creamed mixture, beating well.
Combine the milk with the vanilla and almond extracts.
Alternately add the flour mixture and milk to the creamed mixture, beating well after each addition.
Add the chopped walnuts and beat on low speed until well blended.
Pour batter into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake for 50 minutes or until done.
Cool for 10 minutes in pans.
Invert on racks.
Frost with the Chocolate Walnut Buttercream (recipe follows).

title: simple custard delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium-size bowl, combine sugar and flour.
Mix well with a wire whisk.
Add milk, oil, egg substitute, salt and vanilla.
Mix well with wire whisk.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook onions, green peppers, celery and garlic in hot oil until tender.
Add tomatoes, paste and seasonings; simmer 45 minutes. Mix cornstarch with 2 teaspoons cold water; stir into sauce.
Add shrimp and simmer 10 minutes more.
Spoon over cooked rice. Yield: 8 servings.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook and drain beef.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over hamburger buns and grated Cheddar cheese.

title: burrito sauce
directions: Put all ingredients into large saucepan; simmer for 1 hour. Dip onto Burritos.

title: buster bar surprise
directions: Crush Oreo cookies, reserving 1/2 cup.
Combine remaining cookies with the melted butter.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: individual meat loaves
directions: Cook meat and onion in fat until meat has lost its color and onion is soft.
Combine with other ingredients.
Fill muffin tins or custard cups with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair pie
directions: Mix each pudding with 1 1/2 c. milk. Fold 8 oz. of whipped topping into each pudding. In a 9 x 13 pan, layer graham crackers, 1/2 vanilla pudding mixture.

More crackers, 1/2 chocolate pudding mixture. Crackers, remaining vanilla pudding, crackers, and remaining chocolate pudding. Top with layer of crackers and frost with chocolate frosting. Refrigerate 8 hours before serving. Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake pizza crust according to package directions.
Whip cream cheese, sugar and sour cream together.
Spread on pizza. Wash and drain vegetables; cut up and place on top raw.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Combine green tomatoes, onions, green pepper red pepper and sprinkle lightly with pickling salt.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain and rinse.
Add: vinegar, sugar and
brown sugar.
Place in cheese cloth bag and add to above the following: cloves, cinnamon sticks, mustard seed and
allspice. Bring vegetable and syrup slowly to boil.
Reduce heat and cook slowly about 1 hour.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: quick pork chops with rice
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper. Saute in a small amount of oil until browned on both sides.
Place rice in a 7 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour orange juice over rice. Arrange browned chops on rice and pour soup over chops. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: easy cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons of margarine, brown sugar, nuts and water. Place in Bundt pan.
Mix white sugar and cinnamon together.
Dip each biscuit in margarine mixture, then into cinnamon mixture. Place biscuits on end in pan.
Pinch sides or tips together.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Turn onto plate.

title: cookie candies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix margarine, powdered sugar and vanilla. Stir in flour, oats and salt. Shape dough by teaspoonfuls into balls, crescents, triangles and bars.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake until edges are golden brown, 19 to 20 minutes (watch carefully). Cool.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix and sprinkle over souffle. Bake 35 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: filled cheese
directions: Scoop out cheese and save shell.
Break up cheese and mix to taste with Worcestershire sauce, mustard, chives and olives.
Put mixture back into shell.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: "holiday dinner rolls"
directions: Heat first four ingredients until sugar is dissolved.
Let cool until warm.
Mix yeast, 1/2 teaspoon sugar and water separately. After yeast is dissolved, add to margarine mixture.
Then add egg and 4 cups flour.
Mix good, then add 1 more cup flour.
Let rise until double.
Stir down, chill (4 to 5 hours).
Put 3 teaspoons of dough per muffin cup in muffin pan.
Dip in melted margarine before putting in pan, let rise.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: onion rye appetizers
directions: In a bowl, combine the onions, bacon, mayonnaise and Swiss cheese. Spread about 1 teaspoon of pizza sauce on each slice of bread.
Top with about 1 tablespoon of the cheese mixture.
Bake on an ungreased baking sheet at 350° for 12 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted.

title: no crust egg pie
directions: Grease and dust with flour a 10-inch pie pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: banana split salad
directions: Mix pudding with pineapple as they are from the can. Mix all other ingredients, except Cool Whip. After well mixed, fold in Cool Whip.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until mixture is bubbling in the center.
Then top with crushed corn flakes and slivered almonds and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until light brown.

title: rich krispies balls
directions: Melt caramels, butter and milk.
Dip marshmallows in mixture and roll in Rice Krispies.
Makes 50 to 60 balls.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters with scissors.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and drop quartered biscuits into mixture, coating well. Butter a Bundt pan and put quartered biscuits into pan.
Bring the butter and brown sugar to a boil and boil for 2 to 3 minutes. Pour over biscuits and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This is also called Pull-a-parts.

title: texas casserole
directions: Fry beef and drain grease.
Add onions and cook until translucent.
Add beans, tomatoes, soups, dash of hot sauce and enchilada sauce.
Heat to a slow boil.
Quarter tortillas and heat in oven until crisp.
Place in long pan and cover with meat mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Hot! For cool version, substitute 1 can pinto beans and 1 can tomatoes.

title: apple crunchie
directions: Cut apples into a small greased baking pan; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Squeeze the lemon over the apple/cinnamon.
Cream honey and butter; mix in the grains and seed to make a crunchy topping. Sprinkle over the apples.
Sprinkle cider on top before baking at 375° for 35 minutes.
Serve with cream as a breakfast treat or dessert.

title: 7 hour wheat and white bread
directions: Combine water, sugar and molasses.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup of this mixture and set aside.
Mix wheat flour into remaining mixture.
Add yeast mixture and let stand 1 hour.
Scald milk, salt and oil.
Let cool to room temperature and add to wheat mixture. Stir in 12 cups white flour.
Knead into this as much additional white flour as necessary to keep dough from sticking to hands.
Let rise for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Punch down and cut into 5 loaves.
Let rise in well-greased loaf pans until doubled in size, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 400°.
Bake pie on cookie sheet.
In large saucepan, melt chocolate and margarine. Gradually add milk and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour in pie crust. Bake 40 minutes at 400°.
Cool completely.

title: cottage pie
directions: Boil the potatoes; drain and mash them with the milk, butter and seasoning.
Fry the onion for about 5 minutes and mix with the minced meat with a little stock and mixed herbs.

title: seafood newberg
directions: Saute onions and seafood in margarine.
Add seasonings, then milk and bring almost to a boil.
Add cornstarch mixed with warm water to thicken.
Stir until desired thickness.
Serve over fettucini noodles or baked potatoes, topped with cheese.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Put margarine, oil, cocoa and water in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Sift together flour and sugar and add the chocolate mixture.
Then add the buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla. Mix well.
Pour into a jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: puffed popcorn
directions: Pour popcorn in roaster. In a 2-quart saucepan, combine brown sugar, butter and syrup. Stir for 2 minutes. Add baking soda and stir. Pour over popcorn and bake at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: chewy cake
directions: Mix together.
Spread evenly into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Place pan into a cold oven and turn oven to 300°.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: nutty carrot cake
directions: Mix good all together and frost cake.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, nutmeg and butter.
Add eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over rhubarb in 9-inch pastry-lined pie pan.
Top with pastry.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes, then in moderate oven of 350° about 30 minutes.

title: ground turkey meat loaf
directions: *To make cracker crumbs, I place crackers in a Ziploc bag. Close the bag and, using a rolling pin, crush the crackers as fine as you want them; no mess!

title: poppy seed roll
directions: Grind poppy seed.
Add sugar.
Mix in just enough boiling water to dissolve poppy seed and sugar.
Should be like a thick paste.
Let this mixture set for hours.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips in a large pan.
Remove from heat and stir in cereal.
Coat well.
With buttered hands, shape into small ball.
Shake in a bag of powdered sugar.

title: grandma's chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Add shortening and mix well.
Add water and mix well.
Roll out 2 crusts.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Beat butter to soften.
Add brown sugar; beat until fluffy. Add flour and walnuts; set aside 1 cup of this mixture.
Press remaining mixture into bottom of ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: stir-fried chicken and snow peas
directions: Cut chicken into bite-sized strips.
Blend together soy sauce, sherry, water, ginger and garlic in a bowl.
Mix with chicken and let stand for 30 minutes.
Pour oil in electric frypan or wok. Heat about 5 minutes, then add the marinated chicken, onions, mushrooms and snow peas.
Saute about 5 minutes, stirring constantly until chicken is tender and vegetables are crisp. Yields 4 servings, 250 calories per serving.

title: old fashioned bread stuffing
directions: In a saucepan, cook celery and onion in butter until tender but not brown.
Remove from heat and stir in sage, salt and pepper.
Place the dry bread cubes in a large mixing bowl.
Add the onion mixture.
Drizzle with enough broth to moisten, tossing lightly.
Use to stuff one 10-pound turkey.

title: dill pickles
directions: Scrub cucumbers; rinse well and pack into hot sterilized jars. Heat water and vinegar.
Stuff 2 heads of dill in each jar and a piece of garlic and add the salt.
Fill each jar with hot brine. Seal at once.
Allow 6 to 8 weeks before using.

title: beanie wienies
directions: Mix pork beans, barbecue sauce, syrup, butter and ketchup. Then cut hot dogs up and stir in.
Heat oven to 375° and cook about 10 to 15 minutes or until hot dogs are done.

title: basic oil and vinegar dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve over your favorite salad. Delicious!

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Place in order listed in baking dish including buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Beat and mix eggs and water.
Add sugar, then extracts.
Fold in flour and salt.
Beat egg whites with 1/4 teaspoon salt and 3/4 teaspoon cream of tartar until stiff peaks form.
Fold into yolk mixture.
Pour into ungreased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan squares
directions: Cream
oleo, add small amounts of sugar and cream.
Add eggs, vanilla
and flour (put salt and baking powder in flour and sift into mixture).
Stir well, add nuts and put into a 13 x
x 9-inch pan that has been lightly greased and floured. Bake
at 350° (depending on your oven) for 25 minutes.
Do not overbake. Sprinkle
white powdered sugar on top while hot and cut into squares.

title: orange punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in a punch bowl.
Float sherbet on top.

title: applesauce jello
directions: Heat applesauce.
Add Jell-O, then cool.
Add pop and orange juice.
Refrigerate to set.

title: broccoli and ham salad
directions: Trim off large leaves or broccoli.
Remove rough ends of lower stalks.
Wash broccoli; chop coarsely.
Combine broccoli, ham, cheese, red pepper and onion in a large serving bowl.
Toss gently.

title: family meat loaf ring
directions: Combine brown sugar, tomato sauce and mustard.
Set aside. Combine beef, onion, cracker crumbs, eggs, salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 cup of the tomato sauce mixture and stir until well mixed.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix together and pour over the batter and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
(I usually double the recipe and use a 13 x 9-inch pan.
It will take approximately 60 minutes at 375°.)

title: glazed meatballs
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, onion, milk, egg and seasonings.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Brown in large skillet.
Remove and drain fat. Heat chili sauce and jelly in skillet until jelly melts, stirring constantly.
Add meatballs and stir until coated.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve hot in chafing dish with toothpicks.
Makes approximately 50 meatballs.

title: wine cookies
directions: Cream sugar & margarine.
Add other ingredients & mix well. Roll
into knots.
Dip in sugar.
Put on greased cookie sheet and bake 350° for 15-20 mins.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Combine broccoli with onion and cook as directed on package. Drain and combine with rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Spoon over 2-3 pounds of chicken.
Bake at 375° for 45-60 minutes.

title: sweetheart trifle
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Pour batter into greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done. Cool.

title: coney island chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion until no more grease is left in pan (very, very well done).
Add chili powder and paprika to meat and stir in approximately 1/2 cup water and simmer for 10 minutes. Add more water, if desired.
It should be thick, not watery.

title: favorite fish chowder
directions: In Dutch oven or soup kettle, saute onion in the butter.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Add potatoes; cook 10 minutes.
Add fish and lemon juice.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add milk, evaporated milk, salt and pepper.
Garnish with parsley and serve piping hot.

title: 12 serving punch
directions: Mix together, serve over ice ring or cubes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into lightly greased muffin pan.
Bake at 450° until golden brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, cloves and ginger.
Cream together sugar and eggs.
Stir in oil.
Mix well. Stir in pumpkin.
Stir flour mixture into the creamed mixture. Fold in 1 cup chopped pecans.
(Mix the chopped pecans with a tablespoon of the flour mixture before folding into the batter.) Pour into well-greased pans.

title: chocolate ice cream brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to package directions in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Let cool in pan.
Spread ice cream over brownies; freeze until hardened.

title: chickpea dip(great)
directions: Blend in blender olive oil, garlic, salt, pepper, comino and lemon juice until well blended.
Then blend in chickpeas a little at a time.
Very good on crackers or pita bread.

title: glazed sweet potato wedges
directions: Cut each potato lengthwise into 8 wedges.
Place margarine in an 8 inch square baking dish; microwave on high for 30 seconds, or until melted.
Stir in orange juice and cinnamon; add potatoes, tossing to coat.
Cover with wax paper; microwave on high for 6 to 8 minutes or until tender, stirring and turning dish once during cooking time.
Garnish with orange slices and parsley, if desired. Yield: 4 servings.

title: baby ruth drop cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in other ingredients.
Chill.
Drop by half teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until edges of cookies are brown.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients and knead with your hands until smooth.
Shape into block 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into squares and let harden.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Grind vegetables in food chopper and let stand overnight. Drain well.
Add finely cut celery, celery seed and black pepper. Dilute vinegar with water, add sugar and bring to boiling point. Add other ingredients.
Boil 20 minutes and put into sterilized jars and seal.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Press out sugar cookie dough on lightly greased round pizza pan or regular baking sheet, baking at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
(I usually go for golden brown.)
While crust is baking, combine cream cheese, vanilla and sugar until smooth.
When crust is completely cooled, spread mixture on top. Place sliced strawberries on top.
Spread top with strawberry glaze.
Refrigerate until chilled or serving time.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together.
Add just enough milk to make a paste.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add balance of milk, a little at a time until blended well.
Cook on medium heat until mixture is thick.
Remove from heat and add coconut and flavoring and stir.
Let cool and pour into baked pie crust and top with Cool Whip.
If mixture is too thick, you can add a little milk before you place in crust.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix oil, sugar, molasses and eggs.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, soda, cloves, ginger, cinnamon and salt.
Add to wet ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.
Form into balls and roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except sour cream, and pour 1/2 into oblong dish or fruit bowl.
Let this jell. Then pour sour cream on top.
Pour remaining mixture over sour cream.
Let this jell.
May be served as a salad or dessert.

title: microwave raisin sauce with ham
directions: In 2-cup glass measuring cup, combine water and raisins. Micro on High for 2 minutes.
Stir in sugar, orange juice, cornstarch and cloves.
Micro, uncovered, on High 2 1/2 to 3 minutes, or until mixture boils and thickens, stirring halfway through cooking time.
Remove from micro, add white vinegar, stir. Makes 1 1/2 cups sauce.
Place ham on microsafe plate, single layer.
Micro on High 4 to 6 minutes.
Serve with sauce.
Serves 4.

title: gullivers corn
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and simmer for 5 minutes.
Mix melted butter and flour (roux).
Add to corn mixture; simmer 5 to 10 minutes more until thickened.

title: zeelicious potato pancakes
directions: Put on apron, this gets sloppy!!

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put drained beans in a bowl.
Slice water chestnuts over beans. Saute onions and mushrooms together in margarine.
Pour over top of beans.
Mix soup, soy sauce and half of the mushroom liquid together.
Pour over beans.
Bake, covered, for 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and cover with French fried onions. Bake, uncovered, for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat in skillet. Boil potatoes until done (not mashed). In large saucepan, mix meat, kidney beans, water, chili sauce, tomato sauce, dash of salt and pepper, potatoes and onion (if desired). Cook on medium heat until chili has thickened. Serve hot, topped with shredded cheese and oyster crackers.

title: sweet pickle chips
directions: Bring to a boil the vinegar, salt and sugar.
Tie in a cloth bag the pickling spices.
Dunk the spices in the boiling syrup for 3 minutes.
Take out spices for next day.
Pour syrup over sliced pickles.

title: chicken in lemon-dill sauce
directions: In a large skillet, cook chicken in butter and oil until brown. Remove chicken and keep warm.
In same pan, add garlic.
Cook 1 minute.
Sprinkle in flour; mix until well blended.
Stir in milk and wine mixture.
Cook until slightly thick, stirring occasionally.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes until chicken is done.
Stir in lemon juice and dill. Serve over cooked spinach fettuccini, if desired.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick of the margarine with the cracker crumbs.
Press in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
Beat for 15 minutes with an electric mixer eggs, margarine and powdered sugar.
Spread over crust.
Cover with sliced bananas, then pineapple, Cool Whip, chopped nuts and cherries.
Cover and refrigerate.
Keep covered.

title: syrup pie
directions: Cream syrup, sugar, oleo and eggs.
Add flour, milk and spices.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Combine cake mix, salad dressing, eggs, water and cinnamon. Mix at medium speed until well blended.
Stir in carrots and walnuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool and frost.
Serves 12.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Place yeast and warm water in a large mixing bowl.
Add beaten egg and melted margarine to yeast and then add sugar.
Add flour and mix well.
Drop by spoonful into a well-greased muffin pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
You may refrigerator dough and use later.

title: tuna cheese burgers
directions: Mix tuna, onion, green olives, Cheddar cheese and mayonnaise. Spread hamburger buns with mustard.
Spread with tuna mixture. Wrap in foil and bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Warm tortillas in frypan.
Place equal amounts of scrambled eggs on each tortilla.
Spoon on salsa (to taste).
Sprinkle on grated cheese.
Enjoy!!!

title: crisp lime pickles
directions: First Day:
Wash and slice cucumbers 1/4-inch thick.
Soak in lime water 24 hours.
Do not use metal pan.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, flour and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, cream, butter, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Stir slightly about every 15 minutes, until the top starts to set.

title: buttermilk baked chicken
directions: Dip chicken in 1/2 cup buttermilk and roll in seasoned flour. Melt margarine in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Put chicken in pan, skin side down.
Bake at 425°
for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken over and bake 15 minutes.
Mix remaining buttermilk with soup and pour around chicken.
Bake about 25 minutes more or until tender.

title: munchies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put on 2 baking sheets.
Bake at 250° for 15 minutes for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: layered salsa dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and cottage cheese together.
Spread in bottom of baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Layer remaining ingredients. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: black-eyed skillet dinner
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and green pepper in skillet over medium heat until beef is brown.
Stir to crumble beef; drain. Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, stirring often.
If more liquid is needed, add tomato juice.

title: german sweet chocolate pie
directions: Heat chocolate and a tablespoon of the milk in a saucepan over low heat, stirring until chocolate is melted.
Beat sugar into cream cheese.
Add remaining milk and chocolate mixture; beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping, blending until smooth. Spoon into crust and freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Remove from freezer 30 minutes before serving and keep chilled in refrigerator.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine dressing and mayonnaise
and add rest of ingredients. Chill.
Serve with
slice of chicken breast and roll. Nice ladies luncheon salad.

title: crispy chicken nuggets
directions: In a large frying pan or deep-fat fryer, heat 1 inch of oil to 350°.
Meanwhile, put milk in a bowl.

In a paper bag, mix together the flour, Parmesan cheese, paprika, oregano and mustard. First dip chicken pieces in milk, then place about a dozen pieces of chicken at a time in a bag and shake to coat.
Fry chicken in hot oil in batches without crowding, turning occasionally, for about 5 minutes, until crisp and golden brown.
Drain on paper towel and serve hot.

title: rice 'n easy supper salad
directions: Cook rice mix and cool.
Mix rice with chicken, tomatoes, parsley, green onions, black olives and toasted almonds.
Stir vinegar into evaporated milk until milk thickens.
Add mayonnaise and Italian seasoning.
Stir into rice mixture and chill thoroughly.
Yields 6 1/2 cups.

title: baked custard
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and salt lightly to mix.
Scald milk, nutmeg and vanilla and pour into egg mixture.
Strain into 6 custard cups and set into pan of hot water (1 inch up on cups).
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Serve cool or chilled.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain off fat and add a few tablespoons of water.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Add Tater Tots on top and then spread soup over Tater Tots.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Uncover and brown for 15 minutes.

title: best chocolate cake(one bowl)
directions: In one bowl, mix together sugar, flour, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add eggs, milk, oil, vanilla and boiling water.
Mixture will be thin.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) baking pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes
or until springs back when touched in the middle.

title: microwave pecan brittle
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole stir together sugar and syrup. Microwave at High 4 minutes.
Then stir in pecans and microwave 4 minutes.
Then add oleo and vanilla, blending well, and microwave 1 1/2 minutes more.
Take out of microwave and add soda.
Gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Let cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
When cool break into small pieces and store in airtight container.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, salt, eggs, 1/4 cup butter, milk and vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth. Combine flour, nuts and 1/2 cup butter.
Put on stop of sweet potato mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.

title: raisin ham sauce
directions: Mix sugar, rind, mustard and cornstarch; stir in orange juice. Bring to boil and cook, stirring until thick, about 5 minutes. Add raisins and drippings; cook 3 to 4 minutes longer. Add ginger ale and spoon over sliced ham. Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: hot curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit, combine sugar, margarine and curry powder.
Stir until blended.
Combine fruit in shallow baking dish.
Add sauce. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: terrific turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and form a loaf.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Do not overcook.
May cover part of cooking time.

title: three cheese chicken bake
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in margarine until tender. Stir in soup, mushrooms, pimentos and basil; set aside.

title: good gravy
directions: Let flour cook in butter for one minute.
Add remaining ingredients and let thicken.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese until smooth.
Mix cocoa and sugar; add cheese mix.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased pan.
Cool and cut.
Makes 6 1/2 pounds.

title: a quick easy barbecue sauce(for chicken)
directions: Mix sauce, pour over chicken pieces in a pan. Cook 1 hour or until tender, at 350 degrees.

title: blueberry loaf
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together dry ingredients; add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla. Add mashed blueberries.
Stir in whole blueberries.
Pour batter into a greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle top with granulated sugar. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: stromboli
directions: Roll out dough to a long rectangle.
Combine the next 5 ingredients and spread half on each rectangle 1/2-inch from edge. Layer ham, pepperoni, rice, sausage and cheese.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Seal edges and ends.
Lay on cookie sheet, sealed edges down.
Let rise.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Slice and dip in pizza sauce.
Layer meats and cheeses rather thinly or you won't be able to roll it up.

title: microwave trout almondine(cooking time 7 to 9 minutes)
directions: In a small bowl, melt the 1/3 cup of butter in microwave oven for 30 seconds.
Add almonds and heat, uncovered, in microwave oven for 4 minutes or until lightly browned.
Stir occasionally. Set almonds aside.
Arrange fish in a shallow 2-quart baking dish. Place 1 tablespoon of butter on each fish and sprinkle with lemon juice and salt and pepper to taste.
Heat, covered with wax paper, 5 to 7 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Spoon browned almonds over fish and heat, covered, in microwave oven 2 minutes or until heated through.
Yields 4 servings.

title: dirt
directions: You will also need a new flowerpot (plastic is best) and silk flowers.

title: fritos salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and set aside. Just before serving, add the Fritos, cheese and Catalina dressing.
Mix well and serve.
Serves 10.

title: snowball cake
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water; add boiling water, sugar, salt, lemon juice and pineapple.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Cool completely.
Prepare 1/2 of the dessert topping and fold into first mixture.
Chill until syrupy.
Break cake into small pieces. Line a large mixing bowl with waxed paper.
Alternate layers of cake pieces and gelatin mixture.
Mash down with large spoon as this is added.
Chill overnight.
Turn upside down on serving plate and remove waxed paper.
Ice with other 2 packages of topping.
Sprinkle coconut over top and sides.

title: josie's leg of lamb with plum sauce
directions: Place lamb fat side up on rack in shallow roasting pan. Season with salt and pepper.
Roast at 325° until meat thermometer reaches 175° to 180°, about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: fish stew
directions: Pour oil in pan and saute onion. Add tomato soup, chopped tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce. Simmer for a few minutes. Add fish pieces and crushed pepper. Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Quickly brown pork chop on both sides and remove from heat. Peel and slice potatoes in casserole dish.
Peel and slice onions. Arrange pork chops on top of onions.
Pour mushroom soup over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Work flour until mealy.
Beat egg yolks, sugar and vanilla until thick and fluffy.
Add baking powder, salt and raisins.
(Cook raisins in water until soft. Drain before adding to mixture.)
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in baking pan lined with wax paper.
Always grease the pan before putting wax paper.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Mix well.
Line 3-quart Pyrex with crushed potato chips.
Add chicken mixture.
Top with 1 cup grated cheese.
Top with more crushed chips.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.

title: tortilla dip
directions: Scramble sausage and ground chuck; drain well.
Melt cheese. Add to sausage, ground chuck and taco sauce.
Serve warm or cold with tortilla chips.

title: reese's bars
directions: Mix together the powdered sugar, graham cracker crumbs, peanut butter and oleo.
Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips and peanut butter; spread on top.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: bible cake
directions: Note:
If you have never used your Bible as a cookbook, now is the time to start!
It's fun to find the ingredients from your King James version.

title: baked lemon pudding
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and egg yolks.
Add lemon juice, flour and milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Bake in 6-inch square Pyrex dish which is placed in shallow pan filled with about 1/2-inch water.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients together until creamy. Great with fruit.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together in large bowl.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pans and flour.
Bake approximately 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: cheesecake dip
directions: Beat cheese, sugar and milk until well blended.
Fold in topping and vanilla.
Store in fridge.
Use to dip cookies, cake cubes, fresh fruit, pretzels, etc.
Makes 2 cups.
Approximately 6 calories per teaspoon.

title: salmon salad
directions: Dice salmon, removing skins and bones.
Add chopped celery and pickles.
Mix with other ingredients.
Add salad dressing.
Serve on crisp lettuce leaves.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well with hands. Roll into 1-inch balls. Bake on lightly greased baking sheet at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve warm.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix well.
Use 1 to 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: french dressing
directions: Pour lemon juice over grated onions.
Then put them in a strainer.
Cream sugar, paprika and celery salt with oil.
Add catsup and vinegar and beat.
Now add other juices and blend. Chill and bottle.
Makes 1 quart.

title: easy blueberry-cheese bars
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Press dough evenly in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Beat the cream cheese, egg, sugar and lemon rind in a medium size bowl with electric mixer until smooth. Spread mixture over cookie dough. Drop blueberry pie filling on cheese. Swirl with knife.
Bake in a 350° oven
for 35 minutes. Cool on wire rack.
Cut into bars. Refrigerate.

title: potato soup
directions: Melt butter in a large pan.
Add onion, potato and carrot. Cover and cook over low heat for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add broth, salt and pepper; simmer until vegetables are tender.
Remove from heat.
Puree half the mixture in a blender or mash, then return pureed soup to pan.
Stir in cream.
If desired, garnish each bowl with dill.

title: country-fried venison and gravy
directions: Thinly slice venison steaks.
Tenderize with mallet or saucer edge.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Shake in bag containing flour to dredge well.
Fry in skillet in shortening until brown.
Remove to paper towel or rack to drain.
Pour off all shortening, except 2 tablespoons.
Add several tablespoons flour to drippings and brown.
Add water to desired consistency.
Bring to boil and simmer at least 15 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Cut lard into dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk and mix with hands or wooden spoon.
Pour out onto floured surface and roll or pat dough to approximately 1/2-inch thick.
Use biscuit cutter to shape biscuits and place on greased baking pan.
Bake at 400° until just starting to brown.
Remove from oven and brush top of biscuits with melted butter.
Return to oven and bake until golden brown.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Dredge chicken pieces in flour; brown in butter and oil.
Add 1 tablespoon of flour and rest of ingredients, except biscuit recipe.
Cover and cook on low 30 minutes.
Add more stock as needed.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix together and cook until mixture is a dark brown.
Remove from heat; add 1 stick of butter.
Let dissolve completely.
Add soda.
Drop on well oiled cookie sheet.

title: roasted whole fish a la cornell
directions: If using whole potatoes, wash and peel.
In a food processor fitted with a medium shredding disc, coarsely shred the potato. Or, shred potato with a grater.
To prevent darkening, place shredded potato in a bowl of cold water immediately after shredding.
Rinse potato shreds well and drain.
Squeeze potato shreds to remove any excess water.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all.
Shape and put into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pour tomato juice around meat loaf.
Bake 45 minutes longer.
Just before it is done, smear top with ketchup, brown sugar and a little mustard.

title: curry mayonnaise (veggie dip)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Not good with chips or pretzels.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces. Dip into mixture of 1/2 mustard and 1/2 lite mayo, then into mix of sesame seed and bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: bread-n-butter pickles
directions: Choose 2 dozen firm young cucumbers, 4 to 5-inches long and 1 1/2-inches thick. Wash well and slice into 1/4-inch round slices, unpeeled. Place slices in an airtight container. Sprinkle with 1 cup of kosher salt and cover. Allow to stand in a cool place for 12 hours. During the soaking time, stir and turn over cucumbers 2 or 3 times so that they are evenly covered in brine. Replace lid after each stirring.

title: microwave cracker jacks
directions: Place popcorn and peanuts in heavy grocery bag.
In glass bowl (2-quart) combine sugar, corn syrup, butter and salt.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes on High, stirring after each minute, until mixture comes to a boil, then microwave 2 minutes more.
Quickly stir in soda and pour over corn in bowl.
Close bag and shake well.
Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes.
Shake bag every 30 seconds.
Pour corn onto flat pan and allow to cool 5 minutes.
Break apart with hands and store in Tupperware.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli. Arrange stalks in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken over stalks.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over top. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice and boil carrots in salt water until fork-tender; drain and cool.
Make marinade using remaining liquid from carrots and next 8 ingredients.
Mix well using blender or beater.
Pour mixture over carrots and refrigerate.
Can be prepared several days in advance.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar with flour.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake for about 1 hour at 325° or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: peach tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in airtight container.
Add 3 to 4 teaspoons to a cup of boiling water.

title: orange smoothies
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend together.
Double recipe for a full pitcher full.

title: cider apple drink
directions: Quarter and core the apples.
Puree a few quarters in the blender, along with the cider for about 10 seconds.
Serve iced. Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix together in one bowl; beat until smooth and bake at 350° in greased baking dish.

title: country potato soup
directions: In a large pot, cook potatoes, celery and carrots in water until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain; reserve liquid and set vegetables aside.
In the same pot, saute onions in butter until soft.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk.
Stir constantly until thick.
Stir in cooked vegetables.
Add 1 cup or more of reserved cooking liquid until soup is right thickness desired.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in a large pot with skin on.
Let cool, peel, and cube potatoes.
Mix potatoes with onions, cheese, and mayonnaise.
Pour into a 9 1/2 x 13 inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle cooked bacon on top and bake 1 hour in a 325° oven.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir all together.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Drop by tablespoonful.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: corny corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 400° for 30 minutes (until golden brown).
Serve hot.

title: oatmeal icebox cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Make into rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper and place in refrigerator. Slice amount needed and place on cookie sheet. Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: I put the
crackers and seasoning in the cream.
Let it soften, then add
meat
and mix well.
This is real soft.
You might refrigerate, then form small balls.
Fry.
As I mixed it together I sprinkled the flour over and mixed it in.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Stir together and add soda, flour, salt and baking powder.
Add nuts and mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: crab quiche
directions: Mix eggs, sour cream, Parmesan cheese, flour, onion powder, salt and pepper sauce in a bowl.
Beat with mixer until smooth. Stir in crab meat, mushrooms and Swiss cheese.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch pie plate.
Bake in 350° oven until knife inserted in center comes out clean (about 45 minutes).
Cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Mix the ingredients together and chill.

title: apple crisp
directions: In a well greased dish, place apples.
Sift together sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Add butter using a pastry blender until crumbly.
Pack closely over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is brown.

title: crock-pot chicken cacciatore
directions: Place sliced onions in bottom of crock-pot.
Add chicken pieces, minced garlic, tomato paste, tomatoes, salt, pepper, herbs and white wine (optional). Cover and cook on low 7 to 9 hours. (High 3 to 4 hours.)
Serve chicken pieces with sauce over hot buttered spaghetti or vermicelli.

title: pink punch
directions: Use 2 cans
of	lemonade
to
make a frozen ring with a ring mold.
When
semi-frozen, can
add fresh mint to garnish. Mix 2 cans lemonade
as directed and add 7-Up in a punch bowl. Add frozen lemonade ring.
Serve cold.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except bacon.
Shape into loaf; place in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Arrange bacon strips on top of meat.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix.
Pour into casserole and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fajita nachos
directions: In medium skillet, combine chicken, spices and seasonings for fajitas and water; blend well.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 3 minutes.
In large, shallow ovenproof platter, arrange chips.
Top with chicken and cheese.
Place under broiler and melt cheese.
Top with tomato, olives, green onions and desired amount of salsa.
Can add sour cream, if desired.

title: one dish spaghetti
directions: In a 2 1/2-quart microwave-safe dish, combine beef, onion and garlic.
Cover and microwave on High for 2 1/2 minutes; stir to crumble meat.
Cook 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes longer or until meat is no longer pink; drain.
Add the tomato sauce, salt and oregano; mix well.
Cover and microwave on High for 4 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Blend margarine and sugar well.
Add eggs and then dry ingredients.
Add bananas.
Blend well.
Then stir in nuts.
Pour into two greased and floured 8-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown rice in vegetable oil in medium heat.
Blend onion, garlic, tomato, 1/2 cup water and chicken bouillon cubes in blender until pureed.
Pour mixture into browned rice and cover with lid to simmer for about 5 minutes, then add 2 cups of cold water and let boil until cooked with lid on.
Allow to cool after cooked with lid off.
Rice should be puffy.
(Do not stir frequently; can turn too mushy.)

title: russian cole slaw
directions: Thinly shred cabbage, bell pepper and onion, mix all together.

title: spiced asparagus
directions: Marinate liquids and spices overnight.
Pour over asparagus.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix ingredients together with electric mixer.
Pour in well-greased and floured 11 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
You can also use Pam spray and you can also use three 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: grandma stalker's pizza dough
directions: Follow instructions on the packet of yeast. Stir. In a large bowl add enough flour to make a dough. Knead well.
Bake at 450°f. 230°c. gas mark 8 as needed.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased 13 x 5-inch casserole dish.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until brown.

title: corn casserole 1
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and garlic until brown.
Add mushrooms and tomato sauce and simmer.
Cook egg noodles and put in deep casserole dish.
Mix sour cream, cream cheese and grated onion. Add this to the top of noodles.
Then top with beef mixture. Grate Cheddar cheese and add to top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour, salt and baking powder which have been sifted together. Mix in sweet potatoes and add enough milk to make a dough stiff enough to handle and roll. Roll out on floured surface and cut with biscuit cutter. Bake at 400° about 25 minutes. Do not let them Burn!

title: vanilla wafer pie crust
directions: Combine vanilla wafer crumbs and sugar; stir in butter. Press onto bottom and 1-inch up side of 9-inch spring-form pan. Refrigerate about 30 minutes.

title: glorified potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes and onions.
Mix next four ingredients until blended.
Pour over potatoes.
Crush corn flakes and mix with melted butter.
Sprinkle over top of potatoes.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Cut cherries in halves; drain off cherry juice.
Drain off pineapple juice to make 2 cups liquid.
(Add rest with water
to make 2 cups.)
Bring to a boil.
Pour over the jello.
Let cool, then add Coke, cherries, crushed pineapple and pecans.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: transparent pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add small amount of milk, then flour. Add beaten egg yolks with rest of milk. Add vanilla. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until center of pie doesn't "shake" when pie is moved.

title: pineapple zucchini cake(1 gram fat if nuts omitted)
directions: Place zucchini in a sieve; let drain 30 minutes.
Drain about half of syrup off of pineapple.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat inside of 10-inch tube pan with vegetable cooking spray.
Stir together flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and allspice in large bowl.
Mix together egg substitute, applesauce, pineapple juice concentrate and vanilla in small bowl.
Add to dry ingredients.
Press zucchini to remove excess liquid.
Add drained zucchini and pineapple, walnuts and raisins to bowl. Mix with wooden spoon until well blended, turn into prepared pan.
Bake in preheated oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until wooden pick inserted comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan on wire rack 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool completely.
Frost cake with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Drain Veg-All and pour into pie crust, then chop chicken up and place on top of Veg-All.
Spread cream of chicken soup on top of chicken.
Place second pie crust on top and slightly pinch both crusts together.
Cook until crust is brown.

title: ham 'n tater loaf
directions: Line 9-inch loaf pan with waxed paper.
Mix ham with 1/2 cup real mayonnaise.
Press into bottom of pan.
Mix next 6 ingredients with remaining real mayonnaise.
Add potatoes; toss.
Press lightly over ham layer.
Cover; chill 4 hours.
Unmold.
Serves 6.

title: beef and bean barbecue
directions: Brown beef and vegetables in hot oil until tender.
Add remaining ingredients except sugar and beans.
Blend well and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour sauce over beans and brown sugar in casserole.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cheese pie
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: annie's broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, soup, mayonnaise, eggs and onion in shallow casserole.
Put cheese and cornbread on top.
Dot heavily with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix together the coconut and nuts and put into bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare cake mix according to directions on box and pour over coconut-pecan mixture.
Place margarine and cream cheese in a saucepan and heat until mixture is warm enough to stir in the confectioners sugar.
Spoon over top of cake mix. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Do not cut until cold.
Makes 1 sheet cake.

title: hungarian beef stew(this is my favorite crock-pot meal!)
directions: Place all ingredients, except beef broth, paprika, salt and tomatoes, in crock-pot.
Mix beef broth, paprika, salt and tomatoes; pour over top and stir to blend.
Cover and cook on low setting for 10 to 12 hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings (about 2 1/2 quarts).

title: shrimp baked with feta, ouzo and cognac
directions: Pour tomatoes into mixing bowl.
Squeeze into small pieces. Heat 4 tablespoons oil in heavy saucepan.
Lightly saute onion and garlic.
Add tomatoes, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cook, uncovered, over medium heat until sauce is thickened.

title: corn and green chile casserole
directions: Cook corn according to package directions; drain and set aside.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add cream cheese; stir until blended.
Stir in corn, onions, sugar and green chiles.
Spoon into a lightly greased 1-quart baking dish.
Cover; bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Pour pineapple in large bowl.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well by hand.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: katie's chicken salad
directions: *These seasonings usually are made without salt and without preservatives or m.s.g. added.

title: rush hour supper
directions: Line large, shallow baking pan with 2 layers of heavy-duty foil.
Pour salt into pan, about 1 to 1 1/2 inches deep.
Moisten with water and press down evenly in bottom.
Make small indentation in middle.
Lay roast directly on salt on indentation. Cover with salt.
Sprinkle with water and press firmly around roast, covering completely, about 1 to 1 1/2-inch thick layer.

title: summer vegetable salad
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, sugar and dressing.
Shake in a jar.
Pour over vegetables; let marinate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: potato rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water and set aside. Combine potatoes, sugar, salt and 1 cup lukewarm water in bowl. Add yeast mixture, eggs and shortening-butter mixture.
Stir in flour gradually.
Mix well.
Place in a greased bowl and let rise until double its size.
Punch down and form rolls.
Let the rolls rise until double in size.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 6 dozen.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients, stirring until crumbly.
Drain.
Add next 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes. Pour 1 cup sauce over bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Layer 1/2 of noodles.

title: hanky panky(appetizer)
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage separately.
Drain off fat then mix together.
Cut Velveeta cheese in slices and place on meat mixture.
Mix over low heat until cheese is well melted.
Spread 1 Tbsp. of mix on party rye slice.
Place on broiler rack and broil until bubbly and light brown.
(Can be frozen and broiled at a later date.)

title: crunchy peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Microwaves vary; this is for about 700 power microwave.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt.
Cook 8 minutes on High in microwave oven, stirring well after 4 minutes.
Afterwards, stir in butter and vanilla (if desired, you may add coconut to the ingredients).
Microwave 3 minutes longer on High.
Add baking soda and quickly stir until light and foamy.

title: pavlova
directions: Beat egg whites with pinch of salt for 6 minutes or so until very stiff.
Gradually add sugar, vinegar and vanilla while continuing to beat.
Sift cornflour and fold in lightly.
Wet plate with cold water, then heap mixture onto damp surface. Preheat oven at 400°.
Set at 200° to 250° and bake undisturbed for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Do not allow to go brown, if it does your oven is too hot.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Spread green chili peppers in greased square pan.
Cover with cheese.
Pour eggs over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut in small squares and serve as appetizer.

title: staige's favorite luncheon salad
directions: Put chicken in a large saucepan with 3 cups water, 1 teaspoon salt and a few peppercorns. Bring to boiling; lower heat. Cover. Simmer 45 minutes or until chicken is tender. Drain; bone. Cut meat into bite-size pieces. You should have 2 cups. (Use boneless, skinless chicken breast instead of broiler-fryer recipe calls for.) Combine chicken, water chestnuts, grapes, celery and 1/4 cup of almonds in a large bowl. Mix mayonnaise, curry, soy sauce and lemon juice in a cup. Pour over chicken mixture. Toss lightly to mix. Chill several hours.

title: berry's chocolate applesauce cake
directions: Sift first 6 ingredients together and set aside.
Place applesauce in saucepan and bring to a boil; add chocolate and butter, stirring until melted.
Add applesauce mixture to dry mixture.
Add raisins, baking powder and salt.
Mix well and then add vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pan. Choose either tube pan or layer pans.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 1 hour; bake in layers pans at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well then add next 5 ingredients. After mixing them well, then add grated zucchini (not pared).
Add nuts and raisins, if you like.
Grease and flour lightly 2 loaf pans, turn into pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until done.

title: best crab dip ever
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small casserole bowl, mix cream cheese and crabmeat together.
Add garlic powder and onion flakes. Top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 22 minutes in a covered bowl.
Serve hot with crackers.
Yum!!!

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Pour all ingredients in bowl and mix until smooth.
Pour in an ungreased pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
When baked, cool in pan.

title: applesauce-raisin bread
directions: In a bowl, combine egg, applesauce, melted butter, granulated sugar and brown sugar, blending well.
Stir in flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir well until smooth.
Stir in raisins and chopped nuts.
Turn batter into a well-greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pan or fluted mold with tube, that holds about 1 quart.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven for 45 minutes. Cool and frost with light powdered sugar, if desired.
Makes 1 large loaf.
(Bread slices better the second day.)

title: strawberry soup
directions: In food processor, blend all ingredients.
Serve immediately or chill in refrigerator.
Garnish with mint leaves.
Makes 4 servings.

title: carnell's 8 egg pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time (beating after each one).
Alternate with flour.
Add salt and flavoring. Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: meatball, pasta and spinach soup
directions: Saute onions, zucchini and garlic in oil until tender.
Add water, spaghetti and meat balls, bouillon cubes, spinach and spices.
Simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves six.

title: slush punch
directions: Prepare jello as package directs.
Add pineapple juice, water and sugar.
Pour into container and place in freezer overnight. When ready to use, put slush into punch bowl.
Add 7-Up or ginger ale.
Stir slightly before serving.
Yields 150 ounces.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend
flour,
salt and shortening with pastry blender. Mix water, vinegar and egg; add to flour mixture and mix well. Shape into 4
balls.
Can be rolled out now for use or wrapped and frozen for use later.
Makes 4 (9-inch) pies.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix together flour, baking soda, sugar, eggs, crushed pineapple, vanilla and chopped walnuts.
Bake 35 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While cake is still warm, combine the following ingredients and ice cake:

title: pete's pot o' chili
directions: Brown meat and add bell peppers and onions.
Drain grease. Add spices; mix well.
Now add all other ingredients, mixing well as you go along.
The secret is to cook it slow and stir occasionally.
Makes about 2 gallons.
Let the whole family join in and help!
It tastes better and it's fun!

title: minestrone soup
directions: Saute onion, garlic and celery.
Add everything, except ditalini, peas, beans
and	Parmesan cheese.
Simmer, covered, for 40 minutes or
longer.
Add
ditalini,
peas
and	beans. Bring back to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for 20 minutes or longer. Serve with cheese sprinkled over each serving.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine meat, egg, onion, milk, corn flakes, salt and pepper. Form into patties.
Roll in flour; brown in cooking oil.
Place in baking dish and cover with soup.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 4.

title: individual cheesecake cups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 2 1/2 inch paper liners in 24 muffin cups.

title: sweet potato souffle(old timey)
directions: Heat potatoes.
Drain liquid.
Mash.
Add all ingredients except marshmallows.
Bake at 375° until bubbles or thickens. Place marshmallows on top and heat until they are lightly browned and melted.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: You will need 24 cupcake liners.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken until done and shred.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef in pan.
Drain off fat. Add onions, bouillon and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir in water.
Bring to a boil and add cornstarch mixture to thicken.
Cover and let meat simmer for 20 minutes. Peel and cook potatoes.
Remove from heat. Drain water and add salt, pepper, butter and milk.
Mash potatoes.
In large casserole dish, layer meat mixture on bottom, place corn over meat layer and top everything with mashed potatoes.
Cover pie and place in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Works great made ahead of time for coming in late from a hockey game!

title: jungle juice
directions: Blend ingredients in blender.
(You can add ice for more of a shake effect.)
Put in refrigerator to cool.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Refrigerate overnight. Pour over mixed, cut up raw broccoli, cauliflower and red onion.
(You can also reverse the amount of sour cream and mayonnaise.)

title: potato candy
directions: Peel and cube the potato. Boil until done.
Mash with confectioners sugar until stiff enough to roll out.
Roll 1/8-inch thick.
Spread peanut butter as thick as desired.
Roll into log and slice into bite size pieces.

title: copper pennies
directions: Put carrots in a large bowl that has a lid that fits tightly on it.
In a separate bowl, mix the soup, celery, green pepper, onions, vinegar, black pepper, salt and sugar.
Stir and mix well.
Pour over carrots.
Put in refrigerator; let set at least overnight.

title: salmon vegetable pie
directions: Drain salmon; remove bones and skin.
Flake into a bowl and mix with onion, zucchini, peas, cheese and dill weed.
Beat eggs with yogurt and mayonnaise; stir into salmon mixture. Salt lightly to taste and turn into the pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until filling has set and is lightly browned.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Bake cake on 15 x 11-inch or 15 x 12-inch cook sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat together cream cheese, pudding and milk. Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Spread this on top of cooled cake.
Spread pineapple on top of the pudding.
Spread large Cool Whip on top of pineapple.
Sprinkle with coconut and chopped nuts.
Chill in refrigerator; keep cooled.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Serve with Gingersnaps.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Mix marshmallows and whipped cream. Let stand 1 hour (not always necessary).
Mix remaining ingredients and add to cream and marshmallow mixture.
May use 1/2 cup mayonnaise for tart.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar.
Add Eagle Brand milk and mix; add sweet milk and flavoring.
Pour into freezer.

title: company salisbury steak
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Form into football shape balls. Roll lightly in flour and brown in skillet.
(The balls may be frozen at this point.)
Put in roaster and cover with remaining ingredients that have been mixed together.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.
Baking time may vary according to size of meat balls.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Mix together and add enough milk to make moist and stick together. Roll into balls (about 1-inch) and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° until brown.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine, butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks one at a time.
Add buttermilk alternately with dry ingredients ending with flour.
Add cherries, pecans, vanilla and coconut.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar and fold in.
Bake at 350° in three 9-inch greased layer pans for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients then pour mixture into oil.
Pour over crackers and toss and stir until they are well coated. Spread out and let dry approximately 1 hour.
Do Not Bake.
Store in air tight container.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mash sweet potatoes. Scald the milk and dissolve the sugar and salt in it. Add the butter, stirring until melted. Add this mixture to the potatoes and mix and beat until light and fluffy. Separate the eggs, beat yolks and add to the potatoes. Add the nutmeg, raisins and nuts. Beat egg whites until stiff, cut and fold slightly into the potatoes and pour into a buttered baking dish.

title: country goulash
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: frozen yogurt pops
directions: Stir 1/3 cup Add-A-Crunch into each carton of yogurt.
Spoon about 1 tablespoon remaining Add-A-Crunch into each of 12 (3 1/2 ounce) paper drinking cups.
Spoon yogurt mixture into cups. Place 12 wooden sticks or skewers in center of each cup.
Freeze until firm.
Let stand at room temperature about 3 minutes before serving.
Tear off paper cup to remove.
Makes 12 Yogurt Pops.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water.
Add cold water; add pie filling and extract.
Chill until firm.

title: five in one salad
directions: Mix all together; chill and serve.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: *If no sour milk, use 1 tablespoon vinegar in sweet milk.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Blend in first 7 ingredients.
