Pour boiling water over the bran cereal and add to the mixture.
Bake in well-greased muffin tins
20 minutes in 400°
oven.

title: barrett's sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Sift dry ingredients 3 times; add alternately with sour cream to first mixture.
Add butter flavoring.
Beat until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook celery and onions in butter.
Add flour and milk in cheese soup.
Add to first mixture; mix well.
Stir in tuna, pimiento, olives and mushrooms.
Cook until thick; pour over cooked and drained noodles.
Place in pan.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: lemon pepper bread
directions: Cream ingredients together.
Spread on top of and between slices of French bread.
Wrap bread in foil.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions; drain.
Heat mushroom soup.
Add pimento, green pepper, onion and mayonnaise.
Mix.
In casserole, layer macaroni, sauce and cheese until all is used up. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes until bubbly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: summer spaghetti sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, combine plum jam, vinegar, brown sugar, onion, red chili pepper, garlic and ginger.
Bring mixture to boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool slightly. Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: boiled custard
directions: Beat eggs well. Mix other ingredients and cook in double boiler until it coats a spoon. Strain and cool.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend flour, Crisco, baking powder and salt.
Place egg and vinegar in a measuring cup and add water to 1/2 cup.
Pour into flour
mixture
and
knead.
Bake
at
350° until lightly brown. This makes 2 large or 3 small crusts.

title: baked stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and chop finely.
Mix stems with remaining ingredients and stuff caps with mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika to garnish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: hamburger-noodle casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with some onion.
Combine all ingredients, except shredded cheese, in a casserole.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: apple dessert cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add apples and half and half. Stir dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° and 45 minutes at 300°.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Wash and peel 1 quart mushrooms and cut into dices.
Stir into them the 1 1/2 quarts of chicken broth, then add the flour to thicken soup.
Cream the soup with the butter, then add salt and pepper.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Garnish with croutons.

title: tomatoes lutece
directions: Immerse tomatoes in boiling water for 1 minute.
Remove and peel with a knife.
Combine remaining ingredients to make dressing.
Slice peeled tomatoes into 1/4-inch thick slices. Restack tomatoes with dressing poured between slices and over top. Where stem is removed, place a sprig of parsley, marinating to enhance flavor.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients well and freeze in 1/2 gallon ice cream freezer.
Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: molasses popcorn balls
directions: Cook until mixture forms a hard ball when dropped into cold water.
Add baking soda and beat.
Pour over popped corn.
Form into small balls with lightly greased (butter) hands.

title: red sea clam chowder
directions: Saute bacon for 5 minutes.
Add onion, celery and garlic. Cook until bacon is brown.
Pour off most of the excess fat.
Add tomatoes, V-8, salt and pepper. Bring to boil.
Stir in shell macaroni.
Cover and cook 12 minutes, stirring once.
Add clams and parsley.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add other ingredients. Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper to cool.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Cook rump roast at 325°.
Let cool.
Remove fat and cut rump roast into chunks. Add onion and barbecue sauce.
Mix well.
Place in covered pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Take the margarine, brown sugar and flour and make into crumbs.
Take 1 1/2 cups and set aside for top of the batter.

title: deluxe baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Mix all ingredients.
Add ground beef; stir.
Put in a large 3-quart casserole dish; cover. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry orange bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add orange rind; mix. Combine orange juice, egg and salad oil.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until flour is moistened.
Fold in cranberries. Spread in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or less.
Yield: 1 loaf.

title: nuke-able nachos
directions: Place chips on a dinner plate.
Sprinkle with cheese and tomatoes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or two round pans.
Beat all ingredients in large mixer bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly for 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed, scraping for 3 minutes.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 60 to 65 minutes, or until wooden pick comes out clean.

title: reese cup cake
directions: In saucepan combine 1 cup butter, 1/4 cup cocoa, water and sugar.
Heat, don't boil.
Let cool.
Add flour, baking powder, 1 teaspoon vanilla and eggs; beat for 3 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Spread thin layer of peanut butter on top of cake.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli buds, discarding thick stems.
Peel and chop onion.
Mix raisins, broccoli, onion, cheese and bacon in large mixing bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar; add to broccoli mixture.
Marinate at least 8 hours.

title: sorbet
directions: Mix well in a bowl.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in freezer.
Stir every 1/2 hour, for about 2 hours, until it sets up good!

title: crispy zucchini spears
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Cut off ends of zucchini and slice each in quarters, lengthwise to make 12 spears.
Combine dry ingredients in small bowl.
Combine egg and milk in shallow bowl.
Roll each spear in cornmeal mixture.
Dip into egg mixture and again into cornmeal to coat thoroughly.
Arrange in baking dish.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: potato bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg and milk.
Blend coating mix and cheese.
Roll potatoes in egg mixture, then in coating mixture. Place potatoes in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes.

title: potato wedges
directions: Cut each potato in 8 wedges.
Rinse in cold water and drain thoroughly.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except potatoes, until well blended. Add potatoes.
Toss to coat well. Place potatoes on Pam coated broiler pan.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes or until potatoes are golden brown and tender, turning occasionally.

title: nutty caramel corn
directions: Remove all unpopped kernels from popped corn. Combine popcorn and nuts in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a 1 1/2 quart saucepan combine sugar, butter or margarine, corn syrup and salt. Stir in cinnamon if desired.
Cook and stir over medium heat till butter melts and mixture comes to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook without stirring for 5 more minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn and nuts and gently stir to coat.
Bake in 300° oven about 20 minutes stirring after the first 10 minutes.
Spread mixture on a large piece of foil to cool.

title: fool-proof cheesecake
directions: Cream both cheese in a bowl.
Add sugar gradually; beat well. Add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Stir in lemon juice, vanilla, corn starch and flour.
Add melted butter and mix until smooth.
Blend in sour cream.
Pour in greased and floured 9 inch Spring Form pan.
Do not preheat oven.
Bake for one hour at 325°. Turn off oven and let stay in oven for 3 more hours.
When cool, garnish with cherries, strawberries or blueberries.

title: apple-molasses muffins
directions: About 1 hour before serving or day ahead:
Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 18 (3-inch) muffin pan cups.
Into large bowl, measure all ingredients except apples and walnuts; with mixer at low speed, beat until blended, constantly scraping bowl.
Stir in apples and walnuts.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Defrost peas.
Cook bacon and crumble.
Tear lettuce into bite-size pieces; layer in large container.
Chop celery and layer on top of lettuce.
Chop green pepper and layer.
Slice onion and layer.
Defrosted green peas go on next, then spread mayonnaise like icing.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 teaspoons seasoned salt and 1/2 teaspoon sugar.
Grate cheese and layer.
Sprinkle bacon.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain corn, peas, green beans and pimento.
Bring vinegar, salt, sugar, pepper, salad oil and water to a boil, then cool. Mix with vegetables.
This will keep several weeks in refrigerator.
Serves 16.

title: tuna dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.

title: yolk sponge cake
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together 4 times.
Add salt and flavoring to yolks and beat until thick with rotary beater.
Add sugar and hot water alternately in four portions, beating until very thick after each portion.
Fold in about 1/4 of the flour at a time; beat well.
Pour into ungreased tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook rice following label directions. Drain and cool to room temperature.
Dice tomatoes, celery, cucumber and green onions. Add to cooked rice.
Pour Italian dressing over rice mixture and refrigerate overnight.
Very good with grilled hamburgers.

title: foolproof pastry
directions: Put shortening into bowl; pour on boiling water and milk. Whip until thick like whipped cream.
Sift flour and salt together; add to first mixture.
Roll out and bake.
Makes pastry for 2 (9-inch) pies or for a 9-inch two crust pie.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: May add up to 1/2 cup sugar or omit, depending on preference.

title: chocolate biscuits
directions: Place sugar, salt, flour and cocoa in saucepan, slowly adding milk.
Cook until thick.
Add vanilla and pour over baked biscuits.

title: annie heatherington's orange fluff pie
directions: Combine all and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened, then cook on low for 5 minutes.
Beat 2 egg whites with 1/4 cup sugar into a meringue.
Gently fold meringue into cooked custard and pour all into prepared baked shell.
Top with flaked coconut or baked pastry crumbs or whipped cream.

title: chicken cordon blue
directions: Place chicken on board and cover.
Pound out.
Season each piece, add ham and cheese.
Roll.
Place in Pyrex pan.
Sprinkle paprika.
Cover with undiluted soup on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: special sunday soup(carol's)
directions: Prepare meat balls by combining beef, egg, 3 tablespoons water, bread crumbs, salt and parsley.
Lightly shape about 24 meat balls.
In a 5-quart Dutch oven melt butter and saute meat balls, one layer at a time.
Should be brown on all sides.
Drain off fat and set meat balls aside on paper towel.
Using same Dutch oven, combine 2 cups water, beef broth, tomatoes, onion soup, carrots, celery and remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally, breaking up tomatoes.
Add meat balls and simmer for 20 minutes more.
Makes about 2 quarts, 6 to 7 servings.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and butter; use part for bottom of pan and part on top of cake.
Dissolve jello in hot water; let partly set (not too stiff).
Add to cream cheese the sugar.
Have Milnot real cold, then whip a while longer.
Then add sugar and cheese mixture and beat until smooth.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Let potatoes thaw, then mix with all ingredients except cheese.
Cook 1 hour covered at 350°.
Add grated cheese and let cook 30 minutes longer (uncovered).

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken, bone and cut meat into pieces, use plenty of broth.
Make
stiff
dough
for
rolling.
Separate
into 4 balls. Roll out on
floured
board;
cut
in squares and drop into chicken broth, to
which 4 or 5 potatoes have been added. Make sure broth is boiling.
Soon
as
pot pie is in, cut back heat; cook slow until potatoes are cooked.

title: corn bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add egg yolks, beaten lightly, with a teaspoon cold water.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Fry bacon until crisp in large skillet.
Remove bacon and crumble for topping.
Add onion, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper to bacon grease, stirring, until well blended.
Stir in cabbage; cook over medium heat, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Sprinkle top with bacon after removed from grease.

title: sugar-free pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Pour into already prepared pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 45 minutes or more.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter and toast bread.
Cut into cubes and place in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle raisins over toast if desired.
Thoroughly beat eggs, 1/2 cup sugar, salt, evaporated milk, boiling water and vanilla.
Pour mixture over toast and let stand 10 minutes.
Combine remaining 4 teaspoons of sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over toast.
Place dish in shallow baking pan of water to a depth of 1 inch.
Bake 60 to 65 minutes until done.
Remove dish from pan of water and serve warm or chilled.
Serves 8.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over fresh vegetables.
Chill 24 hours.
Stir often to coat well.
Drain before serving (liquid you drain may be frozen and used again).
When using hard vegetables, i.e., carrots, cauliflower or broccoli, parboil slightly.

title: frozen angel food
directions: Beat egg whites until they peak.
Whip cream until stiff. Combine all ingredients.
Put into dish and freeze.
Let freeze about 4 hours.
Do not stir.

title: cheddar cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except walnuts.
Roll into a ball. Roll in chopped walnuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Brown meat in pan with butter.
Slice potatoes thin and spread half in baking dish.
Cover with half of meat, soup, onion, pepper and carrots.
Repeat same with remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Cover for 1 hour.
Uncover for last 1/2 hour.

title: peach delight
directions: Mix together; bake 15 to 20 minutes until brown.
Let cool completely.

title: oatmeal patties
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and drop by level tablespoonfuls into frying pan over medium heat.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix granulated sugar and cinnamon; add just enough cinnamon to darken sugar.
Cut biscuits into quarters and roll in sugar mixture to coat.
Drop into ungreased bundt cake pan or bread pan. Melt together butter and the brown sugar. (Mixture will be a little grainy when melted because sugar will not be completely dissolved.)
Pour over biscuits.

title: fluffy citrus dressing
directions: In a saucepan combine eggs, sugar and rinds and juice on low heat until mixture thickens, about 10 minutes.
Cool.
Whip the cream and mix together.

title: chow chow
directions: Mix all chopped vegetables. Mix with salt and sugar; let sit overnight. Add the final four ingredients. Bring to a boil and cook for 5 minutes. Place in sterilized jars and seal. Place in boiling water for 5 minutes.

title: corn puppies(recipe for kids)
directions: Mix dry ingredients with oil and water.
Coat the slices of hot dogs with mix. Either bake like a pancake or deep fry the coated hot dog slices.
These are bite size corn dogs. Serve with mustard or ketchup.
Serves 2.

title: lemon-raspberry fool
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease four muffin cups.
Place one sheet of phyllo on work surface; brush with half of butter.
Top with second sheet of phyllo; brush with remaining butter.
Cut phyllo into 8 x 5 1/2-inch pieces.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash and soak cucumbers in cold water 1 to 2 hours.
Drain. Place 2 head of fresh dill or 1 1/2 tsp. dill seed in each jar. Place 1 clove garlic in each jar.
Bring to boil the water, vinegar and salt.
Pack cucumbers in jars, then pour boiling mixture over cucumbers and seal.
Wait 3 weeks before using.

title: italian sausage balls
directions: Mix enough Bisquick with sausage and cheese to form a medium consistency dough.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Space 1-inch apart on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Turn balls over and bake for an additional 4 to 5 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Cut dough into narrow strips.
Wrap dough around smokies. Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes or until brown.

title: carrot-spice muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin cups or line with muffin papers; set aside.

title: potato corn chowder
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, heat to boiling the onion, water, bay leaf and potatoes.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in soup, milk and corn. Cook, uncovered, 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Discard bay leaf.
Serve in bowls and sprinkle with bacon bits and garnish with parsley, if desired.
Yields 4 servings.

title: scallop puffs
directions: Melt the butter in the large frypan.
Add the scallops, lemon zest and garlic.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, about 5 minutes.
Add the dill and let cool to room temperature. Add cheese, mayonnaise and pepper to the scallop mixture and stir to combine well.
Refrigerate in a covered bowl until ready to use, no longer than a week.
Preheat broiler and arrange cocktail bread on cookie sheet.
Broil 1 minute and turn them over and top with a heaping teaspoon of the scallop mixture.
Broil until puffed and golden - approximately 2 minutes.
Keep an eye on them when broiling.
Usually a big hit!

title: party cherry pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Add cherries and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip to which sugar has been added.
Add coloring and blend.
Pour
into
crust
and
chill	overnight. Makes two pies.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain.
Melt butter, saute onions and celery until tender.
Add flour and cook, stirring, for 2 minutes.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Blend in soup.
Add broccoli and mushrooms.
Bake in greased casserole, covered, at 350° for about 30 minutes or freeze and bake at 375° for about 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.
This can also be used as a dip.

title: potato salad
directions: Make sure potatoes and eggs are thoroughly cooled.
Potatoes can have skins on them.
Chop potatoes, eggs and all vegetables. Toss into a large mixing bowl and add dressing; mix thoroughly. Add more to taste.
Should be somewhat moist.
Refrigerate immediately.

title: standing rib roast beef
directions: Rub the roast with seasonings and let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Place in shallow open roasting pan with ribs down or on wire rack if boneless.
Place in cold oven.
Roast 1 hour at 375°.
Turn off oven until 1 hour before serving.
Turn oven back on to 375° for 30 minutes for rare, 40 minutes for pink and 50 minutes for pale pink (done).
Let roast rest for 20 minutes before carving.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fry in hot oil in 1 tablespoon cakes.

title: savory cheese soup
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onion in butter until tender.
Add flour, salt, pepper and garlic powder; stir until smooth. Gradually add milk; cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Meanwhile bring chicken broth to a boil in a small saucepan.
Add carrots and celery to broth and simmer for 5 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Add to milk mixture and stir until blended.
Add cheeses.
Cook and stir until cheeses are melted but do not boil.
Garnish with chives.
Serves 4.

title: pride of iowa cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars until fluffy; beat in the eggs. Sift the flour with baking soda, baking powder and salt; stir into creamed mixture.
Blend in vanilla.
Mix coconut, nuts and rolled oats until uniformly blended.
Roll into 1 1/4-inch balls and space 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheets.
Using fingers, flatten balls into patties about 1/8-inch thick, evening up the ragged edges.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs; beat until fluffy. Add spices, salt, cocoa and vanilla.
Blend well.
Sift soda with flour.
Add alternately with the blackberries.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Frost with caramel frosting.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef in heavy kettle.
Drain excess fat and add onion. Cook until onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese, nacho chips and sour cream.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Ladle into bowls and top with shredded cheese, nacho chips and sour cream.

title: texas pete hot wingers
directions: Cut wings
at all joints and throw away tips.
Deep fry wings for 8
to
minutes
until
crispy or bake in oven on cookie sheet
at
450° for 45 minutes.
Combine Texas Pete and melted margarine.	Place cooked wings in sauce mixture in bowl and
toss and
serve	immediately.
Serve
with
Bleu
cheese dressing and celery.
Makes 24 to 30 pieces.

title: gingerbread
directions: Pour water over shortening; add sugar, molasses and eggs. Beat well.
Sift together the flour, salt, baking powder, soda, cloves, ginger and cinnamon.
Add to other mixture and mix well. Place in 3 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: hamburger and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Set aside.
Cook hamburger with onion.
Drain fat.
Mix with noodles.
Add mushroom soup and water.
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle with lots of Romano cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy sweet pickles
directions: Cut small cucumbers lengthwise.
Soak overnight in salt water solution.
Drain cucumbers.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix well all ingredients, except chocolate chips.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Put waxed paper on cookie sheet to hold balls. Melt chocolate chips in microwave for 2 to 3 minutes.
Dip each ball in melted chocolate.
Place on cookie sheet and refrigerate until firm.
Place in bowl and refrigerate until needed.
Will keep at least 2 weeks.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Stir Cheddar cheese soup until smooth. Gradually add milk. In buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole, arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onion and sauce.
Dot top with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake, covered, at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients with fork until crumbly; set aside.

title: party mix
directions: Throw the first 7 ingredients in a brown paper grocery bag. Mix the oil and dressing.
Pour over stuff in bag.
Close bag and shake, shake, shake!

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and syrup.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cook until mixture reaches a soft ball stage (234°). Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into a greased 8-inch pan to cool.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix flour and meal with sugar and salt.
Add beaten eggs.
Add slightly melted margarine and milk.
Add vanilla and stir well. Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: layered fruit salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and beat until well blended and spreadable.
In a glass bowl, layer the remaining ingredients in order given.
Spread dressing evenly over fruit, sealing to edges of dish.
Dust with nutmeg; cover tightly with clear plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Serve on lettuce as a salad or use as a dessert.

title: baked ham
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Cut rind from ham. Place ham on back in open roasting pan, fat side up. Roast in oven 3 hours. Drain pineapple, reserve syrup. In small saucepan, combine syrup, mustard and allspice. Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes. Remove ham from oven. Keep oven hot. Stud ham with cloves. Brush with glaze. Using wooden toothpicks, secure pineapple slices and cherries to ham and brush with glaze. Return ham
to oven. Roast 30 minutes longer, (about 25 minutes per lb. total cooking time). Brush with glaze 15 minutes before done. Let ham stand 20 minutes before slicing.

title: strawberry salad ring
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice. Add enough water to juice to make 4 cups. Boil 2 cups of juice and pour into Jell-O mix. Dissolve Jell-O and add remaining juice. Melt gelatin in 1/4 to 1/2 cup warm water. Add to Jell-O. Add strawberries and pineapple. Pour half of mixture into ring mold. Refrigerate until jelled. Remove and spread sour cream on top. Chill. Add remaining Jell-O mixture and refrigerate. Serves well with chicken or turkey.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine salad dressing mix, sour cream and mayonnaise; set aside.
Place half the crumbled cornbread in bottom of a large serving bowl.
Top with half the pinto beans.
In a medium bowl, combine tomatoes, peppers and onions; layer half of mixture over beans.
Top with half of cheese, bacon, corn and reserved salad dressing.
Repeat layers, using remaining ingredients.
Garnish if desired.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Mix instant pudding with 3 cups milk and make as directed. Fold in softened Cool Whip; set aside.
Layer graham crackers in a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex pan, then a layer of pudding, then another layer of graham crackers, another layer of pudding, then a last layer of graham crackers.

title: momma's lane cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; sift flour with baking powder.
Add flour to butter and sugar alternately with milk.
After all flour and milk has been added, fold in beaten egg whites.
Grease and flour cake pans.
Bake in thin layers in 350° oven.

title: chili with potato-puff crown
directions: Pour chili in a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Mix potatoes with oregano.
Pile around edge of dish.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: baked stuffed scallop casserole
directions: Wash scallops in cold water and set in an 8 or 9-inch pan. Mix all ingredients until they are well blended.
Pour stuffing on top of scallops and dot with additional butter.
Place in preheated 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: long island punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, mix all the ingredients together.
You can fill a pitcher with this tasty drink and store the rest in your refrigerator.
A pitcher serves 8 to 10.

title: cherry divinity
directions: Bring sugar, syrup and water to the hard boil stage.
Beat egg whites; add cherry Jell-O, one spoon at a time and beat until soft peaks form.
When syrup is done, pour over egg whites and blend. Add nuts and cherries.
Drop on wax paper.

title: waffles or pancakes
directions: Mix all together.
Will keep in refrigerator.

title: italian style chicken casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Set oven for 375°.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese, together.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Lay chicken on top of mixture and cover with grated cheese. Cover with foil.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake for 15 minutes more.

title: favorite baked ham
directions: Place ham in large baking pan.
Place cloves on top.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over ham.
Bake for 2 hours or until done.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients and mix well.
Pour into well-buttered 16 x 10 1/2-inch metal pan or 15 x 9 1/2-inch Pyrex pan.

title: turkey barbecue
directions: Cut onion fine and celery.
Brown in 1/4 pound or less of margarine.
Add turkey to mix.
Mix, then add ketchup, mustard, brown sugar, tomato sauce and vinegar.
Mix well.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Can be frozen.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Combine milk, butter and brown sugar.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Boil about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Put peanut butter, powdered sugar and vanilla in; stir until creamy.
Pour into a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut when cool.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Put margarine, water and cocoa in saucepan and bring to a boil. Can use self-rising flour and forget soda and salt.
Mix rest of ingredients. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in a greased and floured cookie sheet, 15 1/2 x 10
1/2 x 1-inch.

title: lime jello salad
directions: In large bowl, make Jell-O according to instructions or with pineapple substitution.
Fold in the cottage cheese, the Cool Whip, then pineapple and the nuts.
Make sure all ingredients are blended thoroughly.
Refrigerate until firmly set (2 hours).

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook pasta by directions on box.
Drain pasta and mix with sour cream and melted butter.
Spread pasta mixture in casserole dish.
Sprinkle mushrooms over pasta mixture.
Spread sauce over mushrooms.
Sprinkle cheese over sauce.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: cream spinach dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine sour cream, mayo and seasonings. Stir in onions, water chestnuts and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate to blend flavors.

title: sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and water.
Mix well. Blend in flour and nuts.
Chill, then shape into fingers or balls. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 325°.
After they have cooled, roll in powdered sugar.

title: lemon custard pie
directions: Combine sour cream, egg yolks and vanilla pudding.
Add milk and concentrated lemonade (thawed).
Cook until thick and begins to boil.
Spoon warm filling into baked pie shell and cover with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Heat first 2 ingredients on low heat until dissolved in pot. Put hot mixture into vanilla ice cream and mix with hand beater. Add yellow food coloring if desired for color. Place in serving bowl. Put Cool Whip on top and be refreshed on a warm day.
Serves 6.

title: penuche icing
directions: Bring the sugar, milk and Crisco to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes. Beat until lukewarm with an electric mixer. Blend in vanilla. Beat until thick enough to spread.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Fold melted chocolate (room temperature) into Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Garnish with additional Cool Whip and shaved chocolate.
Best when refrigerated overnight.

title: crazy crust pizza
directions: Combine ingredients for crust.
Mix until smooth.
Pour batter into greased and flour dusted 15 x 10-inch pan.
Tilt pan until bottom is covered only.
Arrange toppings of meat, onions and mushrooms on top.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes, on low rack, until golden brown.
Drizzle with cheese and sauce.
Return to oven and bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt with berries.
Add lemon juice.
Put in pastry lined pan and dot with butter.
Add top crust and bake in hot oven at 425° until it is lightly browned.
Then reduce heat to 350° and bake 25 minutes longer.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together a few hours before serving.
Keep refrigerated.
It will keep about 5 days.
Use as dip with tortilla chips.

title: pork chops
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Mix in a large bowl until sugar is dissolved.
Add chops one at a time, then place chops in large Ziploc bags.
Pour remaining sauce in bags with chops and let stand overnight.
Ready to grill next day on medium coals, turning frequently, for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Mix in egg, vanilla and almond extract.
Stir dry ingredients together and blend into creamed mixture.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Heat oven to 375°.
Divide dough in half and roll out on lightly floured cloth covered board. (I put sleeve on rolling pin too.) Roll 3/16-inch thick or less. Cut in 2 or 2 1/2-inch shapes.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar. Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 7 or 8 minutes until delicately golden.

title: microwave peanut butter cookies
directions: Place butter in a microwave-safe bowl, breaking it up into pieces.
Microwave on High power for about 45 seconds, covered with wax paper.
Beat in the sugars, vanilla, peanut butter and eggs.
Combine flour, bran, oats and baking soda.
Stir into butter mixture.

title: apple crunch
directions: Pare apples and slice into a 9-inch pie pan.
Add water and sprinkle apples with 1/2 cup sugar.
Dot with butter or margarine and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Put flour, brown sugar, salt and shortening (best with butter) in mixing bowl and work together until mixture is of the consistency of corn meal.
Then sprinkle it over the top of the apples.
Bake 45 minutes in a moderate oven (350°) or until top is golden brown.

title: roast pork
directions: Insert garlic under fat of meat.
Place meat in doubled plastic bags; stir all ingredients together.
Pour over meat.
Put meat in bag in dish; refrigerate 24 hours, turning occasionally.
Remove meat.
Place on shallow pan.
Strain marinade and reserve.
Bake in 350° oven for about 40 minutes per pound.
Baste with marinade during roasting.

title: south of the border franks
directions: Roll frankfurters in mustard and coat them with the crushed corn chips.
Place on baking sheet, bake in 400° oven about 10 minutes.
In saucepan, melt butter, saute onion and green pepper until tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, pickles and chili powder. Heat to serving temperature.
Serve over franks.
Makes 4 servings.

title: black-eyed pea dip
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet, add seasonings.
Stir in tomato sauce, Rotel and peas.
Simmer for 30 minutes on medium heat or 2 hours in crock pot.
Stir in pimentos and cheese whiz just before removing from heat.

title: baby lima beans with tomatoes and sage
directions: In a large, heavy-bottomed frying pan, combine garlic, oil and sage; cook over low heat, stirring frequently, for 5 to 7 minutes or until the garlic begins to turn golden.
Add the lima beans and tomatoes or tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 20 minutes or until the lima beans have absorbed most of the liquid.
Season with pepper.

title: glaze icing for tube cake
directions: Put all in saucepan. Bring to rolling boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove
from
heat
and
place
pan in sink of cold water. It
will
turn
white
syrup
color. Beat and stir with spoon until it turns white and thick enough to glaze cake.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine all the ingredients except the grated cheese.
Place in refrigerator and let marinate for several hours or overnight. When ready to serve, sprinkle with grated cheese, if desired.

title: mexican cabbage
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper together in a pot. Add cabbage and let cook for a few minutes, until cabbage cooks down a little.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until cabbage is tender.
(You may want to add more chili powder if spicier flavor is desired.)
Serve immediately.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients, putting cheese in last.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: fudge
directions: Blend sugar and cocoa; add milk and butter.
Do not mix.
Cook 2 minutes.
Remove from microwave; then stir and add vanilla.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Squeeze liquid from tomatoes; add vinegar and water.
Sift sugar with salt, flour and spices; mix with tomatoes.
Pour into pie shell and dot with butter.
Cover as for apple pie.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes.

title: shrimp and pepper kabobs
directions: Peel shrimp, leaving tails intact.
Arrange in a large shallow dish. Combine lemon juice, oil, soy sauce, parsley, onion, salt, pepper and garlic in a medium bowl. Stir well.
Pour half of the mixture over the shrimp.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator 4 hours. Drain shrimp, discarding marinade.

Thread shrimp onto 4 (12-inch) skewers alternately with pepper pieces. Grill over medium coals 3 minutes on each side or until shrimp turns pink, basting with remaining marinade. Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: kourabiedes(greek cookies)
directions: Beat butter and sugar until creamy, about 15 minutes.
Add egg yolk, flavorings and almonds, beating until well blended.
By hand, gradually add sifted flour to make a soft dough.
Pinch off pieces of the dough and shape carefully into various designs (crescent, round, etc.).
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until very lightly browned.
Allow to cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.
Carefully place on flat surface which has been sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar over cookies. Cool.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water; set aside.
Cream together shortening, egg, salt and sugar, then add 2 cups warm water.
Next, add yeast mixture.
Add flour and mix well.
Put in large greased bowl; let rise.
Push down and put in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to use, shape into rolls and let rise 3 hours.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes, until brown.
Can be baked one half done, then kept in refrigerator or frozen until ready to use.

title: peanut patties
directions: Mix all together. Cook 1 hour and 10 minutes over low heat. Start timing as soon as you put pan on burner.
Stir occasionally. Take off heat and add 1 tablespoon butter or oleo. Beat until thick and creamy, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Drop on wax paper with large spoon.

title: shepherds pie
directions: Mix gravy, onion and meat together.
Place in well greased 1-quart casserole. Pile mashed potatoes loosely on top.
Bake at 300° until potatoes brown on top.

title: corn fritters
directions: Grate corn and mix beaten eggs and all other ingredients.
Fry in hot pan like pancakes.

title: buttermilk sauce
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan and bring to boil for 2 minutes. Pour over Apple Cinnamon Pound Cake while still in pan.

title: spinach manicotti
directions: Clean spinach and set aside to dry on paper towel.
Mix cottage cheese, Ricotta cheese, garlic, salt and pepper, egg and onion in bowl.
Chop spinach and add to cheese mix.

title: butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix thoroughly all ingredients.
Roll dough 1/4-inch thick on lightly floured cloth-covered board.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch circles.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: jo's candy
directions: Melt white chocolate and pour over mix in bowl.
Spread on wax paper.

title: jackson's favorite chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, eggs and both sugars.
Add flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in chips.
Spoon onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°. Bake until lightly golden.
Do not overbake.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate for 2 hours before serving. Great with veggies or as a dressing on salad or baked potatoes!

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Mix soup mix in mayonnaise and sour cream.
Add rest of ingredients.
Chill at least two hours.
Serve with crackers or in pumpernickel round bread.

title: candy sweet potatoes
directions: Mix sugar, butter, water and salt in heavy skillet.
Cook until bubbly.
Add sweet potatoes and cook slowly, turning occasionally, about 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: corn syrup brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar in mixing bowl.
Blend in syrup and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg. Combine flour, salt and cocoa in another bowl.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9 x 3/4-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until brownies begin to pull away from the edge of the pan.
Delicious served warm.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef or turkey over medium heat and add seasoning according to directions; pour onto a bed of lettuce surrounded by diced tomatoes.
Spread sour cream over the top of meat just enough to cover; top with Cheddar cheese and pour taco sauce over very top.

title: orange slurpee
directions: Combine orange juice and ice in blender.
Blend approximately 1 to 2 minutes or until all ice is crushed.

title: christmas salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water with pineapple.
Let set.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Add the first 3 ingredients to cornmeal.
Follow directions on box to mix and bake.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese into bowl; add butter.
Stir bowl in sink of hot water.
Add flour with pepper gradually to cheese mixture and knead with hands until smooth.
Pack into cookie press.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 275° oven for 35 to 45 minutes. Sprinkle with salt while hot.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Melt butter in skillet. Saute onions. Add spices. Add shrimp and cook for 2 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: zucchini pizza
directions: Note:
This recipe can be tailored for as little or as many ingredients as are available.

title: log jam cookies
directions: Beat sugar, margarine, egg and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Divide dough in 4 parts.
Make 4 rolls on cookie sheet.
Make well in center of rolls and fill with jam.
Bake at 350° for 17 minutes.
Spread a light glaze made with confectioners sugar, vanilla and milk.
Cut in 1 to 1 1/2-inch size pieces.

title: bacon appetizer crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat cream cheese, bacon, cheese, onion, parsley and milk.
Separate dough into 8 rectangles. Spread with 2 tablespoons mix. Cut each rectangle in half. Roll up triangles. Place on sheet and brush with egg mixture. Sprinkle with seeds.

title: onioned potatoes
directions: Scrub spuds; do not peel.
Cut each in 3 to 4 lengthwise slices.
Blend butter and soup mix; spread on slices, then reassemble potatoes.
Wrap each in foil, overlapping ends.
Bake at 350° until done, turning once.
Can be put on grill 45 to 60 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: In skillet, prepare taco seasoning mix with ground beef and water.
Once beef is browned, add refried beans and heat 5 minutes.
In bowl, spread the beef and bean mixture and layer the remaining ingredients in following order: grated cheese, ripe olives, chopped tomato, mashed avocado, sour cream and salsa.
Top with thinly sliced green onions.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Peel and core apples to fill a 12-quart pan.
Cook apples until soft; put through blender.
Mix spices into sauce.
Pour into a 4 1/2-quart crock-pot.
Cook on high for 8 hours or more. Seal hot apple butter in sterilized jars.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix butter or Crisco, sugar, eggs and vanilla well. Add flour using a teaspoon made into ball. Place on greased pan; flatten out and bake at 325° until brown around edges.

title: meatball soup with spaghetti rings
directions: Combine ingredients in a large pot; bring to a boil.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil 2 1/2 to 3 pound chicken.
Take off bones.
Save 2 cups of broth.
Combine soup, broth and mixed vegetables.
Bring to a boil and pour over chicken.
Then mix in bowl the margarine (melted), flour, buttermilk and salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon the mixture over all.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes at 425°.

title: bean soup(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Wash beans and cover with water.
Add 1 tablespoon salt and soak at least 3 hours or overnight.
Drain beans and place in a pot with 2 1/2 quarts of water.
Boil slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Add ham or cooked sausage, cut in bite-sized pieces or whole raw shrimp.
Add sliced onion and garlic.
Cook 2 hours more.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and lemon juice.
Add salt and pepper, if needed. Cook at least 30 minutes more.

title: onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in
butter
in large skillet until tender. Put in 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Combine soup, milk and soy sauce, mixing well and pour over onions.
Sprinkle cheese over top and place bread
slices
over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yield:
8 servings.

title: sausage stir-fry
directions: Slice sausage.
Cut onion and pepper into strips.
Chop tomatoes.
In skillet or wok, pour in oil and all ingredients except rice.
Stir-fry until vegetables are tender.
Prepare rice as directed.
Pour stir-fry over rice.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 25 minutes or until brown on top.

title: 3-bean salad
directions: Mix together and top with dressing.

title: 4 day coconut cake
directions: Mix 2 cups sour cream, 1 1/2 cups sugar and 3 cups frozen coconut.
Stir and put in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Make 1 yellow cake mix in 3 layers and frost with the frosting.
Put in covered container and refrigerate for 3 days before cutting.

title: pot pie
directions: Place all ingredients, except pie crusts, in stock pot.
Heat on medium until chicken is partially cooked.
Place ingredients in one pie crust; level to top of pie plate.
Place second crust over top.
Poke holes in top crust and pinch close along edges.
Place in oven at 325° for 15 minutes, then increase oven temperature to 400° and bake until crust is golden brown.
Place any extra ingredients over top of pie when serving.

title: oat cake
directions: Mix oats, butter, and boiling water together.
Let cool a little.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to oat mixture. Add eggs and vanilla.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix together pecans, butter and flour.
Press in bottom of pan.
Bake until brown at 350°.
Cool.

title: baked rice
directions: Heat oil good and hot (until it smokes).
Beat eggs until frothy, take off heat and add eggs.
Scramble until almost set. Add onions, chestnuts and soy sauce.
Add cooled rice.
Mix well. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat with onions; drain.
Add beans, soups and enchilada sauce.
Line large casserole dish with tortilla chips; spread meat mixture on top of chips.
Spoon tomatoes and green chilies on top of meat mixture.
Put grated cheese on and top with the rest of chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: zucchini squash jam
directions: Measure 3 cups flour into large bowl.
Answer telephone, take large bowl off small son's head, sweep up flour.

title: baked breakfast
directions: Beat milk, salt and mustard.
Add bread, cheese, ham; mix.
Put in well-greased 9 1/2 x 13 inch glass baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Cover with foil.
Must refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: holiday jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add frozen orange juice and grated apples.
Let set until firm.
Combine whipped cream and drained pineapple.
Spread on top.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Place cabbage in large pot of boiling water for 5 minutes to soften leaves.
Remove and cool.
Mix beef, rice, egg, onion, salt and pepper.
Loosen cabbage leaves.
Place a spoonful of meat mixture on cabbage leaf and roll up.
Place seam side down in baking dish.
Mix soup, brown sugar and vinegar; pour over cabbage rolls.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together and let stand 24 hours.

title: ultimate macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; rinse with cold water and drain well.
Add olive oil; toss and cool.
Add onion, cucumber, tomatoes and black olives; toss.
Add mayonnaise, pepper, garlic powder and salt to taste.
Add shrimp; mix.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: great chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken, in bowl.
Dip each piece of chicken in sauce.
Place pieces in slow cooker.
Pour remaining sauce over top.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or high 3 to 4 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Place first 7 ingredients in pan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 8 to 12 minutes until tender.
Blend in blender.
Stir in lime juice.
Pour into 8 bowls and garnish with slice of lemon, teaspoon of sour cream and sprinkle of chives. Enjoy.
Serves 8.

title: rhubarb sponge pie
directions: Cut rhubarb fine; add rolled crackers, sugar and beaten egg yolks.
Beat whites of eggs light and fold into mixture.
Bake in 1 crust until knife comes out clean.
When cold cover with whipped cream.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour, salt and soda.
Add to oil mixture.
Stir in vanilla, apples, coconut and nuts.

title: easy pickles
directions: Put cucumbers in gallon jar or churn.
Add salt and spices. Fill with white vinegar; let stand 6 weeks.
Take out and drain. Slice cucumbers.
Add sugar; stir easy.
Let stand 2 more weeks, then seal in jars.

title: hearty vegetable soup
directions: Combine the undrained beans, water and remaining vegetables and seasonings in a 4-quart Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for about 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: 1 box yellow cake mix, set aside 1 cup. Add: 1/2 cup melted margarine, 1 egg. Mix and spread in 9 X 13 pan, ungreased.

title: chocolate fudge cookies(no-bake cookies)
directions: Boil sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa for 3 minutes; start timing after the mixture reaches a full, rolling boil.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter, oatmeal, vanilla and nuts.
Mix until well blended, then drop on wax paper by the teaspoonful. Allow to cool thoroughly.

title: carrot-potato pancakes(brunch)
directions: Using coarse side of grater, grate potatoes, carrots and onion into mixing bowl.
Beat in eggs, spice, matzo meal and melted fat. Meanwhile, heat 1/2 cup Nyafat in large skillet over medium heat 3 minutes.
Drop potato batter by tablespoons into hot fat.
Flatten into thick cakes and fry 3 minutes on each side over medium heat. Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot (serves 4 to 5) with applesauce.

title: erie party potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add sour cream and cream cheese, salt, garlic powder, and pepper.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Add chives.
Pour into lightly buttered 2 1/2 quart casserole. Sprinkle with paprika and dot with butter.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until golden.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown chuck and onion in oil; drain oil.
Add taco mix, following package directions.
Add Tabasco.
Place in layers over meat mixture:
lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and Doritos.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: franks, peppers and potatoes
directions: Saute potatoes in hot olive oil.
Add peppers, franks cut into chunks and garlic salt to taste.
Lower heat, cover and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: au gratin beans almondine
directions: Cook onions in 1 tablespoon bacon fat until tender.
Add milk and cheese and cook and stir over low heat until cheese melts. Add green beans and pepper.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish; top with crackers and bacon.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: six slim cupcakes
directions: Line a microwave muffin pan or glass custard cups with paper baking liners.
Combine sugar, flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt. Stir with wire whisk.
Pour water into a one cup glass measure. Add oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Using wire whisk, stir liquids into dry mixture.
Pour batter into cups.
Microwave 2 or 2 1/2 minutes on High power or until done when tested with a toothpick.
Rotate cups once.
Cool before removing cupcakes to a rack.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all
ingredients well. Put in 9x13 baking dish and top with crushed saltine crackers. Drizzle with melted butter. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly toward the center.

title: delta bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Gradually add flour, salt, baking powder and vanilla.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Before baking, beat the two egg whites and add the brown sugar.
Beat well and then add the pecans. Spread this mixture over the dough in the pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan and cut into bars.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread. Crumble into a bowl. Mix all other ingredients and refrigerate.

title: holiday potatoes
directions: Will need a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in olive oil.
Add tomatoes with some of the juice.
Add olives; simmer.
Add chicken and wine or sherry.
Add cayenne pepper; simmer a few more minutes.
Lightly grease bottom of deep casserole dish with more olive oil.
Place noodles on bottom.
Cover with chicken mixture.
Cover with cheese.
Place bacon on the top.
Bake at 350° just long enough to melt cheese.
If bacon seems to be getting too crisp, cover with lid the last few minutes.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: english trifle
directions: Place 1 layer
of
cake,
broken up, in bottom of large glass bowl (punch
bowl works well).
Pour 1/4 cup sherry over cake. Spread 1/2	of
pudding
over cake.
Spread with 1/2 of cherry pie filling.
Pour
can
apricot
nectar over all. Spread a layer of
Cool
Whip
over all.	Sprinkle with nuts. Repeat layering in the same order with the remaining ingredients, except Cool Whip and nuts.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: blueberry sour cream pie
directions: Sift together flour and sugar; set aside 1/4 cup.
Combine with sour cream and blueberries.
Pour into pie shell, top with remaining flour mixture.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes; top with whipped cream.

title: the earthquake cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Spray 10 x 14-inch pan with Pam spray.
Spread small amount of cake batter on bottom of pan, just enough to cover.
Mix pecans and coconut and pour into pan. Press gently into batter.
Pour rest of batter over pecans and coconut.
Melt margarine and cream cheese in microwave.
Mix with powdered sugar.
Pour mixture over cake mix.
Do not stir.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Now watch the earthquake happen as it cracks!

title: frozen pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple; save the juice.
Add sugar and flour to juice.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Add cheese and stir to melt.
Beat until smooth and creamy; cool.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Freeze.
Serve frozen in squares. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: lasagne pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie
plate.
Cook and stir beef until it browns.
Drain and stir in oregano, basil, tomato paste and 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese.
Put layer of cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese in plate.
Spoon beef mixture over top.
Beat milk, Bisquick, eggs, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: chili good
directions: Cook meat until browned.
Add onion, garlic and green pepper. Cook until tender.
Add spices, tomatoes, tomato sauce and paste. Simmer about 30 minutes.
Add drained beans and simmer 5 minutes.

title: cheese and potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
In large boiler, boil potatoes until fork-tender (do not overcook).
Drain and pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour and milk; heat over medium heat.
Add cheese; heat until melted.
Pour over potatoes, covering well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: skinny blueberry cobbler
directions: Combine the blueberries, sugar, sweetener, tapioca and water in the bottom of a shallow 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with the vanilla.

Fork-blend the biscuit mix with the skim milk until evenly moistened and spoon on top of the berries. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes until the biscuit crust is well browned. Yields 8 servings.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Mix melted butter and cracker crumbs.
Press in bottom of 9-inch pan.
Layer with other ingredients and pour condensed milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut.
Very rich!

title: rich lemon pie
directions: Chill evaporated milk, then whip.
Add Eagle Brand milk and sugar.
Add lemon juice.
Pour into baked pie shells or graham cracker crusts.
Makes 2 pies.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook rice.
Brown onions and pepper in butter.
Put beef in pepper and onions.
Cook until meat is brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer over low heat 15 minutes.

title: hazel's casserole(serves 6)
directions: Mix altogether.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Place white sugar and cinnamon in plastic bag.
Add biscuit pieces and shake to coat each piece. Grease tube pan and place biscuits in layers until all are used. Sprinkle layers with pecans, raisins and coconut.
Bring brown sugar and margarine to boil in saucepan.
Pour over top of biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Allow to cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.
Turn top side up to serve.
Pieces may be picked apart.

title: sarah's homemade peanut butter
directions: Remove shells from peanuts and discard.
Place peanuts in blender and add oil and salt.
Blend until smooth.

title: chipped beef cheese ball(very good)
directions: Chop scallions and half the greens mix with the cream cheese and chipped beef.
Form into a ball and refrigerate.

title: green chili
directions: Brown pork in oil.
Stir in chicken broth and garlic.
Simmer for 3 hours in crock-pot.
Add green chilies.
Simmer 1/2 hour. Add flour and oil roux to desired thickness.
Serve with fresh tortillas.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Scald 2 quarts milk and add to the rest of the ingredients, except cinnamon.
Beat egg whites and put in last.
Pour into 4 unbaked pie crusts and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Have oven at 400°; after 10 minutes, turn down to 325°.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Layer pineapple in bottom of pan.
Cover with cheese, then top with cracker crumbs.
Mix sugar, flour and juice.
Pour over top. Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: batter rolls
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and oleo.
Cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in large warm bowl containing water.
Stir in "milk mixture", egg and flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Punch down and shape into 2 dozen rolls. Place on greased baking sheet.
Cover and let rise until doubled. Bake at 400° until done.

title: no oil tabouli(try it; you'll be amazed!)
directions: In large bowl, combine tabouli mix and cold water.
Stir and let stand while preparing other ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Let stand in refrigerator at least 4 hours before serving.
Recipe makes 10 servings.
Fat-free.

title: cooked potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Cook until fork can go through potatoes.
Drain off half the water.
Add butter, milk, salt and pepper.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Tenderize chicken breasts (by pounding).
Roll in a small amount of flour, salt and pepper.
Saute the green onion in butter in heavy skillet.
Put in chicken, scallions and butter and brown chicken.
(It is best to weight chicken for even browning and keep it flat.)
Remove chicken from skillet when brown.
Deglaze pan with lemon juice, lemon peel, parsley and garlic.
Boil until reduced.
Pour over chicken. Serve with brown or wild rice.

title: venus dimilo soup
directions: Brown hamburg and onion in small amount of butter with salt and pepper.
Add Veg-All and tomatoes with liquid.
Add dissolved bouillon in water.
Simmer 20 minutes; add orzo.
Simmer 10 more minutes.
Serve with grated cheese and Italian bread.

title: roasted peppers
directions: Wash, core and split peppers in half.
Place on broiler pan lined with foil.
Broil until skin is charred black.
Remove and cover with foil and let stand for about 1/2 hour.
Peel blackened skin and try to reserve any liquid from peppers in a bowl.
Cut peppers into 1/2-inch strips.
Place in bowl with liquid and add the rest of ingredients.
Stir and allow to stand for about 1 hour before serving.
Good as appetizer with Mozzarella or added to a sandwich.

title: caesar salad
directions: Assemble and mix ingredients.

title: crisp skillet chicken with gravy
directions: Dust chicken with flour.
In skillet, brown chicken in butter. Add water.
Cover.
Cook over low heat 45 minutes or until done. Uncover the last 10 minutes to crisp chicken.
Remove to warm platter.
Add gravy; heat, stirring to loosen browned bits.
Serve with chicken.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Blend together sugar, butter, eggs, sour cream and vanilla. Set aside.
Sift together cake flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Beat into shortening mixture.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat until creamy.
Pour into greased dish.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel potatoes and onion; grate both into mixing bowl.
Add slightly beaten eggs, flour and salt; mix well.
Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Drop potato mixture into hot oil by 1/3 cupfuls, forming ragged cakes.
Cook over medium heat until crisp and brown (resist the urge to turn pancakes too quickly).
Serve with hot maple syrup and butter or applesauce.
Terrific for breakfast/brunch or as a side dish at dinner.

title: chicken pan pie
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
(Cut chicken in small pieces and spread over bottom of dish.)
Sprinkle Veg-All and eggs over chicken.
Mix broth, soup, salt and pepper together and heat until warm.
Pour into casserole dish over chicken.
Mix self-rising flour, buttermilk and butter together and pour over top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until golden brown.

title: sea foam
directions: Combine and bring to hard ball stage.
Right before it reaches hard ball stage, beat egg white until they stand in large mixing bowl.
Slowly stir (dribble) in syrup and beat until it stands in a peak.
Spoon (teaspoon) on wax paper and let set.

title: white candy
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter 8 to 10 minutes. Add Marshmallow Creme and nuts.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Cook and stir until thick.
Alternate pudding, then wafers, then bananas.
Do this until container is full; top with vanilla wafers.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Garnish with bacon bits just before serving.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Lightly brown mushrooms and green pepper in butter; add flour and blend together.
Add milk and seasonings to taste.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Stir some of hot mixture into egg yolk and add to remaining hot mixture.
Continue to cook at least 10 minutes, then add chicken or turkey and pimento.
Heat a little longer, until all mixture is hot.
Serve on hot buttered toast. Serves 6.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream ingredients from top to bottom.
Serve with Town House crackers or celery.
Make at least one day ahead and store in refrigerator.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: lobster stuffed tenderloin of beef
directions: Cut tenderloin lengthwise to within 1/2 inch of bottom.
Place frozen lobster tails in boiling salted water to cover; simmer 5 minutes.
Remove lobster from shells; cut in half.
Place lobster end to end inside beef.
Combine melted margarine and lemon juice; drizzle on lobster.
Close meat around and tie roast together with string.
Place in roasting pan on rack.
Roast at 425° for 30 minutes.
Place bacon on top; roast 5 minutes longer.
Saute onion in margarine in saucepan.
Add wine and garlic salt and heat. Slice roast.
Spoon on wine sauce.
Serves 8.

title: heavenly peach
directions: Pour sugar over peaches and let sit for 1 hour.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, crumble cake; add sweetened fruit and sprinkle half the coconut over this.
Mix pudding according to directions; add Cool Whip.
Pour over peaches and coconut.
Shake pan for pudding to sink through fruit.
Sprinkle rest of coconut over this. Refrigerate overnight or at least 6 hours.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender, then dip your vegetables in the dip.

title: salmon patties
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well with hands; form into patties and roll each into fine cracker crumbs.
Fry on both sides in medium hot skillet with 2 tablespoons oil until golden brown.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Pour half this mixture in glass baking dish. Refrigerate until firm.
Evenly spread sour cream over mixture. Gently spoon remainder of strawberry mixture over sour cream and refrigerate.

title: microwave apple crisp
directions: Microwave margarine or butter in medium-size bowl or 4-cup measure until melted.
Stir in oats, brown sugar, flour and nuts. Microwave on High (100%) for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring frequently during the last 2 minutes, until crisp and toasted.
Pour filling into 9-inch microwave-safe pie pan.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes, until hot.
Sprinkle oat mixture over filling.
Serve immediately.
Top with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Place meat in large kettle; cover with cold water.
Add garlic and onion; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover tightly and simmer 3 1/2 hours or until tender.
Place meat on platter and keep warm. Skim fat from liquid.
Add cabbage; simmer 15 minutes, uncovered. Carve meat in thin, diagonal slices across grain.

title: pretzel clusters(microwave)
directions: Melt chocolate.
Stir in broken pretzels and peanuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
When hardened, store in covered container.
Easy to make and eat!

title: ham biscuits
directions: Spray regular or mini muffin pans with Pam.
Fill cups half full.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: honey brownies
directions: Grease a 9-inch square pan.
Cream butter and sugar in a small mixer bowl; blend in honey and vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, cocoa and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from edge of pan.
Cool in pan (top with frosting, if desired).

title: caribbean banana nut bread
directions: Stir together dry ingredients, including nuts.
Blend remaining ingredients.
Add all at once to flour mixture, stirring only until flour is moistened.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) about 60 to 65 minutes or until tests done.
If necessary, cover with aluminum foil to prevent top overbrowning.
Cool 15 minutes before removing to rack.

title: homemade pimento cheese
directions: Have cheese at room temperature; add pimento and mayonnaise.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook corn syrup, sugar, water and raw peanuts to 230°.
Add margarine and vanilla and cook to 290°.
Take off heat and add baking soda.
This makes it real airy.
But make sure baking soda is fresh or it will not be any good.
Then pour onto a well buttered long cookie sheet and let cool a little to where you can work with it with your hands (buttered) and stretch as to desired thickness.

title: tasty hamburger
directions: Place meat and onions in a heavy skillet and lightly brown. Add celery, salt, pepper and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted. Cool in the refrigerator.
Butter one side of the bun and mustard on the other side.
Fill with the cooled mixture.
Wrap each in foil.
Heat in a 400° oven for 20 minutes or until hot.

title: apple nut pudding
directions: Beat egg well.
Add sugar and heat.
Add rest of dry ingredients and apples, nuts and vanilla.
Serve with Cool Whip, ice cream or other topping.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: *Broccoli, cauliflower, red pepper or broccoli, onions and mushrooms.

title: dill crackers
directions: Mix and pour first 4 ingredients over oyster crackers.
Mix well and let stand overnight.

title: smoky baked potato
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Cool, peel and slice.
Sprinkle a deep well-greased (Pam) oven-proof dish with some of the bread crumbs.
Place a layer of sliced potatoes over this.
Chop bacon and fry until crisp.
Scatter half of the bacon over the potatoes in the dish.
Melt butter and cottage cheese in saucepan over low heat.
Pour 1/2 of this mixture over bacon and potatoes.
Add another layer of bacon and potatoes; pour remaining butter and cottage cheese mixture over dish.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle remaining bread crumbs on top and dot with butter.
Bake in moderate oven (275° to 300°) uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: peach marmalade
directions: Peel peaches and put through coarse blade or food chopper. Also the oranges, rind and all.
Cut cherries in quarters, add sugar and cook on low burner until thick, stirring often.
Place in jars and refrigerate.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Place sweetened peaches in deep baking dish with lemon juice. Sift dry ingredients together; add beaten egg.
Mix with fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle evenly over peaches.
Pour melted butter over the crumb mixture.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 or 40 minutes or until crusty and brown.
Serve warm with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, water and Karo and stir well.
Add peanuts and butter.
Cook, stirring until syrup becomes golden brown and reaches hard crack stage (very thick with small bubbles).
Drop in ice water; if it becomes hard in water, it's ready.
Quickly add vanilla, then soda and stir quickly.
Pour into 2 well-buttered cookie sheets.
Turn when cool.
Break into pieces.

title: tabbouleh
directions: Wash bulghur two times; drain lightly.
Let set for half hour. Extra water will absorb.
May drain and squeeze moisture from it. Mix all greens and vegetables with bulghur well.
Add olive oil and lemon juice, plus spices.
Garnish with mint and radishes. Serve in bowl with lettuce leaves and small wedges of bread. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: lemon-garlic broccoli over spaghetti squash(makes 6 servings; carb count: 11 grams)
directions: Place spaghetti squash in large saucepan. Pierce skin with fork. Add enough water to cover. Bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat to low; simmer, covered, 20 to 30 minutes or until squash is soft. Cut squash in half lengthwise; remove seeds.
Set aside.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup, milk and vinegar.
Cook mixture until soft ball stage.
Remove from fire and cool a bit.
Beat in peanut butter thoroughly.
Pour into a buttered pan.
Enjoy.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cut up onions and brown lightly in Crisco or oil.
Add chopped pepper and tomato paste; simmer about 5 minutes, stirring very often to keep from burning.
Add 2 cans water for each can of paste.
Add puree and sauce.
Bring to a boil and add a pinch of soda and rest of spices to taste.
If ribs are not used, I add some lightly fried ground beef for meat sauce.
Add meat balls (do not fry first) and cook at least 3 hours over low heat.
Serves 12.

title: ajiaco bogotano
directions: In heavy 5-quart casserole, combine chicken, shinbone and water.
The water should cover the chicken by an inch.
If necessary, add more water.
Bring to a boil over high heat, skimming off the scum that rises to the surface.
Add onion, bay leaf, cumin, thyme, salt and pepper.
Reduce to low heat.
Cover and cook for 30 minutes, or until the chicken is tender.
Transfer chicken to platter.
Pick out and discard shinbone and onion. Strain stock through sieve; return to casserole.
Skin chicken and cut or pull into pieces.
Discard skin and bones.
Cut chicken into 1/4-inch strips.

title: layered bean dip
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, mix taco mix with can of beans well and spread in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread sour cream on top. Then top with salsa, spreading all around.

title: can't leave alone bars
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and oil together with a fork. Reserve 3/4 cup crumbs. Press remaining mixture in bottom of cake pan. Melt butter, chocolate chips and milk together, then pour over crust. Top with reserved crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until brown on top.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix flour, soda and baking powder together.
Beat egg yolks. Add sugar and oil.
Add mincemeat, then flour mixture.
Fold in all fruit. Beat egg whites stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake in greased angel food cake pan
at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: italian mixed pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Cool.
Mix remaining ingredients. Refrigerate for
1 hour; ready to serve.

title: pineapple cookie
directions: Cream butter and sugars; add egg and vanilla.
Add crushed pineapple and nuts.
Stir all other ingredients and add to mixture.
Drop on cookie sheet.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Layer 1/2 potatoes and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat layers.
Combine egg, milk and salt.
Pour mix over potatoes and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad supreme
directions: Fold fruit into pie filling with rubber spatula.
Spoon into sherbet cups or glass bowl.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Melt in a 450° oven 1/4 cup margarine and 1/4 cup shortening. Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper. Cover chicken with flour mixture and put in pan, skin side down, first for 30 minutes, then turn over and cook 30 minutes on other side.

title: pasta with clam sauce
directions: Cook pasta until done as desired.
Combine chowder and clams until hot and bubbly.
Stir in wine.
Toss with pasta.

title: clam fritters
directions: Mince clams and mix into batter. Drop mixture by tablespoonful into frypan and brown well.

title: hominy grits
directions: Cook slowly 25 to 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Serve with gravy or with butter or with cream and sugar.
Chill the leftovers.
Slice and fry in butter until golden brown.

title: collards
directions: Cook meat and pepper up.
Salt to taste.
Wash collards, cut out large stalks.
Check each leaf for worms.
Cook until tender. Take up.
Drain and skim grease off top of water cooked in and chop up real fine.
Serve with meat and corn bread.

title: saucepot meat balls
directions: In deep, heavy saucepan, bring to boil quickly onion soup mix, water and 1 1/2 cans tomato sauce.
Simmer covered for 10 minutes. Mix ground beef, seasonings, parsley and remaining 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Shape into 16 meat balls; place meat balls into sauce. Simmer gently, uncovered, for 25 minutes, turning occasionally. Serve over hot noodles or spaghetti.
Makes approximately 4 servings.

title: chicken-n-biscuits
directions: You will need 1 large size Reynolds oven cooking bag.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and wash. Drain well.
Add all ingredients. Refrigerate overnight.

title: fresh okra and tomatoes
directions: Fry bacon crisp.
Remove from skillet and drain.
Fry okra in bacon drippings.
Add green pepper and onion.
Cook until tender. Add tomatoes which have been peeled and cubed.
Stir well. Crumble bacon.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 15 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Fill casserole half full of thinly sliced potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste; dot with butter.
Put half can of mushroom soup. Put another layer of potatoes and other half of mushroom soup. Pour soup can half full of milk over potatoes.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: mini ham and cheese rolls
directions: Slice rolls lengthwise and place bottom half in the foil tray that the rolls came in. Place a layer of ham and cheese on bottom half of rolls. Combine butter, poppy seeds, mustard, onion flakes and worcestershire to make a sauce. Spread a small amount over cheese and ham layer.
Replace top half of roll and spread with remaining sauce. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 15-20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: spinach dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients; blend well.
Cover and refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.
Serve with crisp vegetables.

title: bread dressing(for meats)
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chalupa
directions: Soak beans overnight (or quick soak).
Drain.
Put beans, roast and all ingredients in Dutch oven.
Cover with water; cover and cook at 325° for 4 hours.
Remove bones and fat.
Shred meat and return to pot.
Return to oven and bake 1 additional hour. Serve with tortilla chips, tortillas, shredded cheese, chopped green onions, chopped tomatoes, guacamole, etc.
Serves 8.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart bowl, mix together sugar and syrup and microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Take out of microwave and stir in peanuts.
Microwave for 3 to 5 minutes until brown.
Add butter and vanilla.
Blend well.
Microwave 1 to 2 minutes (should be lightly brown).
Add baking soda and stir until frothy.
Pour into Pammed cookie sheet and cool.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together.
Roll into small balls and place on ungreased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 30 to 40 balls.

title: un-hot chocolate
directions: Combine these 3 ingredients for an "almost chocolate" taste treat (without the guilt).

title: orange julius drink
directions: Blend in blender for 30 seconds.
Pour into 2 small glasses or 1 large glass.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Pour pie filling in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon on filling, slice butter on top and cover with top crust. Bake at 400° until brown.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower for 5 minutes in boiling water.
Drain. Combine the next 5 items.
Stir in tomatoes, onion, 1 1/4 cups cheese and cauliflower.
Put in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with 1/4 cup cheese. Bake for approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: clams casino
directions: Saute onions and peppers in butter until soft.
Add minced clams with juice and bacon.
Add bread crumbs, if necessary for consistency.
Fill shells.
Top with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese.
I usually save some bacon to crumble over top also.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Place in long casserole dish. Combine brown sugar, white sugar, vanilla, butter flavor and salt. Pour boiling water over and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over potatoes.
Place in oven for 25 or 30 minutes at 350° or until potatoes are brown.

title: chicken-cordon bleu
directions: Separate chicken breasts in half.
Pound each piece to flatten.
Place 1/2 ounce ham in each piece, in the middle.
Add 1/2 ounce Monterey Jack cheese on top of the ham.
Fold chicken breast over and seal edges.
Dip each piece in the corn flake crumbs and salt mixture.
Coat well.
Place in shallow baking pan, sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix and pour into skillet with melted
butter
and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Use 10-inch skillet.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken, cuban style
directions: Clean and prepare the chicken (removal of the skin will reduce fat and caloric intake).
Crush garlic and spread over both sides of the chicken.
Sprinkle with oregano, salt and pepper, then add the lime or sour orange juice over the chicken.
Place on a 9 x 11-inch baking pan and bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes to an hour, until well done.
Serve with white rice and fried ripe plantains.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream both sugars and shortening together.
Add eggs and vanilla, mix well.
Mix flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add and mix until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients, one at a time, mixing after each addition.
Drop by spoonful on greased baking sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: dump cake
