directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread cherries on bottom of pan.
Spread pineapple on top of cherries. Sprinkle cake mix over pineapple.
Drizzle butter, then top with walnuts and coconut.
Do not mix.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Bake fudge cake mix by directions on box.
Cut cooled cake in small squares.
Prepare pudding mix by directions on box.
Layer the ingredients little by little, in a Trifle bowl.

title: date balls
directions: When cooled, roll into
balls and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: pineapple upside-down rolls
directions: Arrange
pineapple chunks in buttered and brown-sugared muffin pans.
Then drop in balls of sweet yeast dough.
(I use frozen bread dough.) Bake and serve warm.	They are wonderful!

title: pecan pie
directions: Place coarsely chopped nuts in unbaked pastry shell.
Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix together as you would corn bread.
Bake at 400° for about 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients, moistening with a little milk.
Fry quickly.
Makes 8 patties.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in greased glass 2-quart casserole. Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until browned on top at 350°.

title: 7 layer bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Melt in baking pan 1/4 cup butter. Press in 1 cup graham cracker crumbs.
Add one at a time the chocolate chips, coconut, butterscotch chips and pecans.
Pour condensed milk over top and bake 30 minutes.
Use a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: sauerkraut chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (8-inch) square or round baking pans.
Thoroughly cream margarine with sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together cocoa, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add dry mixture alternately with water to egg mixture.
Stir in sauerkraut.
Spoon into baking pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean and cake begins to pull away from sides.
Let cool.

title: chocolate chip cookie mix
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, salt and both sugars in large bowl.
Mix in shortening with fingers.
Stir in pecans and chocolate chips.
Store in airtight container in cool, dry place 6 months.
For longer storage, refrigerate or freeze.
Makes about 28 cups of mix.

title: fruit-cheese tray
directions: Arrange fruit and cheese on salad greens.
The fruit can be cut to your choosing.
Cut cheese into squares.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Peel shrimp and set aside.
Combine all other ingredients and simmer until onion, pepper and celery are done.
Add as much or as little sugar and Old Bay as you desire.
Add shrimp and cook until done, about 10 minutes.
Serve over white rice.
Serves 4.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine evaporated milk and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add chocolate; stir until melted.
Beat until creamy. Remove from heat.
Stir in butter, vanilla and salt.
Yields 3 cups.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add chopped cabbage to onions. Simmer until cabbage is tender.
Boil noodles until done.
Rinse, drain and add noodles to cabbage mixture.
Simmer until well blended.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add a pinch of sugar.

title: basic bread stuffing(for 10 pound turkey)
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo 10 to 15 minutes.
Combine crumbs with seasonings.
Combine all and toss lightly.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook meat; set aside.
Mix next 5 ingredients and add to meat. Serve with toast; Tostitos with cheese.

title: wild rice muffins
directions: Beat cooked rice with milk, eggs and shortening.
Sift dry ingredients into batter.
Mix lightly.
Bake in greased muffin cups at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O in large bowl with boiling water.
Dissolve completely.
Pour in bag of marshmallows.
Stir in drained pineapple and mix well.
Put in refrigerator until starts to set. Take out and stir in Cool Whip.
Put back in refrigerator to finish setting.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in pie shell.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except lemons, in a bowl; stir well.
Add sugar, if desired.
Slice lemons and add to mixture.
Serves 28 to 30.

title: southwestern red chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and garlic in large saucepan. Drain off excess fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat; boil gently, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add other ingredients, except Rice Krispies.
Mix thoroughly, then add Rice Krispies.
Put in refrigerator to harden, then make into balls and flatten.
Or you can use cookie shooter instead of refrigerating.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 15 minutes.

title: irish stew
directions: Mix together soups and sugar, then add meat. Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours. Add the mushrooms and continue to bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: annelle's cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce; mix well.
Chill until syrupy.
Fold in sour cream; beat lightly, if necessary.
Add nuts and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, butter and milk to a boil over medium heat.
Boil 5 minutes; stir constantly.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Pour into buttered pan and refrigerate.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add pumpkin mixture, add water.
Fold in nuts or raisins if desired.
This fills 3 medium greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Bake ahead, they freeze well.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Gradually stir in milk to form a batter.
Melt butter in a 9 x 9-inch pan. Toss peaches with 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour batter into butter without stirring.
Arrange peaches in batter.
bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: zucchini suprise
directions: Steam zucchini slices until tender.
Add oranges, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Sprinkle with pecans, serve.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown beef.
Add green pepper and onion flakes.
Drain fat and let simmer.
Add tomato paste and 1/2 can water.
Add pepperoni. Cook 1 package noodles; drain.
Add garlic powder and Chili-O mix to noodles.
Add all to meat mixture.
Put half of meat mixture into 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle half of cheese, then add rest of meat mixture, then rest of cheese.
Place in oven for 10 minutes at 350°, or until cheese melts.

title: carrot-pineapple cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together the dry ingredients. Add oil, eggs, carrots, pineapple and vanilla. Mix until all ingredients are moistened. Beat with electric mixer 2 minutes at medium speed. Pour batter into a greased and lightly floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° about 35 minutes. Cool.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients. Cut in shortening until mixture looks like coarse crumbs. Add peel, juice and egg to dry ingredients. Mix just enough to moisten. Fold in berries and nuts. Pour into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool. Wrap and store overnight before slicing.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Put flour in mixing bowl.
Add baking powder, shortening and salt.
Mix well.
Add enough milk to make a stiff dough.
Knead and roll out on floured board.
Cut into squares.
Drop in boiling chicken broth.
I put pepper over each layer.
Pour cream or half and half over all.
Simmer a few minutes.
Add cut up deboned chicken.

title: hamburger balls
directions: Mix all together, then make balls.
Blend rest of cream of celery soup with 1/2 cup water.

title: german's chocolate pound cake
directions: Partially melt chocolate over hot water.
Remove and stir rapidly until melted.
Cool.
Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, flavorings and buttermilk.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to shortening.
Mix well.
Blend in chocolate.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 9-inch tube pan.
Bake in a slow oven at 300° about 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from pan while still hot and place under tightly fitting cover until thoroughly cooled. Tastes great anytime, with or without glaze.

title: cream-cheese fudge
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, water and vanilla; blending smooth.
Quickly stir in melted chocolate and nuts.
Turn onto buttered pan, spreading fudge 1 inch thick.
Chill, cut in squares and top with walnuts, if desired.

title: aunt pat's baked spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and green peppers. Season with garlic powder. Drain. Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, oregano, black pepper, water and 1 teaspoon salt. Add mushrooms, if desired. Cover and cook slowly 20 minutes. Boil spaghetti noodles until tender; drain. Combine noodles and meat sauce. Spoon into an ungreased casserole dish. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top. Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 20 minutes or until center is bubbly.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Dump all ingredients into pie crust and bake at 400° until crust is golden brown.
Kids will love it.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and cream of tartar in a bowl.
Add raisins and stir.
Stir in eggs and melted butter.
Add buttermilk.
With wooden spoon mix until well blended.
Divide dough into 3 equal portions.
Lightly grease bread pans.
Bake in preheated oven at 305° for 1 hour.
(If not done after 1 hour, check every 5 minutes.)

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Slightly cook broccoli.
Place on greased casserole dish. Top this with cooked chicken breasts.

title: rocky road ice cream
directions: Beat chocolate, Eagle Brand and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into freezer container.
Freeze.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: beefsteak pizza
directions: Place steak in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour tomatoes and spices over steak.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Top with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts and is light brown.
Makes 6 servings.
Good winter dish.

title: shrimp pasta dish
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add onions.
Saute until onions are translucent.
Add cream and stir.
Add shrimp; stir and add vegetables (optional).
Add pasta and stir.
(Cook pasta as directed on box.)
Enjoy with French or garlic bread.

title: five cup fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for several hours and serve.

title: microwave stuffed acorn squash
directions: Place squash halves cut sides down on cutting board.
Trim 1/4-inch from rounded top of each squash half so that they will stand level when filled.

title: sunshine punch
directions: In a large pitcher or punch bowl, combine all ingredients except sherbet.
Stir until juices are thawed and blended.
Top with scoops of sherbet if desired.
Makes 18 (4-ounce) servings.

title: easy buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix well. Roll out on floured surface. Cut and bake in rectangle pan until brown.

title: barbecued fish
directions: Combine lemon juice and salad oil; pour over fish steaks in shallow pan.
Let stand 30 minutes, turning once or twice.
Broil on grill close to heat for about 3 minutes on each side.
Serve with lemon.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers, in a jar.
Shake to mix well.
Put crackers in container with a lid.
Pour mix over crackers. Shake well to mix.
Let stand at least 2 hours before serving, turning and shaking frequently.
Keeps well in fridge and can be frozen.

title: applesauce bars
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool. Frost with Browned Butter Icing.

title: blueberry pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 12-inch pizza pan on 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, 1 cup oats and 6 tablespoons margarine at low speed until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup crumbs for topping.
To crumbs, blend in egg.
Press in pan and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
To reserved crumbs, add remaining 1/4 cup oats, 2 tablespoons margarine, nuts, sugar and cinnamon. Beat until well mixed.
Spread crust with blueberry filling and sprinkle with crumb mixture.
Return to oven and bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix together first five ingredients.
Pat onto sides and bottom of well-buttered spring-form pan.
Blend cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream and eggs in blender until smooth.
Pour into bowl and mix sugar, flour, margarine, lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix at low speed about 10 minutes.

title: white chocolate cookies
directions: Melt chocolate in oven.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: green dip for vegetables
directions: Mix in blender; chill several hours.
Serve with fresh raw vegetables.

title: corn meal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook over low heat until meal and eggs are done, about 20 minutes.

title: spring spaghetti
directions: Peel tomatoes.
Slice them in half crosswise.
Remove seeds and juice by squeezing.
Chop and drain in colander.

title: cinnamon flop coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add milk and dry ingredients alternately.
Grease and flour 8-inch square pan.
Put in batter and dust top with flour and spread plenty of brown sugar and cinnamon over top.
Punch holes in batter and put lumps of butter in holes.
Bake in moderate oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Put waxed paper over top when out of oven to keep sugar from getting hard.

title: string bean and meatball stew
directions: Season hamburger to taste.
Make bite size meatballs and cook fully in microwave oven.
Cook fully the string beans and potatoes.
In a large stew pot, pour in can of puree and 3/4 can of water.
Season sauce to taste and add sugar.
Add meatballs, string beans and bite size pieces of potatoes.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve with Italian bread.

title: glazed vegetables
directions: Combine ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well.
Pour over vegetables and mix well to coat.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes. Baste occasionally (more vegetable water may be used, if necessary).
Stir well and sprinkle with toasted, slivered or sliced almonds.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water.
Cook to hard ball stage (252°).
Beat egg whites and gelatin until stiff.
Pour hot syrup in thin stream into egg whites.
Beat until candy almost loses gloss.
Fold in nuts and coconut.
Spoon into greased pan or drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: cheese ball
directions: With ingredients at room temperature, mix with a fork.
Shape into a ball. Roll in chopped pecans (optional).
Chill.

title: chocolate bourbon icing
directions: Beat egg and gradually add the sugar.
Melt butter with the chocolate and add lemon juice, vanilla and bourbon.
Mix well with sugar-egg mixture.
Add nuts.
Spread on brownies or cake.

title: italian chicken
directions: Cut chicken in 1-inch cubes and remove fat. Dip chicken into beaten egg and then bread crumbs. Fry in a skillet with margarine until brown. Place chicken into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Spread out evenly.

title: coconut fruitcake cookies
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients. Stir in milk. Fill paper-lined miniature muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pans to waxed paper to cool completely. Let stand for 24 hours in an airtight container at room temperature before serving. Yield: 8 dozen.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Heat soups and taco sauce (do not add any water to the soups) and peppers.
Mix together with meat and onion.
Line bottom of casserole dish with Doritos; layer with meat mixture, then cheese.
Make about 2 layers.
Last layer should be cheese.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Blend together the cake mix, oranges, vegetable oil and eggs. Bake in two 9-inch layer pans according to package directions. When cake is completely cool, frost with the filling and topping mix.
Keep refrigerated.

title: carrot spice cake
directions: Place carrots, sugar, water, raisins, butter and spices in a pan.
Bring
to
a	boil and simmer for 5 minutes.	Cool. Sift flour, baking
powder,
soda
and salt together.
Add the dry ingredients and
nuts
to
the carrot mixture.
Stir until blended.
Pour
into
well-greased
and
floured	ring
mold (9-inch).
Bake at 350°
for 50 minutes.
To fill a Bundt pan, double the recipe.	Frost with Butter Cream Frosting.

title: fresh fruit pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin, sugar and salt in boiling water (first gelatin).
Add yogurt or cream and mix with beater well. Refrigerate until thickened but not set.
Stir in fruit.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: savory meat loaf & vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. In large bowl, mix thoroughly 1/2 c. of soup, beef, bread crumbs, onion, worcestershire, pepper and egg. In 3 quart oblong baking dish, firmly shape meat into 8 X 4 inch loaf pan. Arrange potatoes and carrots around meat loaf. Bake for 45 minutes. Spoon off fat. Meanwhile, in small bowl, combine remaining soup and water. Pour soup mixture over vegetables and meat loaf. Bake 30 minutes more or until vegetables are fork-tender and meat loaf is no longer pink; 160 degree internal temperature. To serve; arrange meat loaf with vegetables on platter. Spoon some sauce over meat loaf. Pass remaining sauce. Garnish with rosemary and mushrooms if desired.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender;
drain well.
Add milk, eggs, oleo and chopped onions.
Cover
top
with
cheese
and sugar. Top with Ritz crackers.
Bake at
350° for 30 minutes.
Use 10 x 13-inch pan.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in large container.
To prepare hot drink:
add 3 tablespoons of mixture to 1 cup of hot water.
Makes great gifts.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Simmer ingredients together for 15 minutes.
Brown chicken in margarine and pour sauce over chicken.
Cover pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: easy crust chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in bottom of large baking dish.
Heat soup and chicken broth, stirring until smooth and pour over chicken.
Mix salt, pepper, flour, baking powder and milk and pour on top.
Top with melted butter.
Leave in layers, do not stir.
Bake 30 minutes at 425°.
Serves 8.

title: tagglirini
directions: Cook garlic and onion in butter until soft.
Add meat and cook until brown.
Add tomato sauce and juice.
When hot, add noodles; stir and cook until noodles lose their crispness.
Add corn, mushrooms and liquid.
Stir and pour into baking dish.
Cover with cheese and dot with olives.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: danish apple cake
directions: Saute bread crumbs until evenly browned in the butter.
Line bottom of deep 9-inch pie pan with browned bread crumbs.
Spread 1/3 of sauce over the crumbs.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Add 2 more layers alternating bread crumbs, applesauce and cinnamon.
End with cinnamon sprinkled crumbs on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Serve hot or cold with whipped cream garnished with bits of jelly. Yields 10 servings.

title: cheese corn
directions: Combine milk, cream cheese, butter, sugar, salt and black pepper in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until cheese melts and is well blended.
Add corn and heat.
Makes 6 servings.

title: champagne punch
directions: Take about a third of the lemonade, dilute with water and freeze it into an ice ring.
Pour rest of lemonade and juice into a punch bowl and add the ice ring.
Carefully pour the sparkling water, ginger ale and champagne down the sides of the bowl.
Stir gently and serve.

title: minestrone soup
directions: In 8-quart Dutch oven on medium heat, add oil, butter, onions, carrots, celery, potatoes and green beans; cook until slightly browned, approximately 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add water, cabbage, tomatoes (with their juices), spinach, zucchini, bouillon cubes and salt.
Bring to boil, stirring to break up tomatoes.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 40 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Do not overcook.
Stir in red and white kidney beans; cook 15 minutes longer or until soup thickens.

title: crab bisque
directions: Whisk soup, milk and water.
Add celery and crabmeat.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: sweet n' sour string beans
directions: Wash beans and break
into
to
inch pieces. Place in 2 quart	casserole
with
cup hot water;
cover. Microwave on High (100%) until beans are tender-crisp, about 9 to 13 minutes.
Let
stand
minutes; drain.
Chop onion and add 3 tablespoons oil.
Microwave
to 5 minutes until onion is transparent.
Add the drained beans and packet Sweet 'N Low with 1/2 cup cider vinegar
and oregano to taste and mix well. Cover and microwave 5 minutes longer.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Skin sausage and brown; drain off any liquid from sausage.
Add spices, tomato sauce, tomato puree, mushrooms and water. Simmer 10 minutes.
Mix with macaroni.
Put half in 9 x 13 pan.
Top with half of the Mozzarella cheese.
Add remaining meat and macaroni.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mom's stollen
directions: Mix first four ingredients as for pie crust and set aside. Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and let stand for 10 minutes.
Mix well beaten egg yolks with warmed milk and add risen yeast. Combine with flour mixture that had previously been set aside.
Put in greased and covered bowl and refrigerate overnight.

title: appetizer pie
directions: Blend cheese and milk.
Stir in dried beef, onion and green pepper; mix well.
Stir in sour cream and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.
Freezes well.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt
peanut butter and butterscotch together.	Stir in nuts and
noodles.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper. Let cool.

title: seven steps to heaven
directions: Melt butter and press with crumbs in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Put the rest of the ingredients in layers as they are listed.
Last, pour the Eagle Brand milk all over the top and bake for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and egg yolks together.
Add this mixture and the butter to the rhubarb; mix thoroughly.
Cook slowly, stirring often until thickened.
Cool and pour into baked pie shell; cover with meringue made with the egg whites and additional sugar and brown in a slow oven.

title: rum-raisin yams
directions: Melt butter over medium heat.
Add sugar and orange juice; simmer.
Add the next 3 spices, cover and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: dorito casserole
directions: Brown meat with onions until onions are tender.
Stir in chilies, soup and milk.
Pour over crumbled Doritos in casserole dish.
Add grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts. Serve warm.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy chicken gumbo
directions: Heat margarine in 3-quart saucepan until melted.
Add okra, onion and green pepper; cook and stir until onion is tender.
Stir in broth, tomatoes (with liquid), bay leaf, salt and pepper.
(We like it spicy, so I add about 1 tablespoon Tony Chachere's Creole seasoning.
Can be found at Food Lion.)
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered 15 minutes.
Stir in chicken and parsley; heat through.
Serve chicken mixture over hot rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: poor man's stroganoff
directions: Chop onion; melt butter in large frying pan and saute chopped onion in butter over medium heat.
Add meat to onion and saute about 5 minutes or until browned.
Put all remaining ingredients, except sour cream, in a blender or food processor in order listed and blend until thoroughly mixed.
Add blended mixture to meat; simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and cook just until heated through.
Serve on hot mashed potatoes, fluffy rice, noodles or toast.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: rosalie's pizza ricotta with spinach
directions: Combine. Pour into oiled deep dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Dot with butter first.

title: andrew innes' shortbread cookies
directions: Beat and cream well.
Roll or pat out onto ungreased cookie sheet/jelly roll pan.
Bake at 300° for 60 minutes, until golden. Cut into bars while still warm.

title: jailhouse special
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in small amount of oil in skillet after salt and pepper.
Put pepper ring on each chop. Fill with 2 tablespoons rice. Top with chopped onion.
Add tomatoes and water. Sprinkle chili powder to taste.
Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: party pickles
directions: Cut pickles into spears. Add sugar and Louisiana Hot sauce to the pickle juice. Place pickles and juice back into gallon jar. Invert jar every 24 hours for 1 week. Drain, chill and serve.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, melted margarine and 1 egg together and press in the bottom of pan.
Then mix coconut and nuts and sprinkle on top of cake mix.
Combine powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs and spread over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: *I've cut the oil down to 1/4 cup.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients into a large bowl.
Beat eggs and oil together.
Sift into flour mixture.
Add apples and nuts; blend well.
Pour into greased 10 x 13-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake 60 to 65 minutes at 325°.

title: pot roast
directions: Brown beef; pour off fat.
Add soup.
Cover; cook over low heat 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until meat is done.
Stir occasionally.
Blend water into flour until smooth; slowly stir into sauce.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.

title: chai blend(a traditional indian blend)
directions: Prepare a strong tea by steeping tea bags in 4 cups boiling water. Steep 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Add cloves, cardamon and ginger and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add half and half or milk and sweeten to taste.
This may also be cooled and served over ice.

title: pickled okra
directions: Pack in hot jar the pepper, garlic, dill seed and okra.
Bring vinegar, water, sugar and salt to a boil and pour over okra.
Fill jar not quite full.
Process 10 minutes in hot water bath to seal. Makes 1 pint jar.

title: fig cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Mix figs, sugar, oil and eggs.
Add the mixtures together and bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 375°.
Put a pan of water on the lower shelf and it will help keep it from getting too brown on the bottom and drying out.

title: marinated beef kabobs
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients; stir well.
Add meat.
Cover; marinate 12 hours in refrigerator, turning meat occasionally. Remove meat from marinade, reserving marinade.
Alternate meat and vegetables on skewers.
Grill over medium coals 15 to 20 minutes, or until desired degree of doneness, basting with marinade.
Serve with rice, if desired.
Yields 12 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Beat milk and cream cheese until smooth.
Add fruit.
Blend thoroughly.
Chill or freeze at least 1 hour before serving. Garnish with cherries or fresh strawberries.

title: rhubarb filled cookies
directions: Cut rhubarb into pieces. Grind whole oranges and raisins. Add sugar and boil down to preserves.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch dish or deep bowl.
Layer lettuce, celery, eggs, peas, green pepper, onion and bacon.

title: key lime pie(quick and easy)
directions: Bake 2 pie crusts.
Soften cream cheese to room temperature. Beat milk and limeade into cream cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip. Chill until stiff.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, then flour sifted with baking powder.
Roll into small balls. Place on cookie sheet.
With a wet fork, flatten in a crisscross design.
Bake at 440° about 10 minutes.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: chicken patties
directions: Combine chicken and eggs.
Mix well.
Pour milk over bread. Mix. Allow to soak 10 minutes.
Add to chicken with onion and seasonings.
Mix well.
Shape into 10 or 12 oval patties.
Cook slowly in nonstick skillet until cooked through and browned.
Serve with Mushroom Sauce.

title: pearl balls
directions: Put egg, sugar, soy sauce and salt in bowl and mix.
Pour over pork already in bowl.
Add mushrooms, 2 green onions, water chestnuts and ginger.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Place uncooked rice on a towel.
Spread out.
Roll pork balls in rice until well coated.
Place balls on a piece of wax paper and put into a steamer.
Steam 30 minutes.
Take out with tongs and put on serving tray.
Serve with duck sauce, soy sauce or even mustard, if preferred.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mulled cider
directions: Mix together in a large saucepan; heat to a boil, then simmer for 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Cream butter, cornstarch and eggs together.
Add milk and pineapple.
Pour into a pastry lined pan.
Bake at 350° until inserted knife comes out clean.
Remove from oven.
Cover with meringue from whites of the eggs.
Brown lightly.

title: baked beans with apples
directions: Heat beans.
Add brown sugar and syrup.
Cook peeled apples and mash.
Add to cooked ingredients.
Serves 5.

title: sourdough bread starter
directions: In a nonstick (not metal) mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water and let stand for 5 minutes.
Stir in starter, vegetable oil, sugar, salt, eggs and 3 cups of flour, continuing to stir in flour until soft dough is reached.
Knead dough on a floured surface until elastic (about 10 minutes).
Form into a ball. Grease another nonstick (not metal) bowl.
Brush top of dough with vegetable oil.

title: mapley microwaved beans
directions: Mix bacon and onion in a 1 1/2-quart microwave casserole. Cover loosely with wax paper.
Microwave on High 5 minutes. Drain.
Stir in beans, syrup, catsup, mustard and pepper sauce. Cover loosely with wax paper.
Microwave 10 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking time.

title: enchilada dinner
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Mix soups, sauces and water together with meat.
Tear up 1 package corn tortillas and add to mixture. Top with chopped onion and grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a bowl mix together eggs, whipping cream and Cheddar cheese soup.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with 1 package of Ritz crackers, crushed.
Pour 1/2 stick melted margarine over crackers.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pine forest country club's famous fudge pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together in top of double boiler over low heat or microwave oven. Meanwhile, place eggs in mixing bowl and beat until light.
Beat in sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add chocolate mixture (slightly cooled) and pecans.
Mix thoroughly and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Top should be crusty and somewhat soft. Serve plain or with whipped cream or ice cream.
Undescribably dee---lish!

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients and pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured cake pan.
Bake in 350° oven until done. While hot, put marshmallow cream on top of cake.
Spread evenly.

title: zesty chicken
directions: Skin chicken and sprinkle onion salt, garlic powder, black pepper and salt.
Brown chicken until done.
Pour Zesty Italian dressing and simmer at low heat for 15 minutes.

title: spoonbread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° in greased pan for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: banana split cake
directions: Put graham crackers and 1 stick of margarine (melted) in a 9 x 13-inch pan and press into place.
Beat powdered sugar, eggs, vanilla and margarine for about 5 minutes.
Spread over crust. Put bananas, then pineapple.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: salad
directions: Mix olive oil, salt, basil, pepper and onion together.
Pour over leaves.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello and pineapple over low heat.
Add buttermilk and chill.
Add Cool Whip and nuts.
Cool until firm.

title: grilled lamb
directions: Mix all ingredients but salt, pepper and olive oil together. Marinate meat for several hours or overnight in marinade.

title: kettle tea
directions: Add sugar to water and milk.
Add biscuit into cup.

title: easy fudge
directions: Dump all ingredients except nuts in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Beat 10 minutes until loss of shine.
Add nuts and drop on waxed paper.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Pour milk into baking dish over butter.
Pour in fruit mix over
other ingredients. Sprinkle top with cinnamon before baking.
Bake at 350 degrees until brown.

title: lamb chunks on skewers laham mishee
directions: Marinate meat in lemon, oil and garlic mashed with salt and allspice.
Cover tightly and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours or overnight.
When ready to cook, place lamb chunks on skewers alternating with onion quarters, pepper squares and cherry tomatoes.
Barbecue, turning several times to cook evenly.

title: treet and applesauce
directions: Slice
Treet;
fry
in vegetable oil until brown; drain oil. Pour in applesauce;
let simmer for about 10 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread everything in layers as ingredients are shown on pizza pie pan.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: citrus sweet potatoes
directions: Place sweet potatoes in a large saucepan and cover with water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 40 to 45 minutes or until tender. Drain and cool. Cut into 1/2-inch slices. Place in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: spiced cider baked ham
directions: Place both ham steaks in a 2-quart utility dish.
Arrange onion over the steaks.
Mix together the cider and sugar; pour over the steaks.
Place cloves in fat along edges of ham, if desired.
Cook in microwave, covered, on Full power for 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn ham over halfway through cooking time.
Remove ham from the juice.

title: hot chicken souffle
directions: Cut 3 slices of trimmed bread.
Place in bottom of greased baking dish.
Combine chicken, vegetables, mayonnaise and seasoning.
Spoon over sliced bread.
Trim remaining bread and arrange on top of mixture.
Cover and chill overnight.
When ready to bake, combine eggs and milk and spoon over mixture.
Cover with mushroom soup spread over top with spoon.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.
Sprinkle cheese on top for the last 15 minutes of baking time.
Serves 6.

title: quick oatmeal-fudge bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix brown sugar, 3/4 cup margarine, eggs and 2 teaspoons vanilla. Stir in oats and baking mix until a uniform consistency.
Heat chocolate chips, milk, 2 tablespoons margarine and the salt in 2-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Stir in nuts and 2 teaspoons vanilla. Press 2/3 of the oatmeal mixture into a greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan with greased hands.
Spread chocolate mixture over oatmeal. Drop remaining oatmeal by tablespoonfuls on top. Bake until light brown, about 30 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine corn, green beans, onion, bell pepper, yellow wax beans and red kidney beans in a large bowl.
Mix the oil, sugar, black pepper, vinegar and salt together and pour over vegetables. Cover and stand in refrigerator; stir once or twice.
This salad will keep for several days if kept refrigerated in covered container.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Beat well and spread over Marshmallow Creme.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Combine biscuit mix, milk and 2 tablespoons mayonnaise.
Stir well.
Spread mixture in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Cook sausage and onion until browned.
Drain.
Layer sausage mixture over biscuit mixture.
Combine egg, cheese, chilies and rest of mayonnaise.
Spread over sausage mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook meat in small amount of oil until crumbly.
Add garlic, onion, celery and salt.
Cook until tender.
Stir in tomato paste, water and seasoning.
Mix well, cover and simmer for 50 minutes. Drain off extra fat.
Arrange alternate layers of noodles, meat sauce and cheeses in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, beginning with very small amount of meat sauce in bottom of pan.
End with layer of Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Let stand out of oven for 5 minutes before cutting.

title: pasta with pesto saucehouston, texas
directions: Place basil, parsley, nuts and garlic in blender or food processor with metal blade and puree.
Blend in cheese and slowly add olive oil until well mixed.
Boil pasta (use a stockpot), drain and toss with Pesto Sauce. Serve hot.
Some people like more Parmesan cheese on top.

title: peanut butter fudge icing
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients on high, stirring occasionally.
Bring to boil and boil until it forms a soft ball.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir until real creamy.
Pour on cake.

title: corn dogs
directions: Wash and dry hot dogs.
Roll in flour; dip in batter.
Deep fry.
Makes about 20.

title: homemade french dressing
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour over lettuce salad.

title: zesty cheese spread
directions: Mix and serve with crackers and pretzel sticks.

title: focaccia (fo ka cho)(pizza bread)
directions: Make sponge with water, yeast and 1/2 cup flour.
Mix for at least 2 minutes.
Add oil, salt and 1 cup flour and beat until well mixed and fairly stiff.
Knead on floured surface until pushes back.
Let rise twice in oiled bowl.
Roll out on oiled surface and place in pan.
Let rise for 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix all, except potato chips.
Pour into well-greased 2-quart baking dish.
Top with potato chips.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes until bubbly hot.

title: hamburger bologna
directions: In large bowl, put hamburger meat.
Sprinkle other ingredients over the top.
If you use onion flakes, soak them in the water for a few minutes.
Mix well.
Shape into rolls the size of Ritz crackers.
Wrap in aluminum foil and refrigerate for at least 24 hours.
Remove from foil; place on pan.
Let set at room temperature while oven heats to 350°.

title: hawaiian sweet bread
directions: In medium saucepan mix milk, water and margarine.
Heat to 120° to 130°.
Combine 3 cups flour, sugar, salt, ginger, vanilla, yeast and potato flakes in large bowl.
Add liquid, pineapple juice and eggs.
Blend to moisten, then beat four minutes.
By hand stir in remaining flour.
Knead 5 to 8 minutes, until smooth and elastic. Place in greased bowl in warm place until double in size (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down.
Divide into three parts and let rise again (about 1 hour).
Bake in three 8 to 9-inch pans at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add egg yolks, flour, salt, juice and rind from lemon.
Add milk and beaten egg whites.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: crispy oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine, gradually add sugars,
beating at medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add egg substitute and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour and next 2 ingredients, stirring well.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats and cereal.
Drop dough by level tablespoonfuls, 2 inches apart, onto cookie sheets coated with cooking spray.

title: french mustard
directions: Into
vinegar, slice the onion and let stand overnight. Pour off vinegar into a saucepan and discard the onion.

title: cajun chicken salad
directions: Combine salad dressing and seasonings.
Mix well. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly. Chill. Add additional salad dressing just before serving, if desired. Serve on rice cakes, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: watercress quiche
directions: Saute watercress in butter.
Mix with all other ingredients. Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: holiday delight fruitcake
directions: *Use 2 cups of flour to dredge fruit and nuts.

title: onion biscuits
directions: Melt butter in a 10-inch covered frying pan.
Add onion soup. Add refrigerator biscuits, cut into quarters.
Place lid on pan, cook on burner set at 275° to 300°.
Turn once during cooking. When browned, set burner at low temperature for keeping warm. Yields 40 pieces.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly and add sugar, Karo, pecans, vanilla and salt.
Mix well and pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake in slow oven about 1 hour (I use 325° and bake about 1 hour and 5 minutes).
Cool on wire rack.

title: peach cobbler 3
directions: Melt butter.
Pour peaches into empty dish.
Pour 1 box of cake mix on top of peaches.
Evenly drizzle butter over dry cake mix.
Bake at 400 degrees until cake mix is browned.
May substitute cherry, blueberry, pear, or blackberry.

title: mexican casserole
directions: In skillet, cook onion and pepper in butter.
Stir in chili and corn and bring to a boil.
Add cheese; stir to melt.
Put into greased 11 x 7 -inch baking pan.
Prepare muffin mix according to package.
Spoon dough in diagonal bands across top of casserole. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Put all other ingredients in mixing bowl and mix at medium speed for 10 minutes.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: beer dip
directions: Hollow out loaf of pumpernickel or rye bread; put mixture in center for dipping rye bread cubes.

title: baked pheasant
directions: Rub each pheasant with salt and pepper and place in baking dish.
Place 2 slices bacon over breast of each pheasant.
Add celery, onion, parsley, mushrooms and hot water.
Cover and bake in moderate gas oven (350°) for 1 1/2 hours or until tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: all berry ice
directions: Puree berries in a blender or food processor with orange juice and sugar.
Pour into a metal bowl; freeze until mushy.
Return to blender or food processor.
Add egg white; process again until light and completely smooth.
Pour into a covered mold or container; freeze until firm, at least 4 hours.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving to soften slightly.
Garnish with fresh mint leaves.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need a flower pot.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar, Karo and salt together in microwavable bowl.
Cover loosely with Saran Wrap.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir; cook 3 to 4 more minutes; add butter and vanilla. Stir; cook 1 minute.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Add soda; stir until mixture stops foaming.
Pour on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Let cool.
Break apart and store.

title: homemade french dressing
directions: See Cheese Dip recipe for use, too.

title: grilled walleye
directions: Make a mixture of Italian dressing and soy sauce using as much of each to taste as needed for amount of fish you have.
Fashion a "cookie sheet" out of heavy-duty foil and put on the grill grate.

title: phyllis vary's enchilada casserole
directions: You will also need a casserole pan about 2 inches deep.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onion in 1 stick butter.
Combine all ingredients and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: meat loaf pinwheel
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, half of process cheese spread, egg and salt.
Pat out meat mixture to cover 12 x 10-inch rectangle of foil.
Combine remaining cheese, rice and parsley; spread over meat.
Roll up, starting at narrow end.
Wrap securely. Refrigerate several hours or overnight (overnight is best).
Cut roll into eight even slices; place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve lemon jello, orange jello and boiling water.
Add cold water, bananas and crushed pineapple.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover top with miniature marshmallows.
Let congeal in refrigerator.

title: instant mocha mix
directions: Mix all.
Put into airtight container.
Mix 2 to 3 teaspoons in cup of hot water.

title: salisbury steak
directions: In bowl, combine first 4 ingredients and 2 tablespoons onions. Shape into 4 oval patties.
In skillet, cook patties until brown. Spoon off fat; add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Brown onion and garlic in olive oil. Add tomatoes, tomato puree and tomato paste. Add water to thin sauce, if desired. Add spices and baking soda. Simmer for a few hours. Serve over pasta or chicken Parmesan. Add meat or meatballs to sauce.

title: mandarin orange pie
directions: Mix lemon juice with the can of Eagle Brand milk.
When thick, add Mandarin oranges, well drained.
Whip cream and powdered sugar; spread over the filling.
Sprinkle lightly with wafer crumbs and chill.
Line pie pan with vanilla wafers.

title: taco shells(soft)
directions: Mix well.
Cook on medium or medium-hot heat on stove burner. Use an iron skillet.
Use no oil or grease on pan.
Ladle mix onto pan and smooth down into thin, flat pancake shape, 8 or 9-inches in diameter.
Flip once.
Throw first shell away, as it will be the one to clean out the surface of the pan.

title: flo's garlic cheese rolls
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Coat with paprika on wax paper.
Roll on wax paper.
Makes at least 8 long rolls.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: sausage bread(pan bread)
directions: Cook and drain sausage; add spinach and mix.
Roll out bread. Spread sausage and spinach mix over bread, leaving 1 to 2-inch border on all sides.
Spread cheeses, mushrooms and olives over sausage and spinach mix.
Pinch sides of loaf to seal.
Place on cookie sheet, seam side down; brush with oleo.
Bake at 400° for approximately 20 to 25 minutes.
Have a salad to go with this. Serves 4.
This is a "Must".
Enjoy.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order given. Bake in greased loaf tin.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: corn bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans and corn, pour into greased casserole dish. Mix soup, sour cream, cheese, onion and salt; spread over vegetables.
Mix melted butter with crushed crackers and almonds; spread over top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole 4
directions: Cook squash and onion
6 minutes on High in microwave.
Mix sour cream, dressing mix and bacon bits.
Add to squash and onion. Add egg mixture.
Top with cheese and then stuffing mix.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: milky way cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Mix the flour and cocoa.
Add alternately with the milk and syrup.
Add the vanilla; beat thoroughly.

title: marzetti
directions: Brown meat and onion together; cook noodles as directed on package.
Put meat, onions and rest of ingredients except cheese in with noodles and let simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Put 1/2 of this mixture into roaster and dice half of cheese on top.
Add rest of mixture and dice rest of cheese.
Bake at 325° covered for 2 hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and set aside.
Dissolve shortening, sugar and salt in boiling water.
Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Add the two mixtures alternately to flour; mix well. Let rise in warm place until double in bulk.* Roll out on lightly floured pastry sheet about 1/2 to 1/4 inch thick.
Cut in various shapes.
Dip each piece in melted margarine (takes 3 sticks margarine).
Place in layers in 2 greased tube pans.
Let rise again until double in bulk.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Let cool about 10 minutes in pan before removing.
Do not cut to serve; serve whole and pull apart servings by hand.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a loaf or square pan (9 x 9-inch).
Bake at 325° until done.

title: boyfriend fudge
directions: Put all ingredients, except butter and vanilla, in a 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Continue to cook and stir only a few times until mixture reaches soft ball stage on candy thermometer.
(Maybe just a little longer.) Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat until it thickens and loses its shiny look.
Add nuts.
Pour into a buttered 9-inch square pan to set.

title: salsa
directions: Process together in food processor; cover and chill at least 1 hour.

title: mexican chef's salad
directions: Place onion, tomatoes and lettuce in large salad bowl. Toss in cheese. Toss again with dressing and Tabasco. Remove 10 to 12 whole Doritos chips from bag and crush remaining chips into small pieces. Add crushed chips to salad. Reserve a few slices of avocado and add remaining slices to salad. Brown meat; drain off grease and toss with beans, salt, corn and chili powder. Simmer 10 minutes then add to salad and toss. Decorate top of salad with whole Doritos chips and avocado slices. Serve immediately. Serves 6 as a
main dish or 12 as a salad course.

title: chocolate peanut butter mickey mouse cookies
directions: Combine flour and baking soda in a small bowl.
Beat butter, peanut butter, sugars and vanilla in a large mixer bowl until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Beat in flour mixture.
Stir in 1 cup of morsels and oats.
Freeze until slightly firm, but not hard.

title: megan's favorite jello
directions: In a large bowl, combine jello and hot water. Add the pineapple and cherry pie filling. Pour into an 8 x 10-inch glass dish. Chill until set. Soften the cream cheese and mix well with the sugar. Blend in the sour cream and vanilla. Spread over the jello mixture. Sprinkle with nuts.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all, except cornbread mix, in bowl.
Add cornbread mix (or make your own cornbread) to mixture.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and heat in oven.
Bake (using metal pan) 30 minutes at 400°.
Or bake (using glass pan) 25 minutes at 400°.
Great as brunch muffins.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Let stand until cold; roll in balls and then in sugar and bake.
They should crack on top when baked (or you can roll them out and cut out with a cutter).

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix first four ingredients together, then add juice, oil, egg and vanilla.
Fold in cranberries.
Grease the loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: molded mandarin cranberry salad
directions: In a saucepan, mix gelatin, sugar and salt.
Drain oranges. Stir syrup into gelatin mixture.
Place over low heat.
Stir constantly until gelatin and sugar are dissolved, then remove from heat.
Add lemon juice, cranberry sauce, diced celery and chopped nuts.
Arrange orange sections in mold.
Pour mixture over. Refrigerate until firm.
Serve plain or top with mayonnaise thinned with fruit juice.

title: chopped broccoli - cooked
directions: Layer of broccoli, layer of Pepperidge mix, layer of Parmesan cheese and layer of soup.
Bake in oven at 300° for 1 hour or 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: easy chicken gravy
directions: Brown onions. Mix all ingredients, except sour cream.
Heat; add sour cream last.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Cook roast at least 8 hours in crock-pot on low heat until tender.
Discard liquid, fat and bone.
Shred meat; return to crock-pot and add sugar and chili sauce.
Stir well.
Reheat on low 2 to 3 hours, or until ready to serve.
Makes approximately 24 sandwiches.

title: snickers bar cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In a food processor, combine crumbs and butter and process until well blended. Press into bottom and about 1-inch up sides of a 9 1/2 or 10-inch spring-form pan. In a large bowl, beat together cream cheese and sugar with an electric mixer on medium speed until smooth, 1 to 2 minutes. Beat in eggs, 1 at a time. Beat in vanilla and heavy cream; beat 3 to 4 minutes. Fold in 1 1/2 cups cut up Snickers pieces. Turn into crumb-lined pan. Bake 1 hour and 15 to 25 minutes or until cheesecake is almost set but center still jiggles slightly. Let cool to room temperature. Sprinkle remaining candy pieces over top of cheesecake. Refrigerate at least 4 to 5 hours before serving. Run a knife around edge of pan to loosen cake and remove spring-form side of pan. Drizzle warm topping over cake. Serves 12 to 14. Can do ahead.

title: date-pecan coffee cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir alternately with sour cream into sugar mixture.
Stir in dates.

title: big boy strawberry pie
directions: Cook until clear the sugar, cornstarch and water.
Add the jello and food color.
Set aside to cool.
Mix together flour, margarine and cold water.
Pat into pie pan; prick with fork. Bake at 350° until brown; cool.
Arrange strawberries in bottom of cooled crust.
Drizzle jello mixture over berries and refrigerate. Serve with whipped cream on top.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions, drain well.
Dice 3/4 stick butter and add Velveeta.
Spread on top of broccoli.
Crush Ritz crackers and brown in 1/4 stick oleo.
Sprinkle on top of cheese and oleo.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Double for large casserole.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, milk, eggs and chocolate chips in a large bowl.
Mix by hand until well blended (about 2 minutes). Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan or tube pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed.
Do not overbake.
Cool 15 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan and continue cooling on rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or drizzle with chocolate glaze, if desired.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and shape into balls.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix first four ingredients. Mix the next two ingredients and pour over potato mixture.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Heat all ingredients except first 2.
Pour sauce mixture over cabbage and onions.
Let stand in refrigerator until cool.
May be stored in refrigerator 2 to 3 days.

title: nanny's dark secrets
directions: Mix sugar with eggs.
Add butter; mix well.
Add dates and nuts.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add to egg mixture.
Mix well; pour into greased and floured pan (7 x 11 x 1 1/2-inch).
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 to 35 minutes. When cool, cut into 1-inch squares.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together everything except soup and cheese.
Put in refrigerator overnight in 9 x 12-inch dish.
Add soup in a.m. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Add cheese last few minutes.

title: the best chicken casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender (not brown).
Add noodles, broth, lemon peel, Accent and salt and bring to a boil.
Cover and cook over low heat until noodles are done.
Stir in sherry, sour cream and chicken and heat through.
Sprinkle with almonds and parsley.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: salsa burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Form mixture into 6 to 8 patties; layer patties in aluminum foil and refrigerate to firm them up. Broil, grill or bake to desired doneness.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Mix together cream cheese, chives and onion.
Spread on ham slice and roll tightly.
When done, refrigerate ham roll-ups for at least 1 hour.
Slice into 1/2-inch slices.
Put on plate and serve as is or with crackers.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix well and put 1/4 cup into coffee mug and fill with boiling water. Add marshmallow or whipped cream, if desired. Good for Christmas gifts.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Place flour in large glass bowl.
Make a well.
Pour in yeast and water.
Gradually stir flour into water.
When well mixed, beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Cover lightly.
Place in draft free area.
Ready to use after 24 hours. Makes 4 cups.

title: tangy pork chops and vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sprinkle trimmed chops with salt and pepper.
Brush chops all over with 2 tablespoons salad dressing. Combine cabbage and carrot in 2-quart casserole.
Drizzle remaining dressing over top.
Toss together.
Spread mixture evenly in bottom of dish.
Arrange chops on top.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until chops and vegetables are tender.

title: cold tomato soup
directions: Put tomatoes in a blender; blend to make 2 cups.
Add soup and blend.
Add cream, salt and pepper; blend.
Serve in iced bowls with dollops of sour cream.
This will keep well in the refrigerator for 4 or 5 days.
Serves 6.

title: beef and kraut casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
In large skillet, saute ground beef, onion, salt and pepper.
Drain excess fat.
Stir in sauerkraut, soup, caraway seed and pimento.
Gently fold in noodles and pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Heat the griddle at medium, making sure it is hot enough by splashing a drop of water.
If it sizzles fast, that means it is hot enough.
Mix the flour, milk, egg, salt, oil, sugar and baking powder together.
Pour in 4 circles on griddle; flip when they have bubbles.
You can put chocolate chips on them, if you want, before flipping.

title: pork chops
directions: Fry pork chops.
Put in a baking pan.
Mix soup with water. Put broccoli over pork chops.
Pour soup over them.
Bake 30 minutes.
The last 10 minutes, sprinkle Cheddar cheese over it.

title: texas pecan candy cake(fruit cake)
directions: Preheat oven to slow (250°).
Grease and flour tube pan with removable bottom.
Set pan aside.

title: sauteed chicken breasts
directions: Heat vegetable oil and butter in heavy skillet.
Saute chicken breasts over medium-high heat for 5 to 10 minutes each side. Transfer to plate and keep warm.
Add green onions to pan and cook gently for 1 minute.
Stir in 2 tablespoons vinegar, then quickly stir in 1/2 cup cream.
Boil gently for 1 minute.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon over warm chicken breasts and serve.

title: frozen slaw
directions: Chop and mix together the vegetables.
Make a dressing of the sugar, vinegar, water, salt and celery salt.
Bring dressing to a boil for 1 minute.
Let cool.
Mix dressing with cabbage mixture. Pour into containers and freeze.
Allow to thaw slightly before serving.

title: turkey a la king
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, flour and seasonings in medium saucepan. Gradually stir in milk, onions and pimientos. Cook, stirring occasionally, over medium heat for 5 minutes or until thickened. Reduce heat to low. Stir in turkey, peas and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes. Serve over rice, toast or biscuits.

title: lemon loaf
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add sifted dry ingredients in thirds alternately with milk, beating until smooth after each addition.
Fold in lemon rind.
Turn into a greased, foil-lined 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peppy parmesan pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package instructions.
Meanwhile, in a serving bowl, combine the tomato, pepperoni, cheese, olives, oil, salt and garlic powder.
Drain pasta; add to the tomato mixture.
Toss to coat.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Soften cheese; blend in milk, dried beef, green pepper, onion flakes, garlic salt and sour cream.
Place in 8-inch pie plate. Sprinkle chopped pecans over cheese mixture.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve on little crackers.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix together.
Marinate for 5 to 6 hours.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and carrots in salt water for 5 minutes, then drain.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrots, squash, onion and salt to taste.
Combine stuffing and butter.

title: lucy's pot roast
directions: Line roast pan with foil.
Place roast in foiled pan.
Spread cream of mushroom soup on the roast, then sprinkle dry onion soup on the roast.
Add 1 cup of water to bottom of the pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours.

title: spinach roll-ups
directions: Combine ingredients and spread mixture evenly over tortillas. Roll up and refrigerate in plastic wrap until ready to use. Slice and serve.

title: mindy's mom's broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli by directions on the package.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Mix all ingredients together and put into casserole dish and top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix sunflower seeds, broccoli, green onions and raisins.
Then mix mayo, sugar and vinegar.
Combine and add Bac*Os.

title: apple pie
directions: Put apple pie filling in bottom of loaf pan.
Then put half of cake mix on second layer.
Spread butter on cake mix.
Make sure all the butter covers the cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until it browns.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Pare and slice eggplant and onion and slice the pepper.
Brown in frying pan with vegetable fat.
Place the brown vegetables in a greased casserole, alternating with the tomatoes (sliced).
Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Bake in a 400° oven for 40 minutes.

title: lemony oven spareribs
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Arrange ribs in 13 1/2 x 3/4-inch baking dish.
Roast ribs for 30 minutes; drain.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
In a 1-quart saucepan, stir together ketchup, chili sauce, sugar, mustard and seasonings.
Cover; simmer over low heat for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour half ketchup mixture over ribs.
Layer with half onion and lemon slices.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining sauce, onions and lemons. Cover with foil.
Continue baking 30 minutes.
Garnish with celery leaves, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients and bake at 350° for 40 minutes in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: christmas rainbow poke cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour batter into 2 (8 or 9-inch) cake pans.
Bake as directed; cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely.
Place cake layers top side up back in the clean pans.
Prick each layer with fork at 1/2-inch intervals. Pour 1 cup boiling water over raspberry Jell-O in a bowl and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Spoon over one layer.
Repeat with lime Jell-O on second layer.
Refrigerate up to 4 hours.
Dip 1 layer in pan into warm water 10 seconds, invert on plate gently shaking to loosen.
Remove pan; spread one layer with 1 cup whipped topping.
Repeat process for second layer inverting on top of first layer.
Remove pan; frost with remaining topping.
Refrigerate. Garnish with flattened gumdrops cut to resemble holly.

title: great grandma's recipe for stew
directions: In large skillet, heat oil and brown beef.
Add tomatoes, carrots, onion, salt, pepper and garlic.
Simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, 1 1/2 hours or until beef is tender.
Stir in flour blended with water.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: fried pizzas
directions: You will need a deep fryer.

title: billy's burgers
directions: Pat out burgers and sprinkle skillet with salt.
Place burgers in hot skillet.
Cover with chili powder and a generous amount of hot sauce.
Sprinkle lightly with soy sauce and fry.

title: chicken jambalaya
directions: Melt shortening or
oil in a large thick pot; place on medium hot burner and add deboned chicken.
Cook until meat has lost all pink color.
Add sausage and cook until hot.
Add onions, pepper, salt and black pepper.
Reduce heat to medium low and cover pot. Cook until very dark, stirring and scraping bottom of pot often. Add Worcestershire sauce and stir around.
Pour in the water and bring to a boil.
Add rice and bring back to a boil.
Reduce heat to a simmer until moisture is absorbed by rice.
Let stand for 18 minutes in pot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sprite eggnog
directions: Combine eggnog and softened ice cream in punch bowl. Slowly add chilled Sprite. Dust lightly with nutmeg. Serves approx. 40 people.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix white sugar, brown sugar, salt and meal together. Add all the spices equally, except ginger (add less of it) to the mixture. When the mixture is a light to medium brown color, you will know you have the right amount of spices. Add all the rest of the ingredients to it and put it on the stove. Cook and stir constantly until it starts bubbling real big, then pour it into an unbaked pie shell. Put in a preheated oven at 325°. Cook for 45 minutes or until done.

title: alabama pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients into mixing bowl.
Beat 12 minutes.
Pour into a greased pan.
Put into a cold oven and bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: dewberry or strawberry pie filling
directions: Mix all
together
and
pour over berries in an unbaked pie shell.
For 9-inch pie shell, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch cake pan, greased, at 350° for 40 minutes (20 minutes for cookie sheet).

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream sugar with oleo.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Mix.
Add flour until just crumbly mixed.
Press into unbuttered 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° until slightly browned, about 15 minutes or so. Frost with chocolate powdered sugar frosting and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: easiest pasta con broccoli
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in baking dish in oven. Remove.
Stir in garlic, creamer, soup, 1/2 of Parmesan cheese and seasonings.
Stir to combine.
Gently stir in broccoli and pasta. Sprinkle remaining Parmesan cheese over top.
Bake 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: grape dessert
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sour cream and Cool Whip.
Mix in powdered sugar and lemon juice.
Last, add the well drained and washed grapes.

title: chocolate cinnamon cake
directions: Then add to mixing bowl and mix well.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Frost with chocolate butter frosting.
Place pecan halves on top.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender and blend for 1 full minute. Pour into 10-inch greased pie tin.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Makes its own crust.

title: french dip roast
directions: Put roast in crock-pot and pour sauce with seasonings over it. Add enough water to come within 1-inch of the top of the roast. Cook on high all day.
Eat with hard rolls and use sauce for dipping sandwich.

title: tipsy chicken
directions: Split chicken breasts lengthwise and pound thin between two sheets of waxed paper.
On another sheet of waxed paper, combine flour, dried mint, salt and pepper.
Lightly dredge the pounded chicken breasts in mixture. Shake off excess flour.

title: cajun stew
directions: Cut chicken breasts into quarters; heat oil in frying pan and brown chicken well.
Add onion, green pepper, garlic, chili powder and cumin.
Saute 2 minutes until onion is soft; stir in rice, water and salt and bring to boiling.
Transfer to stew pot, cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in shrimp and tomatoes. Return to simmering, cover and cook 15 minutes.
Add crab and okra and cook 5 minutes longer.
Stir in chopped parsley just before serving.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on package.
Pour 1/2 of batter in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
While cake is baking, melt together milk, caramels and butter.
Cool and pour over first 1/2 of cake then sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour remaining batter over top and bake additional 20 to 25 minutes.

title: potato yeast bread
directions: Combine eggs, potatoes, Crisco, sugar, salt and yeast and mix well.
Add warm milk and flour to make soft dough.
Alternate flour and milk until dough is soft and elastic.
Allow to rise.
Work down.
Make into cloverleaf rolls.
Bake after second rise at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: refrigerated yeast rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over margarine, sugar and salt.
Blend and cool.
Add egg.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and add to first mixture.
Add flour and blend well.
Cover and place in refrigerator for 4 hours or overnight.
Keeps 7 - 10 days in refrigerator.
About 2 hours before using roll into desired shapes, tea rolls, cinnamon rolls, etc.
Place in greased pans and allow to rise until double.
To make cinnamon rolls, flatten to rectangle about 10x13 inch.
Spread with 1/2 cup margarine or butter.
Top with cinnamon and sugar in desired amount.
Bake at 375 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Pour 3/4 cup of butter or margarine in a bowl.
Pour 1 cup of sugar on it.
Put 2 eggs in it and stir, then you put 1 teaspoon vanilla and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Stir again.
After that, put it in your icebox for 1 hour, then cook them at 375°.

title: "banana granola cookies"
directions: Grease 2 cookie sheets.
In a large bowl, cream the butter and sugar with an electric mixer at medium speed.
Add the egg, vanilla and bananas, beating until well blended.
Add the flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt and mix until blended.
Stir in the granola.
Drop by the tablespoon onto the prepared cookie sheets, spacing about 2 inches apart.
Bake in a 375° oven for 12 minutes. Cool on a wire rack.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper; drain. In deep casserole, add 1/2 cup rice and tomatoes. Add beef mixture; stir together. Add 2 teaspoons chili powder, salt and pepper. Bake in covered casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: steak and peppers
directions: Preheat broiler.
Saute sliced peppers in hot oil.
Add jar of Ragu; simmer gently for 10 minutes.
Broil a 2 pound steak for 4 minutes on each side.

title: colorful cole slaw
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar and milk.
Pour over other mixed ingredients.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: relish type salad
directions: Boil vinegar, oil and sugar.
Heat until sugar is dissolved well.
Add salt and pepper.
Let cool; pour over vegetables. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Keeps real well in covered jar.
Cutting the vegetables real fine will make a more attractive dish.

title: weight watchers cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
In small bowl, mix egg, oil, water and flavoring, beat with fork.
Combine everything, mix well. Spray mini-loaf pan with "Pam."
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: garlic cheese grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in boiling water according to package directions. When cooled, add remaining ingredients. Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 275° about 1 hour. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, peanut butter, vanilla and corn syrup.
Beat well.
Add oats, soda and salt, stirring well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: roast duck
directions: Rub ducks with garlic, salt and pepper.
Place breast side down in roaster.
Combine other ingredients except paprika; pour over ducks.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.
When ducks are tender, turn breast side up and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake until golden brown.
Can be served with gravy.
Add small amount of flour to drippings and cook until thickened, gradually add water to your desire.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine crushed graham crackers with sugar and butter in 9-inch pie plate.
Put into refrigerator for 45 minutes.
Soften 1 quart vanilla ice cream.
Fold in the peanut butter and Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust and freeze about 4 to 5 hours.

title: best cheese cake you ever ate
directions: Prepare crust and put in refrigerator while you prepare filling.

title: jimmy's caramel corn
directions: Combine sugar, butter and Karo; boil slowly a few minutes. Add milk; cook to 238°.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over popped corn.
Mix and serve.

title: bar cheese
directions: Combine cheeses and garlic.
Then add remaining ingredients except beer.
Mix with wooden spoon adding beer, little at a time, to make a smooth paste.
Store in covered crock in refrigerator.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs, sugar, salt, butter and syrup.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until filling is set.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix together and add one bottle of Western dressing.

title: venison chili
directions: Salt and pepper meat.
Brown meat, onions and green pepper in small amount of oil in a large skillet; drain.
In a large saucepan, pour in red kidney beans, chili mix, tomato sauce and 4 cans of water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer.

title: oriental salad
directions: Mix together salad ingredients.

title: bits 'o brickle cookies
directions: Mix in order, adding brickle last, until creamy.
Roll into small balls and cook at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes a lot!

title: glorified cheese cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat. Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in cheese and red pepper sauce.
Cook and stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Pour sauce over hot cauliflower.

title: butterfinger torte
directions: Cream together.
Add 2 cups Cool Whip.
Mix with angel food cake and put in pan.
Top with 4 or 6 Butterfinger candy bars, crushed.

title: round steak parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Pound steak and cut into serving pieces, dip into egg and roll in mixture of bread crumbs and parmesan cheese.
In a large skillet brown meat in vegetable oil. Remove meat
and place in baking dish; saute onion in skillet drippings. Stir in sugar, salt, pepper, tomato paste and water; boil for 5 minutes.
Pour 2/3 of the sauce over steak; cover with mozzarella cheese.
Cover with remaining sauce.
Cover baking dish with foil; bake for 1 hour or until meat is tender.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw the hash brown potatoes and blend in sour cream, cheese, onion, soup and melted margarine.
Crush the roll of Ritz crackers and blend with 1/2 stick of melted margarine.
Put on top of casserole and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: fresh fruit cream pie
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold whipped topping, blending thoroughly.
Gently add fruit, folding carefully so as not to mash.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, about 4 hours.

title: perfect divinity
directions: In large saucepan, dissolve sugar and syrup in water.
Without stirring cook to a firm ball stage (240 degrees on candy thermometer).
Remove pan from heat.
In a separate bowl, stiffly beat egg whites.
Add sugar, syrup and vanilla.
Continue beating until mixture will hold shape when dropped from a spoon.
Stir in pecans.
Drop mix by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Makes about 50.

title: ice creamy chocolate pie
directions: For crust:
Mix together butter, flour and pecans.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until light brown.
Cool.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Combine caramels and 1/3 cup canned milk and melt.
Mix cake mix, 1/3 cup milk and butter.
Put half cake mix into cake pan and bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven; add chocolate chips and cover with melted caramel.
Add remaining cake mix and bake 15 to 18 minutes.

title: pinwheels in the micro
directions: Spray an 8 or 9-inch square pan with nonstick cooking spray (2 to 3 short sprays).
Spread on bottom and sides of pan with paper towel.
Mix Jell-O and water in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart microwavable bowl.
Microwave on High for approximately 1 1/2 minutes, stirring to dissolve completely.
Add marshmallows; microwave about 1 minute, or until marshmallows are puffed and almost melted.
Stir mixture slowly until marshmallows are completely melted and mixture is smooth (creamy layer will float to top).
Pour into prepared pan; refrigerate 45 minutes, or until set.
Loosen edges with knife for easy rolling.
Starting at one edge, roll up tightly.
With seam side down, cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Use sharp knife dipped in hot water for easier cutting.
Serve immediately, or refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 10 to 12 pieces.

title: alsatian kraut
directions: *If no bacon, can use bacon bits.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Reserve one cup cake mix for topping.
Mix rest of cake mix, margarine and egg into a paste and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well; pour into Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine shortening, butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Put in other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: oatmeal cookies(no bake)
directions: Mix milk and sugar. Stir in cocoa and oleo. Boil for 2 minutes.
Add oatmeal and vanilla.
Put on cookie sheet.

title: delicious brownies
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add 4 eggs, one at a time, Hershey's syrup, flour, salt, vanilla and chopped walnuts. Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Saute the ground beef and onion until meat is browned.
Add pizza sauce and salt and pepper to taste.
Cool, then add cheese. Spread on halves of hamburger buns or English muffins.
Cook under broiler until cheese is bubbly and edges of buns are toasted.

title: ice cream sandwich cake
directions: Line lasagna dish with
ice
cream
sandwiches
(cut to fit). Pour over ice
cream
sandwiches 1/3 cup Kahlua.
Cover with 3/4 large container Cool
Whip.
Pour 1/3 cup Kahlua over that, then more Cool Whip.
Shave chocolate and nuts over top. Cover with aluminum foil and
freeze
at
least
8 to 12 hours before serving.

title: never fail chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in one bowl.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 1 layer.

title: pork chops and rice casserole
directions: Place rice in bottom of baking dish. Add consomme, soup, seasoning and onion.
Place chops on top of mixture. Top each chop with a slice of bell pepper.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour, covered.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, egg and milk.
Then add dry ingredients.
Batter may look lumpy.
Add berries.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 muffins.

title: peanut brittle protein shake
directions: Add all ingredients to blender; whip and serve.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Layer country ham slices in
roaster pan or 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover ham with 1/2 of
a 2 liter bottle of Pepsi Cola. Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake
1 hour at 350°.
Cover ham again with Pepsi Cola.
Cover
with
foil and bake another hour at 350°.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Cream butter, then add sugar gradually. Beat in eggs, pumpkin and vanilla, mixing to combine. Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and spices. Blend in with pumpkin mixture. Add nuts and raisins. Pour into well-greased and floured loaf pans. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until center springs back. Let cool before serving.
