title: chicken adobo
directions: Cut up chicken, wash it
and put in pot with lid.
Add all ingredients and boil (medium heat) for 1 hour with lid on.

title: "slushes"
directions: Boil the water and sugar. Mix the remaining ingredients with the water and sugar. Place in Tupperware container and freeze. Place scooper full in glass and add Squirt. Yum!

title: chocolate candy
directions: Cook to soft ball stage.
Cool.
Beat until thick.
Pour in buttered pan.

title: bigos mysliwski hunter's stew
directions: Soak the mushrooms in the water for 2 hours, then bring to boil and simmer for 30 minutes.
Save the liquid; chop the mushrooms.
Set aside.
Wash the sauerkraut and squeeze gently; add mushrooms with the liquid and add the apples, tomatoes and spices.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Add the meat and the bacon; simmer again for 1 hour longer.
It is best when prepared a day ahead of serving.

title: fruit and chicken
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: creamed corn
directions: In heavy skillet heat margarine; add flour and stir until slightly brown.
Add corn and stir well; add milk, salt and sugar. Boil about 10 minutes.

title: ravioli casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons oil.
Cook spinach per directions.
Drain and reserve liquid.
Add water to make 1 cup liquid.
Combine spinach liquid, spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce, tomato paste and salt.
Then stir into meat mixture. Combine spinach, macaroni, cheese, bread crumbs, eggs and 1/4 cup salad oil.
Spread spinach mixture in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Saute ground beef and onion, until beef loses red color.
Add chicken gumbo soup, mustard and ketchup.
Salt to taste.
Simmer for a few minutes until done.

title: nana's baked clams
directions: Wash clams in cold water.
Remove clams from shell and save the juice.
Chop clams.
Combine clams and juice with ingredients (except the arrowroot) in a saucepan. Bring to a boil, lower flame and simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add arrowroot. Spoon clam stuffing into empty shells.
Place under broiler (500°) until golden brown (3 to 5 minutes).
Sprinkle paprika on clams.

title: broiled mushroom almond salmon steak
directions: Place Market Day salmon steak on a lightly oiled pan; squeeze on lemon juice.
Broil 4 to 5 inches from heat, allowing 8 minutes cooking time per inch of thickness or until salmon steak flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Turn salmon steak over halfway through cooking time.
Meanwhile, in a bowl combine butter and lemon peel; stir in mushrooms, parsley and almonds.
Spread mixture evenly over salmon.
Broil 1 to 2 minutes longer.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Combine butter, margarine, shortening and sugar; cream until light.
Add eggs one at one time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and food coloring.
Combine flour and salt;
Add to creamed sugar alternately with milk;
beat well. Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: polish christmas cookies
directions: Cream together eggs, sugar, butter and lard.
Add anise and cream.
In separate bowl, add flour and baking powder.
Slowly add cream mixture.
Slowly add milk.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: happy day cake
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Stir shortening in.
Add 3/4 cup of milk and mix until flour is dampened.
Add eggs, vanilla and rest of milk.
Bake at 375°.
May put in layers or stem pan.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: curried seafood pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir together oil, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder, salt and garlic.
Add shrimp, macaroni, tuna, celery, parsley and olives to mayonnaise mixture.
Toss gently and coat, being careful not to tear macaroni.
Cover and chill.

title: strawberry soup
directions: Blend strawberries until smooth.
Add sugar and sour cream; blend 30 seconds.
Add ice water; blend and enjoy.

title: tuna cutlets
directions: Separate tuna into flakes.
Put oil in saucepan.
Add flour and blend.
Add milk and cook until very thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add tuna and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Form mixture into cutlets or patties. Refrigerate about 2 hours.
Dip cutlets into slightly beaten egg and roll in cracker crumbs.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown. Garnish with halved cherry tomatoes or tomato slices and lemon wedges.
Serve with fish sauce, if desired.

title: cream puff shells(sfogliata di crema)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put butter and water in saucepan and heat slowly
until
butter melts.
Bring to a boil on high heat. Sift flour
and
salt together; drop into boiling water mixture. Beat vigorously
until the paste is smooth and forms a ball of dough.
Remove from heat and allow to cool slightly. Add the eggs a
little
at
a
time,
beating
well
to give a smooth, shiny mixture.
Drop
by
teaspoonfuls
onto
greased baking sheet. Cook
in
oven
for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove when golden and puffed; split and remove doughy center and return
to the
oven
for
5 minutes to dry.
When cool, fill
with
whipped cream,
chocolate
cream or Ricotta cream.
(See
recipes.) Sprinkle
with powdered sugar.
Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: fig conserve
directions: Cook figs
and sugar over low heat until thick (about 1 hour). Add orange juice, raisins and pecans.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: low-fat rascranberry jello salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Add enough water to make 2 cups liquid.
Bring liquid to a boil, add to Jell-O in large bowl. Chill until almost set.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and round into a ball; chop pecans to cover cheese ball if desired.

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: In skillet, cook tortillas in hot oil one at a time for 15 seconds on each side (don't overcook).
Place 2 tablespoons shredded cheese, 1 tablespoon chopped onion and 1 teaspoon chopped chilies on each tortilla and roll up.
Put seam side down in 11 x 17 x 1-inch baking dish.

title: love potion (or boozy fruit)
directions: Chop all fruit.
Put in glass jar.
Cover, but do not seal or refrigerate.
Place in dark cabinet for 2 weeks.
Every 2 weeks, add 1 cup sugar and 1 cup fruit.
This is good by itself or as a sauce.

title: banana cereal bread
directions: Combine cereal and milk; let stand 5 minutes.
Mix flour with sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir egg, shortening and bananas into cereal mixture.
Add flour mixture.
Stir just until all flour is moistened.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and finish cooling on rack.
Wrap in foil and store overnight before slicing.

title: apple caramel dip
directions: Beat well with electric mixer until creamy.
Serve with tray of apples.

title: cool whip dessert
directions: Let Cool Whip set at room temperature.
Add orange jello and stir together.
Add oranges and mix together.
Add nuts if desired.
This recipe can be used with your favorite jello and fruit.

title: goldenrod eggs
directions: Boil the eggs until hard (10 minutes after they start to boil).

title: fruit party punch
directions: Add water to orange juice and lemonade according to directions. Mix with other liquids.
Serves 50 people.

title: chocolate dream pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine Dream Whip, 1 cup milk and vanilla. Beat until fluffy.
Add 1 3/4 cup milk and Jell-O pudding mix at low speed until mixed good.
Beat on high speed 2 minutes.
Pour into two (9-inch) baked pie shells.
Chill four hours.

title: e.d.'s pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Beat at high speed for 5 1/2 minutes.
Pour into greased tube pan (I use a waxed paper lining on the bottom of the pan) and bake in pre-heated 325 degree oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool for about 10 minutes and then remove from pan onto a wire rack.
You can use your favorite icing or dust with powdered sugar.
Delicious!

title: miniature pizza appetizers
directions: Fry sausage until well done; drain well.
Pat with paper towels to remove excess grease.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Mound on slices of cocktail rye and broil or bake 3 to 5 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1 cup nuts, until smooth. Shape into a ball.
Wrap in plastic film and refrigerate overnight.
Coat with remaining nuts the next day.

title: chocolate marble loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pan, then flour lightly.
Cream 1/2 cup butter, salt and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs and mix in thoroughly.
Alternate flour mixture with milk to 1/3 of the batter.
Add chocolate and tablespoon of butter to remaining batter.
Add vanilla.
Pour white batter into loaf pan. Pour chocolate batter on top and with spatula lightly swirl the batter.
Do not overmix.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: chinese pork and green vegetables
directions: Heat oil in skillet; stir in pork 10 minutes.
Add soy sauce and garlic.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Add pea pods and green onions. Stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Stir in cornstarch blended with broth and heat about 10 minutes or until sauce is slightly thickened.

title: hamburg pot pie
directions: Mix ground beef and onions together.
In large pot (Dutch oven), layer (alternating) beef, sliced potatoes and pot pie squares.
Continue layering; add salt and pepper.
Cover with water and cook over medium to medium-high heat for about 25 minutes or until the potatoes are cooked.

title: cauliflower-broccoli salad
directions: Break cauliflower and broccoli into bite size pieces.
Combine green pepper and onions.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Let stand for an hour or overnight.
The addition of red pimento peppers add a nice holiday touch.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon.
Drain off all but 2 tablespoons of fat.
Fry chopped onion in hot fat until light brown.
Add flour and blend, then add sugar, salt, vinegar, water, celery and parsley.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour dressing over the diced potatoes.
Sprinkle with pepper.

title: cherry crumb
directions: In a bowl, cream sugars, butter, and shortening.
Add oatmeal and stir well.
Sift together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, and salt.
Add to other mixture and stir.
Press half of this mixture into a 11 1/2 X 7 1/2 X 2 inch pan.
Pour pie filling on top. Cover with rest of mixture.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.
Serve topped with ice cream.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients and put in a casserole.
Cover with the topping.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chai green tea fruit smoothie
directions: Brew chai green tea in boiling water; steep for 3 to 5 minutes. Remove tea bag.
Place all the fruit in a blender and pour in the hot tea.
Blend until smooth.
The tea gives a great taste to the fruit smoothie.

title: microwave apples
directions: Peel apples and cut into bite size pieces.
Place in 2-quart Pyrex bowl.
Add water, lemon juice and sugar.
Cook on High for 20 minutes.
Stir well.
Cook 20 minutes more.
Apples will be transparent. Makes about 2 quarts.

title: crepes
directions: Measure flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a bowl. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Beat with rotary beater until smooth.
For each crepe, lightly butter 8-inch skillet.
Heat over medium heat until butter is bubbly.
Pour 1/4 cup of the batter into skillet; immediately rotate pan until batter covers bottom. Cook until light brown; turn and brown on other side.
If desired, while warm spread applesauce, sweetened strawberries, currant jelly or raspberry jam thinly on crepes.
Roll up.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Makes 12 crepes.

title: light fettuccine alfredo
directions: In a medium saucepan, whisk milk, garlic, cornstarch and cream cheese.
Bring to boil, whisk constantly.
Reduce heat; simmer 2 minutes or until thick.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Parmesan and Molly McButter.
Pour over noodles.
Salt and pepper.
Serves 4.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper.
Cook spaghetti until done.
Mix ingredients together with 1 (8 ounce) cheese.
Top with other (8 ounce) cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: riviera dressing
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a blender jar.
Process on slow speed the chopped onion, sugar and celery seed.
Continue to process until sugar is dissolved or until well mixed.
Serve over tossed salads or cabbage salad.

title: britne's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown and white sugars.
Add eggs and beat. Add the combined flour, soda, salt and vanilla, mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 325°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Grease cake pan with 1 stick of butter.
Add 1/2 cup milk to cake mix.
Mix peaches, sugar and cinnamon together.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: apricot casserole
directions: Drain apricots for 1 hour.
Add sugar and let stand overnight.
Arrange apricots in bottom of a baking dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers and mix with melted butter.
Spread over apricots. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: scripture cake
directions: The ingredients for this recipe are found in the Bible verses King James Version.
Look up the passages to find the ingredients. (Read carefully.)
Then bake the cake.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Toast pecans in melted butter in skillet over medium heat until golden brown.
Mix sugar, pudding, canned milk, vanilla and salt.
Add toasted pecans and butter.
Pour into freezer container.
Fill to
line and freeze.
No cholesterol.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Mix yeast and warm water.
Add buttermilk, soda, sugar, cooking oil and flour.
Mix well.
Store in a covered container in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.
Dough is very "sticky."
Drop by spoonful onto greased baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° to 375° oven until golden brown (about 12 to 15 minutes).
These biscuits freeze well, also.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: In a large bowl, mix the flour, white sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Stir in grated carrots, raisins, walnuts, coconut and pineapple or apple.
In a small bowl, heat the eggs, vegetable oil and vanilla.
Stir into flour mixture until batter is just combined.
Spoon into muffin tin, filling to the top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix
together
in order listed.
Blend in blender until oil disappears.
(If you like the taste of onion, you can add one medium size onion,	finely	grated.) Once this dressing is thoroughly mixed, it will never
separate and you can store it in the refrigerator for
months.
(I
always
use
the
onion whether for fruit or not.) Good for fruit or vegetable salad.

title: stuffed peppers or meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pack into pepper half.
Place peppers in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top meat with 2 teaspoons catsup for each serving.
Bake
at
350° for 30 to 35 minutes or bake as meat loaf.

title: mini tostados
directions: Place tortilla chips on a cookie sheet.
Spread refried beans that have been mixed with can of Ro-Tel.
Place in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove and add cheese, jalapenos, shredded tomatoes and lettuce.
Top with sour cream.

title: green rice
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake without stirring in a 2-quart casserole dish with a tight fitting cover for 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove cover and toss as seasoning stays on top.
Serve hot.

title: sourdough bread starter
directions: Mix
flour,
yeast,
sugar and salt in large bowl.
Add water and beat until smooth.
Cover with towel and set in warm (80° to 85°) place (kitchen or other warm room in summer;
in oven with oven
light on in winter).	Stir 2 to 3 times a day for 3
days until
starter
is	bubbly	and produces a yeasty aroma.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces using scissors.
In large bowl, combine first 3 ingredients.
Seal bowl with lid and shake until biscuits are well coated.
Grease a Bundt pan and layer biscuits and pecans.
Bring the next 4 ingredients to a boil.
Pour over biscuits and pecans.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Immediately turn out of pan and serve hot.

title: christmas old fashioned shortbread
directions: Use pizza dough from former recipe.
Place dough in pizza pan. Top pizza with 2 cans flat fillets of anchovies, spreading each anchovie across top of dough.
Also top the pizza with the anchovie oil that's in the cans.
Spread oil with your fingers. Add Parmesan cheese (sprinkle atop pizza), also oregano.

title: cheese fudge
directions: Melt in double boiler the cheese and margarine.
Mix in separate bowl the cocoa and sugar.
Combine with cheese mixture and add vanilla and nuts.
Pour in pan and cool.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
It may sit overnight.
Add 1 head lettuce just before serving, if desired.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts and cut up into pieces in an oblong pan. Mix soups together with 3/4 can of water.
Pour over cut up chicken.
Put on layer of Cheddar cheese.
Make up Stove Top dressing per instructions on box, then put this on top of cheese and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: braunschweiger ball
directions: Combine and mix well first 6 ingredients.
Shape into a ball. Combine and blend together last 3 ingredients.
Spread over ball. Garnish with olives or nuts.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Crush wafers. Grind nuts and coconut.
Slice orange candy into small pieces.
Mix all together.
Add condensed milk.
Press into square pan or cake plate.
Let set 3 to 4 hours.
Ready to eat.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Saute onions, bell pepper, celery and margarine.
Add crab meat and season with garlic powder, salt and red pepper.
Pull off stems of mushrooms and stuff mushrooms and baste with sauce.

title: strawberry banana pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Divide filling between two crusts.
Sprinkle a layer of pecans or walnuts.
Next, layer bananas and strawberries.
Divide Cool Whip and spread evenly over the two pies.
Top with another layer of nuts.
Keep cool.

title: munnie's ambrosia
directions: Layer sliced navel oranges, pineapple tidbits (drained) and fresh grated coconut.
Sprinkle top with 1/2 cup sugar.
Repeat layers, topping again with 1/2 cup sugar.
Store covered in refrigerator.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: In saucepan, put cheese, 1/4 cup oleo and soup; heat until cheese is melted, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream.
Peel and finely chop the potatoes.
Mix with chopped onion and prepared sauce.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix together crushed corn flakes and 2 tablespoons melted oleo. Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly and slightly browned.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix together top 5 ingredients.
In the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish put a layer of bread cubes.
Spread the chicken mix atop the layer of bread cubes, then top with 3 more slices of bread cubes.
In a bowl, beat eggs with a fork, add milk; pour this mixture over casserole.
Cover with Saran Wrap, refrigerate overnight.
Next day, pour 1 can undiluted cream of mushroom soup on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.
Remove from oven, sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Return to oven approximately 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: custard sauce(microwave)
directions: Mix together all ingredients in a 4-cup measure or 1-quart casserole until well blended.
Microwave on Medium-high (70%) for 7 to 8 minutes or until back of spoon is coated.
Stir occasionally during cooking.
Chill before serving.
Recipe yields about 2 1/2 cups.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Fold into casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese and potato chips.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: selma bradley's coconut pound cake
directions: Combine sugar and Crisco; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, beating well after each one.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Gently fold in flavorings.
Bake in four 9-inch layer pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Bring milk, sugar, salt and oleo to rolling boil.
Have ready in a bowl the oats, nuts, vanilla and chocolate chips.
Put boiling ingredients in and stir.
Make balls or pack together; cool.

title: five cup fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and let stand for a few hours in refrigerator.

title: sour cream waffles
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat the yolks with milk and add to the four mixture, beating well.
Combine sour cream and soda and add to mixture.
Stir in butter or margarine. Lastly, beat the 2 egg whites and fold into the mixture.
Bake in usual manner.
This recipe will make 6 nice crisp waffles.
Try these for company breakfast.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Mix all together.
Cook 2 hours at 250° or until done.
Bake in a tube pan.

title: cora's candy
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallow cream, butterscotch and semi-sweet morsels.
Stir until melted. Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Clean and slice tomatoes.
Mix meal, flour, salt and pepper. Coat tomato slices with dry mixture.
Heat shortening in skillet over medium heat.
Place breaded slices in skillet.
Cook until brown and turn.
Cook until tender.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate cookie pudding
directions: Place crushed cookies in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. (Save a few crumbs for topping.) Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and whipped topping. Place on top of cookies. Mix vanilla pudding, chocolate pudding and milk. Pour on top of cream cheese mixture. Top with whipped topping and cookie crumbs.

title: granny's meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, onion and egg.
Shape into patties and fry in a little oil until brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: crab-cream cheese special
directions: Beat together cream cheese and milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, dash of salt and dash of pepper.
Stir in crab meat.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Makes 1 3/4 cups dip.

title: lentil soup
directions: Saute sausage, onion and garlic in oil 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except spinach.
Cook on low about 2 hours. Add spinach last 10 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs and beat.
Add the dry ingredients and beat, then add the carrots and nuts and beat again.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured, and bake at 350° until done, about 1 hour.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook lima beans as directed.
In saucepan, combine 2 tablespoons butter, flour, cheese and salt.
Add in milk and mix until thick and smooth.
Pour sauce over beans in a casserole dish. Mix remaining 1 tablespoon butter with breadcrumbs; sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: foil baked chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Have a jelly roll pan ready.
Tear six 14 x 12-inch strips of foil.
Lightly coat 1 side with vegetable spray or oil.
Place chicken breast half on each piece; sprinkle with oregano, salt and pepper.
Scatter mushrooms, then cheese on top. Dot with margarine and spoon on juice or cider.
Fold foil and seal edges securely.
Arrange packets on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until chicken is done.
Remove from oven.
Let stand 2 minutes, then place packets on plates.
Serve with chilled cream of tomato soup, carrots cooked with ginger and green onions, brownies topped with coffee ice cream and fudge sauce.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry-banana smoothie
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender.
Add a few ice cubes; whip until smooth.
Freeze what you don't use.
Makes 4 servings.
Per serving:
50 calories and 1 g. fat.

title: marinated carrot salad
directions: Cook slightly the carrots.
Do not cover.
Cook and marinate in the remaining ingredients.
Marinate overnight.
(The dressing that is leftover after the carrots are used is good on lettuce salad.)

title: creamed corn bread
directions: Mix first five ingredients with wire whisk.
In another bowl, mix last 4 ingredients and add to dry ingredients, mixing lightly. Pour into buttered or sprayed 9 inch round pan or 9 inch round black skillet.
If using skillet, get it hot first in 450 degree oven.

title: jewish pound cake
directions: Mix raisins and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Turn off gas.
Add baking soda and set aside.
Mix together sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla, flour and nuts.
Add water, raisins and baking soda mixture.

title: pecan pie
directions: Slightly beat eggs.
Mix in sugar, Golden Eagle syrup, salt and margarine.
Sprinkle pecans in.
Preheat oven at 350° and bake for approximately 45 minutes.

title: cottage cheese jello salad
directions: Drain juice off oranges and pineapple.
Then add all the other ingredients.
Mix and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg and beat well.
Dissolve baking soda in soup and add alternately with flour.
Add spices and floured fruit.
Bake in moderate oven for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast cookies
directions: Measure flour, sugar and soda into bowl and mix.
Add apricots, butter and egg.
Stir until well blended.
Stir in cereal.
Drop by teaspoons, 3 inches apart, on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350 degrees for 13-15 minutes or until cookies are lightly browned but still soft.

title: erath county pecan pie(stephenville, texas)
directions: Pour into pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Add meringue and return to oven to brown.
For meringue use 4 egg whites and a pinch of salt.
Beat until frothy.
Add 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Beat until mixture holds soft peaks. Add 8 tablespoons sugar gradually.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Heat water in a large pot over medium heat.
Add onion, celery and garlic.
Cook and stir over medium heat for 5 minutes or until lightly browned.
Add more water, if needed.

title: boneless pork loin roast
directions: Cut knife holes every 2 inches across top of meat (fat side up).
Place 1 clove of garlic in each hole.
Cover completely all sides of meat with salt; cover with pepper.
Cook at 325° for 30 minutes per pound (medium rare).

title: beef and bacon meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix together ground beef, rolled oats, chopped onion, powdered mustard, salt and pepper.
Shape into meatballs.
Wrap each meatball in a half-slice of bacon and secure with a toothpick.

title: fat-free carrot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray muffin cups with nonstick cooking spray.
Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, baking soda, baking powder and ginger.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed with mixer for 5 minutes. Beat in sugar. Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice. Add dry ingredients. Spread in a greased and floured jelly roll (15 x 10 x 1-inch) pan. Top with walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Turn out on a towel covered with powdered sugar.
Starting at narrow end, roll towel and cake together.
Cool.
Unroll and add filling. Re-roll and chill or freeze.

title: cottage waldorf salad
directions: Toss apples with lemon juice.
Stir in cottage cheese, sour cream, nuts, celery seed and salt.
Cover and chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dad's ramen noodle goulash
directions: Season and bake drumsticks thoroughly.
While chicken is baking, begin boiling eggs.
After chicken is done, prepare Ramen noodles as directed on package (slightly undercook them).
Once noodles are done, drain off water until it just covers noodles. Next, dice eggs; add some pepper and mix with noodles.
Add entire can of string beans including juice.
Place baked chicken in bottom of casserole dish; pour noodle mixture over top.
Place in oven and bake at 325° to 350° until firm or until most liquid is absorbed.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Cook chicken breasts till tender, yet moist.
(Bake or cook in waterless fry pan.)
Add bouillon and wine while chicken is cooking.
Cook noodles per directions; rinse.
Remove, chicken breasts to a 9x11 inch baking dish.
Stir mushroom soup and milk into small amount of juice where chicken cooked.
Add parsley flakes and sour cream.
Stir in noodles, coating with sauce and heating thoroughly.
Stir in Parmesan cheese.
Pour over chicken. Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: jamaican bun
directions: Dissolve sugar, butter and honey in stout over medium heat. Add spices and cheese.
Put mixed fruits in flour.
Beat eggs and mix all together.

title: corn chowder
directions: Use deep pan; usually make day before.
Cook 3 tablespoons butter and salt pork slowly until fat is melted (pork bits crisp and brown).
Add onion.
Cook slowly 5 minutes, stirring often. Add potatoes and water.
Cook until tender.
Add corn and milk. Heat 3 tablespoons butter, salt and pepper and add.
You can use additional can of corn (whole kernel), drained.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add all other ingredients and toss.
Let stand in refrigerator several hours or overnight.

title: grandma's fried chicken
directions: Pour about 1/2-inch of oil in electric skillet.
Heat to 350°. Dredge rinsed, skinless, boneless chicken breasts in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Place chicken in skillet, turn down heat to 250°.
Brown on both sides.
Cook for about 1 hour or until done.

title: dream dessert
directions: Mix pudding as directed (add 1/2 Cool Whip to each).
Layer a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Layer chocolate pudding (1/2 Cool Whip added), layer of graham crackers and layer of vanilla pudding (1/2 Cool Whip added).
Layer top with the Cool Whip and pudding mixture and refrigerate overnight.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix hot roll mix as per directions on the back of the box. Set aside and let rise.
Fry cabbage in one skillet.
Brown hamburger meat and onion in another skillet until done.
Mix hamburger and cabbage together.
Salt and pepper mixture to taste. When double the original size, take dough and roll out on floured surface until not sticky any more.
Tear off golfball size piece of dough and roll out on floured surface.
Put cabbage mixture in center and fold up and place in a greased and floured pan and bake at 350° until golden brown on top.

title: creamy chocolate pie
directions: Place chocolate wafers and butter in a 9-inch pie plate; press into crust.
In blender, place chocolate chips, egg yolks, coffee and cream; blend until smooth.
The hot cream will cook the eggs. Pour into pie crust and refrigerate until firm.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add other ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
